cmky154o0000r38zvsr18exhe	cmjrjorwn0003b3n6srvqqp17	A developer transfers ownership of the streets in a subdivision to the county.	{"Eminent Domain",Condemnation,Dedication,Escheat}	2	{"correct": "Dedication is the voluntary transfer of private property (like streets or parks) by a developer to the government for public use.", "incorrect": ["Eminent Domain. Eminent domain is the government's power to take private property for public use, usually against the owner's will.", "Condemnation is the legal process used to enforce eminent domain.<div><br></div>", "", "Escheat is the reversion of property to the state when an owner dies without a will and without heirs.<div><br></div>"]}	1	chapter	2026-01-28 12:57:05.695	2026-01-28 13:00:41.136	\N	\N	\N	\N	/audio/1769605230281-Dedication_is_the_vo.mp3	/timestamps/1769605230281-Dedication_is_the_vo.timestamps.json	["/audio/1769605231518-Eminent_Domain__Emin.mp3", "/audio/1769605232507-Condemnation_is_the_.mp3", "", "/audio/1769605233610-Escheat_is_the_rever.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1769605231518-Eminent_Domain__Emin.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1769605232507-Condemnation_is_the_.timestamps.json", "", "/timestamps/1769605233610-Escheat_is_the_rever.timestamps.json"]	["/audio/1769605227436-Eminent_Domain.mp3", "/audio/1769605228021-Condemnation.mp3", "/audio/1769605228542-Dedication.mp3", "/audio/1769605228995-Escheat.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1769605227436-Eminent_Domain.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1769605228021-Condemnation.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1769605228542-Dedication.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1769605228995-Escheat.timestamps.json"]	/audio/1769605226729-A_developer_transfer.mp3	/timestamps/1769605226729-A_developer_transfer.timestamps.json
cmljznipw0084r4ev2kpnaou7	cmk8if4vt0000sxhb8i62wdi6	An applicant for a real estate license was convicted of a misdemeanor 10 years ago. Adjudication was withheld. Does the applicant need to disclose this on the application?	{"No, because it was a misdemeanor","No, because adjudication was withheld","No, because it was more than 5 years ago","Yes, all criminal history must be disclosed"}	3	{"correct": "Applicants must disclose all criminal convictions, pleas of nolo contendere (no contest), or guilty pleas, even if adjudication was withheld.", "incorrect": ["Misdemeanors must be disclosed.&nbsp;", "Withheld adjudication does not exempt you from disclosure.", "&nbsp;There is no time limit on the disclosure requirement.", ""]}	22	chapter	2026-02-12 21:46:20.362	2026-02-12 21:46:20.362	\N	\N	\N	\N	/audio/1770932773218-Applicants_must_disc.mp3	/timestamps/1770932773218-Applicants_must_disc.timestamps.json	["/audio/1770932774402-Misdemeanors_must_be.mp3", "/audio/1770932775120-Withheld_adjudicatio.mp3", "/audio/1770932775945-There_is_no_time_lim.mp3", ""]	["/timestamps/1770932774402-Misdemeanors_must_be.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1770932775120-Withheld_adjudicatio.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1770932775945-There_is_no_time_lim.timestamps.json", ""]	["/audio/1770932768874-No__because_it_was_a.mp3", "/audio/1770932769855-No__because_adjudica.mp3", "/audio/1770932770776-No__because_it_was_m.mp3", "/audio/1770932771624-Yes__all_criminal_hi.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1770932768874-No__because_it_was_a.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1770932769855-No__because_adjudica.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1770932770776-No__because_it_was_m.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1770932771624-Yes__all_criminal_hi.timestamps.json"]	/audio/1770932768182-An_applicant_for_a_r.mp3	/timestamps/1770932768182-An_applicant_for_a_r.timestamps.json
cmljzvldi0088r4evhr1hn5s2	cmk8if4vt0000sxhb8i62wdi6	What is the purpose of the "Summary of Applicants" (SOA) agenda at a FREC meeting?	{" To list all applicants who passed the state exam that month","To review applications with background issues or criminal history for approval or denial","To swear in new licensees"," To review applications for mutual recognition only"}	1	{"correct": "The SOA is the list of applicants whose files require individual review by the Commission due to criminal history or other potential disqualifiers found during the background check.", "incorrect": ["Most standard applications are processed by DBPR staff without FREC review.", "", "This is not the function of the SOA.", "The SOA includes all applicant types with background questions, not just mutual recognition."]}	24	chapter	2026-02-12 21:52:37.11	2026-02-12 21:52:37.11	\N	\N	\N	\N	/audio/1770933150260-The_SOA_is_the_list_.mp3	/timestamps/1770933150260-The_SOA_is_the_list_.timestamps.json	["/audio/1770933151234-Most_standard_applic.mp3", "", "/audio/1770933151877-This_is_not_the_func.mp3", "/audio/1770933152845-The_SOA_includes_all.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1770933151234-Most_standard_applic.timestamps.json", "", "/timestamps/1770933151877-This_is_not_the_func.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1770933152845-The_SOA_includes_all.timestamps.json"]	["/audio/1770933145565-To_list_all_applican.mp3", "/audio/1770933146710-To_review_applicatio.mp3", "/audio/1770933147339-To_swear_in_new_lice.mp3", "/audio/1770933148535-To_review_applicatio.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1770933145565-To_list_all_applican.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1770933146710-To_review_applicatio.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1770933147339-To_swear_in_new_lice.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1770933148535-To_review_applicatio.timestamps.json"]	/audio/1770933144286-What_is_the_purpose_.mp3	/timestamps/1770933144286-What_is_the_purpose_.timestamps.json
cmky18z6s000t38zv267upr79	cmjrjorwn0003b3n6srvqqp17	Which statement regarding a Comparative Market Analysis (CMA) is TRUE?	{"It must comply with USPAP standards.","It is an appraisal","It is exempt from USPAP standards"," It cannot be performed for a fee"}	2	{"correct": "Real estate licensees preparing a CMA are exempt from the Uniform Standards of Professional Appraisal Practice.", "incorrect": ["Only formal appraisals must comply with USPAP; CMAs are exempt.", "A CMA is an opinion of value for marketing purposes, distinct from a formal appraisal.", "", "Licensees may charge a fee for a CMA, though it is often provided as a courtesy to gain a listing."]}	2	chapter	2026-01-28 13:00:05.283	2026-01-28 13:00:05.283	\N	\N	\N	\N	/audio/1769605197908-Real_estate_licensee.mp3	/timestamps/1769605197908-Real_estate_licensee.timestamps.json	["/audio/1769605198974-Only_formal_appraisa.mp3", "/audio/1769605199897-A_CMA_is_an_opinion_.mp3", "", "/audio/1769605201113-Licensees_may_charge.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1769605198974-Only_formal_appraisa.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1769605199897-A_CMA_is_an_opinion_.timestamps.json", "", "/timestamps/1769605201113-Licensees_may_charge.timestamps.json"]	["/audio/1769605194287-It_must_comply_with_.mp3", "/audio/1769605194874-It_is_an_appraisal.mp3", "/audio/1769605195599-It_is_exempt_from_US.mp3", "/audio/1769605196358-It_cannot_be_perform.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1769605194287-It_must_comply_with_.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1769605194874-It_is_an_appraisal.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1769605195599-It_is_exempt_from_US.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1769605196358-It_cannot_be_perform.timestamps.json"]	/audio/1769605193563-Which_statement_rega.mp3	/timestamps/1769605193563-Which_statement_rega.timestamps.json
cmky1cve8000v38zvv6rort34	cmjrjorwn0003b3n6srvqqp17	A map recorded in public records showing the division of land into lots and blocks is called	{"A deed","A survey","A subdivision plat map","A zoning variance"}	2	{"correct": "This map shows the layout of a subdivision, including lots, blocks, and streets, and is recorded in public records.", "incorrect": ["A deed is a document that conveys title from one party to another.", "A survey outlines the specific boundaries of a single property but is not the master map for the entire subdivision recorded for development.", "", "A variance is permission to deviate from zoning rules, not a map."]}	3	chapter	2026-01-28 13:03:06.992	2026-01-28 13:03:06.992	\N	\N	\N	\N	/audio/1769605379055-This_map_shows_the_l.mp3	/timestamps/1769605379055-This_map_shows_the_l.timestamps.json	["/audio/1769605379927-A_deed_is_a_document.mp3", "/audio/1769605381510-A_survey_outlines_th.mp3", "", "/audio/1769605382336-A_variance_is_permis.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1769605379927-A_deed_is_a_document.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1769605381510-A_survey_outlines_th.timestamps.json", "", "/timestamps/1769605382336-A_variance_is_permis.timestamps.json"]	["/audio/1769605375810-A_deed.mp3", "/audio/1769605376390-A_survey.mp3", "/audio/1769605377066-A_subdivision_plat_m.mp3", "/audio/1769605377701-A_zoning_variance.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1769605375810-A_deed.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1769605376390-A_survey.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1769605377066-A_subdivision_plat_m.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1769605377701-A_zoning_variance.timestamps.json"]	/audio/1769605375314-A_map_recorded_in_pu.mp3	/timestamps/1769605375314-A_map_recorded_in_pu.timestamps.json
cmljzzmiz008ar4ev40du20of	cmk8if4vt0000sxhb8i62wdi6	An applicant submits a completed application to the DBPR. If the Department does not approve or deny the application within 90 days, what is the outcome?	{"The application is automatically denied","The application is deemed approved","The applicant must submit a new fee","The applicant must request a hearing"}	1	{"correct": "Florida statutes require the Department to approve or deny a properly completed application within 90 days. If they fail to do so, the application is considered approved by default.", "incorrect": ["Inaction by the state results in approval, not denial.", "", "No additional fee is required due to the Department's delay.", "A hearing is not necessary because the approval is automatic.&nbsp;", ""]}	25	chapter	2026-02-12 21:55:45.227	2026-02-12 21:55:45.227	\N	\N	\N	\N	/audio/1770933337723-Florida_statutes_req.mp3	/timestamps/1770933337723-Florida_statutes_req.timestamps.json	["/audio/1770933338607-Inaction_by_the_stat.mp3", "", "/audio/1770933339506-No_additional_fee_is.mp3", "/audio/1770933340368-A_hearing_is_not_nec.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1770933338607-Inaction_by_the_stat.timestamps.json", "", "/timestamps/1770933339506-No_additional_fee_is.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1770933340368-A_hearing_is_not_nec.timestamps.json"]	["/audio/1770933333891-The_application_is_a.mp3", "/audio/1770933334653-The_application_is_d.mp3", "/audio/1770933335278-The_applicant_must_s.mp3", "/audio/1770933335938-The_applicant_must_r.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1770933333891-The_application_is_a.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1770933334653-The_application_is_d.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1770933335278-The_applicant_must_s.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1770933335938-The_applicant_must_r.timestamps.json"]	/audio/1770933333192-An_applicant_submits.mp3	/timestamps/1770933333192-An_applicant_submits.timestamps.json
cmlk03ska008cr4evf4etdiqf	cmk8if4vt0000sxhb8i62wdi6	An applicant fails the state exam and wishes to review the questions they missed. How many days do they have to make this request?	{"10 days","15 days","21 days","30 days"}	2	{"correct": "Candidates are entitled to review their most recent examination questions that they answered incorrectly. The request to review must be made within 21 days from the date of the examination.", "incorrect": ["This is the timeline for address changes, not exam review.", "This is not the correct statutory timeframe.", "", "This is the time to file an appeal for a final order, but the specific request to review the exam must be made within 21 days.<div><br></div>"]}	26	chapter	2026-02-12 21:58:59.674	2026-02-12 21:58:59.674	\N	\N	\N	\N	/audio/1770933529618-Candidates_are_entit.mp3	/timestamps/1770933529618-Candidates_are_entit.timestamps.json	["/audio/1770933530613-This_is_the_timeline.mp3", "/audio/1770933531518-This_is_not_the_corr.mp3", "", "/audio/1770933533156-This_is_the_time_to_.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1770933530613-This_is_the_timeline.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1770933531518-This_is_not_the_corr.timestamps.json", "", "/timestamps/1770933533156-This_is_the_time_to_.timestamps.json"]	["/audio/1770933525935-10_days.mp3", "/audio/1770933526772-15_days.mp3", "/audio/1770933527474-21_days.mp3", "/audio/1770933528048-30_days.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1770933525935-10_days.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1770933526772-15_days.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1770933527474-21_days.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1770933528048-30_days.timestamps.json"]	/audio/1770933525354-An_applicant_fails_t.mp3	/timestamps/1770933525354-An_applicant_fails_t.timestamps.json
cmltvg13l00qyr4evltq2rjes	cmlslqsgt00l1r4evfhnwe7be	Which business entity can register as a real estate broker?	{"Limited partnership","Business trust","Cooperative association","Joint venture"}	0	{"correct": "<div>A Limited partnership may legally register as a real estate brokerage in Florida, provided that there is at least one general partner who holds an active real estate broker license.<br></div>", "incorrect": ["", "A Business trust (or common-law trust) cannot be registered with the DBPR as a real estate brokerage.", "A Cooperative association is permitted to buy, sell, and lease property for its own use, but it cannot be registered as a real estate brokerage to perform services for the public.", "<div>A Joint venture is typically a temporary business arrangement formed for a single transaction or project. Because of its temporary nature, a joint venture itself cannot be registered as a real estate brokerage entity.</div>"]}	37	chapter	2026-02-19 19:46:14.289	2026-02-19 20:02:15.556	\N	\N	\N	\N	/audio/1771531330859-A_Limited_partnershi.mp3	/timestamps/1771531330859-A_Limited_partnershi.timestamps.json	["", "/audio/1771531332276-A_Business_trust__or.mp3", "/audio/1771531333816-A_Cooperative_associ.mp3", "/audio/1771531335387-A_Joint_venture_is_t.mp3"]	["", "/timestamps/1771531332276-A_Business_trust__or.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771531333816-A_Cooperative_associ.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771531335387-A_Joint_venture_is_t.timestamps.json"]	["/audio/1771531327274-Limited_partnership.mp3", "/audio/1771531327859-Business_trust.mp3", "/audio/1771531328599-Cooperative_associat.mp3", "/audio/1771531329161-Joint_venture.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1771531327274-Limited_partnership.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771531327859-Business_trust.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771531328599-Cooperative_associat.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771531329161-Joint_venture.timestamps.json"]	/audio/1771531326705-Which_business_entit.mp3	/timestamps/1771531326705-Which_business_entit.timestamps.json
cmkzmvvre000jd90dsh3l9pug	cmjrjorwn0003b3n6srvqqp17	Which organization is the largest trade association in the world?	{"The Florida Real Estate Commission (FREC) ","The Department of Housing and Urban Development (HUD) ","The National Association of REALTORS (NAR) ","The Division of Real Estate (DRE)"}	2	{"correct": "The NAR is the largest professional trade organization globally, representing millions of members.", "incorrect": ["The FREC is a regulatory body, not a trade association.", "HUD is a federal government agency, not a trade association.", "", "The DRE provides administrative support to the FREC and is a government division, not a trade group."]}	6	chapter	2026-01-29 15:53:32.041	2026-01-29 15:53:32.041	\N	\N	\N	\N	/audio/1769702005051-The_NAR_is_the_large.mp3	/timestamps/1769702005051-The_NAR_is_the_large.timestamps.json	["/audio/1769702005895-The_FREC_is_a_regula.mp3", "/audio/1769702006643-HUD_is_a_federal_gov.mp3", "", "/audio/1769702007782-The_DRE_provides_adm.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1769702005895-The_FREC_is_a_regula.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1769702006643-HUD_is_a_federal_gov.timestamps.json", "", "/timestamps/1769702007782-The_DRE_provides_adm.timestamps.json"]	["/audio/1769702000604-The_Florida_Real_Est.mp3", "/audio/1769702001773-The_Department_of_Ho.mp3", "/audio/1769702003111-The_National_Associa.mp3", "/audio/1769702003762-The_Division_of_Real.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1769702000604-The_Florida_Real_Est.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1769702001773-The_Department_of_Ho.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1769702003111-The_National_Associa.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1769702003762-The_Division_of_Real.timestamps.json"]	/audio/1769701999901-Which_organization_i.mp3	/timestamps/1769701999901-Which_organization_i.timestamps.json
cmlprl1f400jmr4ev4gjcm95s	cmlpniy5e00gyr4ev7l7y4vur	Brokers must retain disclosure documents for residential transactions that result in:	{"A showing of the property","A verbal offer","A written offer to purchase and sell real property.","A listing agreement only."}	2	{"correct": "Retention is required for files that result in a written offer to purchase and sell real property.", "incorrect": ["A mere showing does not trigger the 5-year retention rule if no offer results.", "It has to be a written offer&nbsp;", "", "Retention applies to purchase offers, not just listing agreements."]}	16	chapter	2026-02-16 22:47:04.816	2026-02-16 23:17:24.594	\N	\N	\N	\N	/audio/1771283841552-Retention_is_require.mp3	/timestamps/1771283841552-Retention_is_require.timestamps.json	["/audio/1771283842656-A_mere_showing_does_.mp3", "/audio/1771283843430-It_has_to_be_a_writt.mp3", "", "/audio/1771283844372-Retention_applies_to.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1771283842656-A_mere_showing_does_.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771283843430-It_has_to_be_a_writt.timestamps.json", "", "/timestamps/1771283844372-Retention_applies_to.timestamps.json"]	["/audio/1771283838179-A_showing_of_the_pro.mp3", "/audio/1771283838773-A_verbal_offer.mp3", "/audio/1771283839683-A_written_offer_to_p.mp3", "/audio/1771283840425-A_listing_agreement_.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1771283838179-A_showing_of_the_pro.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771283838773-A_verbal_offer.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771283839683-A_written_offer_to_p.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771283840425-A_listing_agreement_.timestamps.json"]	/audio/1771283837449-Brokers_must_retain_.mp3	/timestamps/1771283837449-Brokers_must_retain_.timestamps.json
cmkzmn7m4000fd90dj3jrjkax	cmjrjorwn0003b3n6srvqqp17	Which level of government has the most direct impact on real estate property owners through zoning and property taxation?	{"Federal government","State government","Local government ","International government"}	2	{"correct": "Local government bodies (cities and counties) are responsible for property taxes, zoning ordinances, and building codes which directly affect property use and ownership costs.", "incorrect": ["The federal government influences real estate primarily through monetary policy and laws like Fair Housing, rather than direct property regulation like zoning.", "State government handles documentary stamps and recording of documents, but does not typically handle specific property zoning.<div><br></div>", "", "There is no international government body that regulates local real estate zoning or taxation."]}	4	chapter	2026-01-29 15:46:47.5	2026-02-19 17:03:02.696	\N	\N	\N	\N	/audio/1769701598937-Local_government_bod.mp3	/timestamps/1769701598937-Local_government_bod.timestamps.json	["/audio/1769701600545-The_federal_governme.mp3", "/audio/1769701601920-State_government_han.mp3", "", "/audio/1769701603016-There_is_no_internat.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1769701600545-The_federal_governme.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1769701601920-State_government_han.timestamps.json", "", "/timestamps/1769701603016-There_is_no_internat.timestamps.json"]	["/audio/1769701595608-Federal_government.mp3", "/audio/1769701596294-State_government.mp3", "/audio/1769701596889-Local_government.mp3", "/audio/1769701597451-International_govern.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1769701595608-Federal_government.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1769701596294-State_government.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1769701596889-Local_government.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1769701597451-International_govern.timestamps.json"]	/audio/1769701594720-Which_level_of_gover.mp3	/timestamps/1769701594720-Which_level_of_gover.timestamps.json
cmkzn09zw000ld90d6a5s59s9	cmjrjorwn0003b3n6srvqqp17	There are more property managers now than ever before because:	{"It became easier to get a CAM license ","There are fewer absentee owners ","There are more absentee owners ","There is a larger demand for rental properties"}	2	{"correct": "&nbsp;The growth in the property management field is primarily attributed to the increase in absentee owners (investors who own real estate but do not reside on the property). These owners typically hire professionals to manage their investments.", "incorrect": ["The growth of the profession is driven by market demand (owners needing help), not the difficulty level of obtaining a license.", "A decrease in absentee owners would reduce the need for property managers, not increase it.", "", "While a high demand for rentals contributes to the market, the specific structural reason for the rise in professional management is the ownership structure (absentee owners) rather than just tenant demand."]}	7	chapter	2026-01-29 15:56:57.116	2026-01-29 15:56:57.116	\N	\N	\N	\N	/audio/1769702209417-The_growth_in_the_pr.mp3	/timestamps/1769702209417-The_growth_in_the_pr.timestamps.json	["/audio/1769702210865-The_growth_of_the_pr.mp3", "/audio/1769702211938-A_decrease_in_absent.mp3", "", "/audio/1769702213679-While_a_high_demand_.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1769702210865-The_growth_of_the_pr.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1769702211938-A_decrease_in_absent.timestamps.json", "", "/timestamps/1769702213679-While_a_high_demand_.timestamps.json"]	["/audio/1769702204579-It_became_easier_to_.mp3", "/audio/1769702205232-There_are_fewer_abse.mp3", "/audio/1769702206301-There_are_more_absen.mp3", "/audio/1769702207500-There_is_a_larger_de.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1769702204579-It_became_easier_to_.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1769702205232-There_are_fewer_abse.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1769702206301-There_are_more_absen.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1769702207500-There_is_a_larger_de.timestamps.json"]	/audio/1769702203808-There_are_more_prope.mp3	/timestamps/1769702203808-There_are_more_prope.timestamps.json
cmms3npg700ij4be72jq1lci8	cmmry1yz800fh4be796sih9l4	Tom grants a property to his mother, Mary, for the rest of her life. The deed stipulates that upon Mary's death, the property will pass to Tom's daughter, Sarah. What type of estate does Sarah possess while Mary is still alive?	{"A reversionary estate","A leasehold estate","A remainder estate","A fee simple absolute"}	2	{"correct": "&nbsp;A remainder estate is a future interest given to a third party (the remainderman) that takes effect after the termination of a prior estate, such as a life estate. Sarah is the designated third party who gets the property after Mary dies.", "incorrect": ["A reversionary estate occurs when the property returns to the original grantor (Tom), not a third party.", "A leasehold is a tenant's right to occupy a property under a lease, not an ownership interest.", "", "While Sarah will eventually have a fee simple absolute estate after Mary dies, she currently only possesses a remainder estate while Mary is living."]}	26	chapter	2026-03-15 18:40:19.351	2026-03-15 19:07:04.542	\N	\N	\N	\N	/audio/1773601620122-A_remainder_estate_i.mp3	/timestamps/1773601620122-A_remainder_estate_i.timestamps.json	["/audio/1773601621698-A_reversionary_estat.mp3", "/audio/1773601622846-A_leasehold_is_a_ten.mp3", "", "/audio/1773601624356-While_Sarah_will_eve.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1773601621698-A_reversionary_estat.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1773601622846-A_leasehold_is_a_ten.timestamps.json", "", "/timestamps/1773601624356-While_Sarah_will_eve.timestamps.json"]	["/audio/1773601615397-A_reversionary_estat.mp3", "/audio/1773601616200-A_leasehold_estate.mp3", "/audio/1773601617029-A_remainder_estate.mp3", "/audio/1773601617670-A_fee_simple_absolut.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1773601615397-A_reversionary_estat.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1773601616200-A_leasehold_estate.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1773601617029-A_remainder_estate.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1773601617670-A_fee_simple_absolut.timestamps.json"]	/audio/1773601614572-Tom_grants_a_propert.mp3	/timestamps/1773601614572-Tom_grants_a_propert.timestamps.json
cmlk073rw008er4evkzs47b40	cmk8if4vt0000sxhb8i62wdi6	A licensee is an active duty member of the U.S. Army. They are not practicing real estate in Florida. Which statement is TRUE regarding their license renewal?	{"They must renew their license and pay fees every 2 years like all other licensees","They are exempt from renewal requirements during active duty and for 2 years after  discharge","They must complete continuing education but are exempt from the renewal fee","Their license is automatically revoked upon deployment"}	1	{"correct": "Section 455.02, F.S. exempts active duty members from renewal provisions while serving and for 2 years post-discharge, provided they do not practice for profit.", "incorrect": ["They are statutorily exempt.", "", "They are exempt from CE as well if not practicing.", "Military service protects the license; it does not revoke it."]}	27	chapter	2026-02-12 22:01:34.172	2026-02-12 22:01:34.172	\N	\N	\N	\N	/audio/1770933687493-Section_455_02__F_S_.mp3	/timestamps/1770933687493-Section_455_02__F_S_.timestamps.json	["/audio/1770933688181-They_are_statutorily.mp3", "", "/audio/1770933689036-They_are_exempt_from.mp3", "/audio/1770933689895-Military_service_pro.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1770933688181-They_are_statutorily.timestamps.json", "", "/timestamps/1770933689036-They_are_exempt_from.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1770933689895-Military_service_pro.timestamps.json"]	["/audio/1770933682293-They_must_renew_thei.mp3", "/audio/1770933683521-They_are_exempt_from.mp3", "/audio/1770933684676-They_must_complete_c.mp3", "/audio/1770933685465-Their_license_is_aut.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1770933682293-They_must_renew_thei.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1770933683521-They_are_exempt_from.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1770933684676-They_must_complete_c.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1770933685465-Their_license_is_aut.timestamps.json"]	/audio/1770933681008-A_licensee_is_an_act.mp3	/timestamps/1770933681008-A_licensee_is_an_act.timestamps.json
cmlk0bf7g008gr4ev9zwzsnfk	cmk8if4vt0000sxhb8i62wdi6	The spouse of a U.S. Navy officer is a licensed real estate sales associate. The family is stationed in Virginia for 3 years. Is the spouse required to renew their Florida license during this time?	{"Yes, they must complete CE and pay fees to keep the license active","No, they are exempt from renewal requirements because they are absent from Florida due to their spouse's military duties","No, but they must place their license in \\"Voluntary Inactive\\" status and pay a fee","Yes, but they only have to pay half the renewal fee"}	1	{"correct": "Chapter 455.02 extends the renewal exemption to spouses who are absent from the state due to the service member's military orders.<div><br></div>", "incorrect": ["They are exempt while absent due to military orders.", "", "The exemption covers the renewal process itself; they do not need to switch to voluntary inactive and pay.", "There is no \\"half fee\\" provision; it is a full exemption."]}	28	chapter	2026-02-12 22:04:55.612	2026-02-12 22:04:55.612	\N	\N	\N	\N	/audio/1770933888570-Chapter_455_02_exten.mp3	/timestamps/1770933888570-Chapter_455_02_exten.timestamps.json	["/audio/1770933889508-They_are_exempt_whil.mp3", "", "/audio/1770933890695-The_exemption_covers.mp3", "/audio/1770933891695-There_is_no__half_fe.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1770933889508-They_are_exempt_whil.timestamps.json", "", "/timestamps/1770933890695-The_exemption_covers.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1770933891695-There_is_no__half_fe.timestamps.json"]	["/audio/1770933882920-Yes__they_must_compl.mp3", "/audio/1770933884240-No__they_are_exempt_.mp3", "/audio/1770933885591-No__but_they_must_pl.mp3", "/audio/1770933886407-Yes__but_they_only_h.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1770933882920-Yes__they_must_compl.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1770933884240-No__they_are_exempt_.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1770933885591-No__but_they_must_pl.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1770933886407-Yes__but_they_only_h.timestamps.json"]	/audio/1770933881712-The_spouse_of_a_U_S_.mp3	/timestamps/1770933881712-The_spouse_of_a_U_S_.timestamps.json
cmltvpnm700r0r4evfh83hdzx	cmlslqsgt00l1r4evfhnwe7be	A sales associate receives conflicting demands from a buyer and a seller regarding an escrow deposit. What is the deadline for the sales associate to notify their employing broker of this dispute?	{"Immediately, or no later than the end of the next business day","Within 3 business day","Within 15 business days","Within 30 business days"}	0	{"correct": "A sales associate is an agent of the broker. If an associate receives conflicting demands or has any good-faith doubt about who is entitled to the escrow funds, they must notify their employing broker immediately, which means no later than the end of the next business day. This ensures the broker has enough time to meet their own legal deadlines.", "incorrect": ["", "Three business days is the timeframe a broker has to deposit actual funds into the escrow account after the associate receives them, not the deadline to report a dispute.", "Fifteen business days is the deadline for the broker to notify the Florida Real Estate Commission (FREC) in writing about the conflicting demands.", "<div>Thirty business days is the deadline for the broker to formally institute a settlement procedure.</div>"]}	38	chapter	2026-02-19 19:53:43.284	2026-02-19 20:02:26.851	\N	\N	\N	\N	/audio/1771531342544-A_sales_associate_is.mp3	/timestamps/1771531342544-A_sales_associate_is.timestamps.json	["", "/audio/1771531344264-Three_business_days_.mp3", "/audio/1771531345603-Fifteen_business_day.mp3", "/audio/1771531346655-Thirty_business_days.mp3"]	["", "/timestamps/1771531344264-Three_business_days_.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771531345603-Fifteen_business_day.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771531346655-Thirty_business_days.timestamps.json"]	["/audio/1771531338025-Immediately__or_no_l.mp3", "/audio/1771531338682-Within_3_business_da.mp3", "/audio/1771531339356-Within_15_business_d.mp3", "/audio/1771531340097-Within_30_business_d.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1771531338025-Immediately__or_no_l.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771531338682-Within_3_business_da.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771531339356-Within_15_business_d.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771531340097-Within_30_business_d.timestamps.json"]	/audio/1771531337226-A_sales_associate_re.mp3	/timestamps/1771531337226-A_sales_associate_re.timestamps.json
cmkznjh4o000rd90d1q7zrnds	cmjrjorwn0003b3n6srvqqp17	Effective advertising involving developing a database of prospects to direct a specific message is called	{"Institutional advertising","Computer efficiency","Target marketing",Merchandizing}	2	{"correct": "Target marketing involves defining a specific group of potential customers (prospects) and directing marketing efforts specifically toward them. Developing a database of prospects to send a tailored, specific message is a key component of this strategy. In real estate, \\"farming\\" is a common form of target marketing where a licensee focuses on a specific demographic or geographic area.", "incorrect": ["Institutional advertising is designed to build the reputation and brand awareness of the brokerage or company as a whole, rather than selling a specific property or targeting a specific list of prospects with a direct message.", "This is a general term referring to how well a computer system performs tasks. While computers are used to maintain databases, \\"computer efficiency\\" is not the marketing strategy itself.", "", "Merchandising typically refers to the presentation and display of products in a retail environment to stimulate interest and sales. It is not the term used for database-driven prospect marketing in real estate."]}	10	chapter	2026-01-29 16:11:52.823	2026-01-29 16:12:55.143	\N	\N	\N	\N	/audio/1769703108917-Target_marketing_inv.mp3	/timestamps/1769703108917-Target_marketing_inv.timestamps.json	["/audio/1769703151707-Institutional_advert.mp3", "/audio/1769703156097-This_is_a_general_te.mp3", "", "/audio/1769703159888-Merchandising_typica.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1769703151707-Institutional_advert.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1769703156097-This_is_a_general_te.timestamps.json", "", "/timestamps/1769703159888-Merchandising_typica.timestamps.json"]	["/audio/1769703104513-Institutional_advert.mp3", "/audio/1769703105143-Computer_efficiency.mp3", "/audio/1769703105698-Target_marketing.mp3", "/audio/1769703106300-Merchandizing.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1769703104513-Institutional_advert.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1769703105143-Computer_efficiency.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1769703105698-Target_marketing.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1769703106300-Merchandizing.timestamps.json"]	/audio/1769703103719-Effective_advertisin.mp3	/timestamps/1769703103719-Effective_advertisin.timestamps.json
cmlk2g084008ur4ev52uco9ts	cmk8if4vt0000sxhb8i62wdi6	Which individual is performing a service that requires a real estate license?	{"An owner selling their own home","A salaried employee of an apartment complex leasing units","An attorney acting as an executor of a will selling the deceased's property","A person auctioning farm land for a neighbor for a flat fee"}	3	{"correct": "Auctioning real property for another person for compensation (even a flat fee) is a real estate service that requires a license.", "incorrect": ["Property owners are exempt from licensure when buying, selling, or leasing their own property.", "Salaried employees of an apartment community who work in an onsite rental office are exempt, provided they do not receive a commission (or bonus) for each transaction.", "Persons appointed by a court of law to perform specific duties, such as personal representatives (executors), guardians, or trustees, are exempt from licensure while acting within the scope of their appointment.", ""]}	35	chapter	2026-02-12 23:04:28.633	2026-02-12 23:04:28.633	\N	\N	\N	\N	/audio/1770937460067-Auctioning_real_prop.mp3	/timestamps/1770937460067-Auctioning_real_prop.timestamps.json	["/audio/1770937461417-Property_owners_are_.mp3", "/audio/1770937463114-Salaried_employees_o.mp3", "/audio/1770937464932-Persons_appointed_by.mp3", ""]	["/timestamps/1770937461417-Property_owners_are_.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1770937463114-Salaried_employees_o.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1770937464932-Persons_appointed_by.timestamps.json", ""]	["/audio/1770937455205-An_owner_selling_the.mp3", "/audio/1770937456079-A_salaried_employee_.mp3", "/audio/1770937457589-An_attorney_acting_a.mp3", "/audio/1770937458694-A_person_auctioning_.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1770937455205-An_owner_selling_the.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1770937456079-A_salaried_employee_.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1770937457589-An_attorney_acting_a.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1770937458694-A_person_auctioning_.timestamps.json"]	/audio/1770937454333-Which_individual_is_.mp3	/timestamps/1770937454333-Which_individual_is_.timestamps.json
cmlk2il3j008wr4ev8ekx9erh	cmk8if4vt0000sxhb8i62wdi6	A sales associate fails to complete their 45-hour post-licensure course before their first renewal date. What is the status of their license?	{"Involuntary Inactive",Suspended,"Null and Void","Voluntary Inactive"}	2	{"correct": "Failure to complete the post-license education requirement results in the license becoming null and void. The individual must re-qualify as a new applicant (retake the 63-hour course and state exam).", "incorrect": ["This status applies when a licensee fails to complete continuing education (14 hours) after the first renewal cycle, not the initial post-licensing requirement.&nbsp;", "Suspension is a disciplinary penalty for a violation of the law, not for failing to complete education.&nbsp;", "", "This is a status chosen by a licensee who has completed their education but chooses not to practice."]}	36	chapter	2026-02-12 23:06:29.07	2026-02-12 23:06:29.07	\N	\N	\N	\N	/audio/1770937581133-Failure_to_complete_.mp3	/timestamps/1770937581133-Failure_to_complete_.timestamps.json	["/audio/1770937583005-This_status_applies_.mp3", "/audio/1770937584241-Suspension_is_a_disc.mp3", "", "/audio/1770937585361-This_is_a_status_cho.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1770937583005-This_status_applies_.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1770937584241-Suspension_is_a_disc.timestamps.json", "", "/timestamps/1770937585361-This_is_a_status_cho.timestamps.json"]	["/audio/1770937577355-Involuntary_Inactive.mp3", "/audio/1770937577995-Suspended.mp3", "/audio/1770937578571-Null_and_Void.mp3", "/audio/1770937579391-Voluntary_Inactive.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1770937577355-Involuntary_Inactive.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1770937577995-Suspended.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1770937578571-Null_and_Void.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1770937579391-Voluntary_Inactive.timestamps.json"]	/audio/1770937576652-A_sales_associate_fa.mp3	/timestamps/1770937576652-A_sales_associate_fa.timestamps.json
cmlprpm0100jor4evxwyy5ptm	cmlpniy5e00gyr4ev7l7y4vur	What specific duties does a Designated Sales Associate owe to their client?	{"Limited representation only","Fiduciary responsibility","No brokerage duties only","The same duties as a Transaction Broker"}	1	{"correct": "Each designated sales associate has a \\"fiduciary responsibility\\" to their client.", "incorrect": ["Limited representation describes a Transaction Broker.", "", "They owe much more than just the No Brokerage duties.", "Transaction Brokers are non-fiduciary; Designated Associates are fiduciaries."]}	17	chapter	2026-02-16 22:50:38.112	2026-02-16 23:17:32.992	\N	\N	\N	\N	/audio/1771283849738-Each_designated_sale.mp3	/timestamps/1771283849738-Each_designated_sale.timestamps.json	["/audio/1771283850844-Limited_representati.mp3", "", "/audio/1771283851671-They_owe_much_more_t.mp3", "/audio/1771283852798-Transaction_Brokers_.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1771283850844-Limited_representati.timestamps.json", "", "/timestamps/1771283851671-They_owe_much_more_t.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771283852798-Transaction_Brokers_.timestamps.json"]	["/audio/1771283846488-Limited_representati.mp3", "/audio/1771283847188-Fiduciary_responsibi.mp3", "/audio/1771283847766-No_brokerage_duties_.mp3", "/audio/1771283848568-The_same_duties_as_a.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1771283846488-Limited_representati.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771283847188-Fiduciary_responsibi.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771283847766-No_brokerage_duties_.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771283848568-The_same_duties_as_a.timestamps.json"]	/audio/1771283845697-What_specific_duties.mp3	/timestamps/1771283845697-What_specific_duties.timestamps.json
cmkznu9bs000xd90da3b706v8	cmjrjorwn0003b3n6srvqqp17	A developer acquires a large tract of land, records a subdivision plat, and builds several model homes. Buyers then select a floor plan and a lot. This type of residential construction is called: &nbsp;	{"Speculative (spec) building","Custom building","Tract building","Commercial building"}	2	{"correct": "Tract building involves constructing model homes in a new subdivision to allow buyers to view the product and select a floor plan to be built on a lot within that subdivision.", "incorrect": ["Speculative building involves building a home without a buyer in advance, whereas tract building involves buyers selecting plans based on models.", "Custom building involves building a specific home under contract for a specific buyer using unique plans, not picking from a developer's set of model floor plans.", "", "Commercial building refers to retail or office construction, not residential homes."]}	13	chapter	2026-01-29 16:20:15.928	2026-01-29 16:20:38.536	\N	\N	\N	\N	/audio/1769703630716-Tract_building_invol.mp3	/timestamps/1769703630716-Tract_building_invol.timestamps.json	["/audio/1769703632080-Speculative_building.mp3", "/audio/1769703633638-Custom_building_invo.mp3", "", "/audio/1769703634674-Commercial_building_.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1769703632080-Speculative_building.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1769703633638-Custom_building_invo.timestamps.json", "", "/timestamps/1769703634674-Commercial_building_.timestamps.json"]	["/audio/1769703627717-Speculative__spec__b.mp3", "/audio/1769703628216-Custom_building.mp3", "/audio/1769703628727-Tract_building.mp3", "/audio/1769703629318-Commercial_building.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1769703627717-Speculative__spec__b.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1769703628216-Custom_building.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1769703628727-Tract_building.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1769703629318-Commercial_building.timestamps.json"]	/audio/1769703626984-A_developer_acquires.mp3	/timestamps/1769703626984-A_developer_acquires.timestamps.json
cmmqxpgt2004c4be7243207ss	cmmqbpz7v00044be7x0za79d7	An owner of a rental building changes management companies. What must happen with tenants' security deposits, which the old management company is holding in their escrow account?	{"Send refund to tenants, provide final accounting showing the amounts that was credited back to each tenant.","Transfer the money to the new management company with a final accounting showing the amounts to be credited to each tenant’s account.","Ask tenants if they would like to receive a refund or to credit the funds to their accounts with the new management company.","Keep the money in escrow until the end of the lease."}	1	{"correct": "When a property management agreement is terminated, the outgoing broker or management company must transfer all tenant security deposits and advance rents to the new management company (or directly to the owner, if the owner is taking over). This transfer must be accompanied by a comprehensive final accounting that details exactly how much money belongs to each specific tenant.<div><br></div>", "incorrect": ["The old management company cannot simply refund the deposits to the tenants. The tenants' leases are still active, and the new management company (or owner) legally needs those funds held in their own escrow account to secure the ongoing leases.", "", "Tenants do not get the option to cash out their deposits mid-lease simply because the landlord decided to hire a new management company. The funds must automatically follow the property management responsibilities.", "Once the management agreement is terminated, the old management company no longer has a legal relationship with the property. Therefore, they have no legal right or authority to continue holding the tenants' funds in their escrow account."]}	34	chapter	2026-03-14 23:05:57.59	2026-03-14 23:17:08.054	\N	\N	\N	\N	/audio/1773530221387-When_a_property_mana.mp3	/timestamps/1773530221387-When_a_property_mana.timestamps.json	["/audio/1773530224054-The_old_management_c.mp3", "", "/audio/1773530225923-Tenants_do_not_get_t.mp3", "/audio/1773530227901-Once_the_management_.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1773530224054-The_old_management_c.timestamps.json", "", "/timestamps/1773530225923-Tenants_do_not_get_t.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1773530227901-Once_the_management_.timestamps.json"]	["/audio/1773530214789-Send_refund_to_tenan.mp3", "/audio/1773530215920-Transfer_the_money_t.mp3", "/audio/1773530216947-Ask_tenants_if_they_.mp3", "/audio/1773530217830-Keep_the_money_in_es.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1773530214789-Send_refund_to_tenan.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1773530215920-Transfer_the_money_t.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1773530216947-Ask_tenants_if_they_.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1773530217830-Keep_the_money_in_es.timestamps.json"]	/audio/1773530213464-An_owner_of_a_rental.mp3	/timestamps/1773530213464-An_owner_of_a_rental.timestamps.json
cmlo7uq4w00ctr4ev0z4jewbm	cmlo3p21500b9r4evvq0cbmdp	What happens to a license when the FREC revokes it?	{"It becomes Null and Void","It becomes Involuntary Inactive","It is suspended for 10 years","It becomes Voluntary Inactive"}	0	{"correct": "When the FREC revokes a real estate license, the license becomes null and void.", "incorrect": ["", "Revocation is final; it does not revert to inactive status.", "Suspension is a temporary penalty; revocation is permanent.", "Voluntary status must be requested; revocation is a punishment."]}	12	chapter	2026-02-15 20:46:58.256	2026-02-16 13:57:44.463	\N	\N	\N	\N	/audio/1771250261509-When_the_FREC_revoke.mp3	/timestamps/1771250261509-When_the_FREC_revoke.timestamps.json	["", "/audio/1771250262406-Revocation_is_final_.mp3", "/audio/1771250263363-Suspension_is_a_temp.mp3", "/audio/1771250264210-Voluntary_status_mus.mp3"]	["", "/timestamps/1771250262406-Revocation_is_final_.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771250263363-Suspension_is_a_temp.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771250264210-Voluntary_status_mus.timestamps.json"]	["/audio/1771250258344-It_becomes_Null_and_.mp3", "/audio/1771250259017-It_becomes_Involunta.mp3", "/audio/1771250259680-It_is_suspended_for_.mp3", "/audio/1771250260354-It_becomes_Voluntary.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1771250258344-It_becomes_Null_and_.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771250259017-It_becomes_Involunta.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771250259680-It_is_suspended_for_.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771250260354-It_becomes_Voluntary.timestamps.json"]	/audio/1771250257709-What_happens_to_a_li.mp3	/timestamps/1771250257709-What_happens_to_a_li.timestamps.json
cmlk0fjg9008ir4evy060iqcq	cmk8if4vt0000sxhb8i62wdi6	A nonresident applicant who holds a valid real estate license in a state with a mutual recognition agreement with Florida:	{" Is automatically licensed in Florida upon payment of a fee","Must take the 63-hour pre-license course and pass the state exam","Is exempt from the pre-license course but must pass a 40-question law exam","Must have a broker's license to qualify"}	2	{"correct": "Under mutual recognition, eligible nonresidents are exempt from the pre-license education and the full 100-question exam but must demonstrate knowledge of Florida law by passing a specific 40-question jurisprudence exam.", "incorrect": ["Reciprocity is not automatic; an exam is required.", "Mutual recognition waives this requirement.", "", "Mutual recognition applies to sales associates and brokers."]}	29	chapter	2026-02-12 22:08:07.737	2026-02-12 22:08:07.737	\N	\N	\N	\N	/audio/1770934079582-Under_mutual_recogni.mp3	/timestamps/1770934079582-Under_mutual_recogni.timestamps.json	["/audio/1770934080341-Reciprocity_is_not_a.mp3", "/audio/1770934081013-Mutual_recognition_w.mp3", "", "/audio/1770934081857-Mutual_recognition_a.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1770934080341-Reciprocity_is_not_a.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1770934081013-Mutual_recognition_w.timestamps.json", "", "/timestamps/1770934081857-Mutual_recognition_a.timestamps.json"]	["/audio/1770934074588-Is_automatically_lic.mp3", "/audio/1770934075821-Must_take_the_63_hou.mp3", "/audio/1770934076818-Is_exempt_from_the_p.mp3", "/audio/1770934077518-Must_have_a_broker_s.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1770934074588-Is_automatically_lic.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1770934075821-Must_take_the_63_hou.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1770934076818-Is_exempt_from_the_p.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1770934077518-Must_have_a_broker_s.timestamps.json"]	/audio/1770934073378-A_nonresident_applic.mp3	/timestamps/1770934073378-A_nonresident_applic.timestamps.json
cmlk0jdyb008kr4evuyv2gwng	cmk8if4vt0000sxhb8i62wdi6	A Florida real estate licensee moves to Georgia and becomes a nonresident. How long do they have to notify the Commission of their change in residency?	{"10 days","30 days","60 days","90 days"}	2	{"correct": "Section 475.180(2)(a), F.S. specifically requires licensees to notify the Commission within 60 days of becoming a nonresident.", "incorrect": ["This is for a simple change of mailing address, not a change in state residency status.", "Incorrect timeframe.", "", "Incorrect timeframe."]}	30	chapter	2026-02-12 22:11:07.235	2026-02-12 22:11:07.235	\N	\N	\N	\N	/audio/1770934260075-Section_475_180_2__a.mp3	/timestamps/1770934260075-Section_475_180_2__a.timestamps.json	["/audio/1770934261117-This_is_for_a_simple.mp3", "/audio/1770934262073-Incorrect_timeframe_.mp3", "", "/audio/1770934262780-Incorrect_timeframe_.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1770934261117-This_is_for_a_simple.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1770934262073-Incorrect_timeframe_.timestamps.json", "", "/timestamps/1770934262780-Incorrect_timeframe_.timestamps.json"]	["/audio/1770934256369-10_days.mp3", "/audio/1770934256886-30_days.mp3", "/audio/1770934257561-60_days.mp3", "/audio/1770934258089-90_days.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1770934256369-10_days.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1770934256886-30_days.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1770934257561-60_days.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1770934258089-90_days.timestamps.json"]	/audio/1770934255737-A_Florida_real_estat.mp3	/timestamps/1770934255737-A_Florida_real_estat.timestamps.json
cmkznxw64000zd90dzp31k30x	cmjrjorwn0003b3n6srvqqp17	A builder purchases a lot and begins construction on a single-family home without having a buyer or a signed sales contract. This is known as:	{" Custom building ","Spec building ","Tract building ",Dedication}	1	{"correct": "Building \\"on speculation\\" (Spec homes) involves purchasing a lot and constructing a home without a buyer in advance (no presale).", "incorrect": ["Custom building requires a contract with a buyer before construction begins.", "", "Tract building relies on model homes and buyers selecting floor plans, usually within a specific subdivision context.", "Dedication is the gift of land to the government, not a type of home construction."]}	14	chapter	2026-01-29 16:23:05.5	2026-02-19 17:40:26.488	\N	\N	\N	\N	/audio/1769703773124-Building__on_specula.mp3	/timestamps/1769703773124-Building__on_specula.timestamps.json	["/audio/1769703774046-Custom_building_requ.mp3", "", "/audio/1769703775350-Tract_building_relie.mp3", "/audio/1769703776386-Dedication_is_the_gi.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1769703774046-Custom_building_requ.timestamps.json", "", "/timestamps/1769703775350-Tract_building_relie.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1769703776386-Dedication_is_the_gi.timestamps.json"]	["/audio/1769703768880-Custom_building.mp3", "/audio/1769703769839-Spec_building.mp3", "/audio/1769703770538-Tract_building.mp3", "/audio/1769703771354-Dedication.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1769703768880-Custom_building.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1769703769839-Spec_building.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1769703770538-Tract_building.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1769703771354-Dedication.timestamps.json"]	/audio/1771522820112-A_builder_purchases_.mp3	/timestamps/1771522820112-A_builder_purchases_.timestamps.json
cmkzobt770013d90d5ommyipa	cmjrjorwn0003b3n6srvqqp17	According to Florida law, what requirement must be met to sell or lease business opportunities?&nbsp;	{"The individual must hold a specific \\"Business Broker\\" license issued by the state.","The individual must hold an active current real estate license.","No license is required if the transaction only involves the sale of personal property (inventory).","The individual must be a licensed attorney."}	1	{"correct": "In Florida, an active current real estate license is required to sell or lease business opportunities.\\" This is due to the presumption that real property (like a lease or land) is involved.", "incorrect": ["Florida does not issue a separate license specifically for \\"Business Brokers.\\" The activity is covered under the standard real estate license.", "", "A license is required because Florida law presumes that a business opportunity will involve some interest in real property (such as a long-term lease), making it a real estate activity.", "While attorneys handle legal aspects, an active real estate license is required for selling or leasing the business opportunity itself."]}	16	chapter	2026-01-29 16:33:54.768	2026-01-29 16:33:54.768	\N	\N	\N	\N	/audio/1769704426359-In_Florida__an_activ.mp3	/timestamps/1769704426359-In_Florida__an_activ.timestamps.json	["/audio/1769704427930-Florida_does_not_iss.mp3", "", "/audio/1769704429411-A_license_is_require.mp3", "/audio/1769704430817-While_attorneys_hand.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1769704427930-Florida_does_not_iss.timestamps.json", "", "/timestamps/1769704429411-A_license_is_require.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1769704430817-While_attorneys_hand.timestamps.json"]	["/audio/1769704421699-The_individual_must_.mp3", "/audio/1769704422509-The_individual_must_.mp3", "/audio/1769704423723-No_license_is_requir.mp3", "/audio/1769704424539-The_individual_must_.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1769704421699-The_individual_must_.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1769704422509-The_individual_must_.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1769704423723-No_license_is_requir.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1769704424539-The_individual_must_.timestamps.json"]	/audio/1769704420701-According_to_Florida.mp3	/timestamps/1769704420701-According_to_Florida.timestamps.json
cmms3pgsf00il4be7kuqlrxv5	cmmry1yz800fh4be796sih9l4	When calculating the annual property taxes for a primary residence in Florida, the homestead tax exemption is legally deducted from which of the following?	{"The property's estimated market value","The property's assessed value","The property's final taxable value","The original purchase price of the home"}	1	{"correct": "In the property tax calculation formula, all eligible tax exemptions (including the homestead exemption) are subtracted directly from the property's assessed value. (The formula is: Assessed Value - Exemptions = Taxable Value).", "incorrect": ["The market value (often called \\"just value\\" in Florida) is the initial starting point determined by the county appraiser. However, exemptions are not deducted from this raw number; they are deducted only after the Save Our Homes (SOH) assessment cap has been applied to find the assessed value.", "", "The taxable value is the final result of the calculation, not the number the exemption is deducted from. Once you find the taxable value, you multiply it by the local millage rates to get the actual tax bill.", "Property taxes are based on current, annual valuations determined by the county property appraiser, not the historical purchase price the buyer originally paid."]}	27	chapter	2026-03-15 18:41:41.439	2026-03-15 19:07:18.676	\N	\N	\N	\N	/audio/1773601631616-In_the_property_tax_.mp3	/timestamps/1773601631616-In_the_property_tax_.timestamps.json	["/audio/1773601634351-The_market_value__of.mp3", "", "/audio/1773601636393-The_taxable_value_is.mp3", "/audio/1773601638508-Property_taxes_are_b.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1773601634351-The_market_value__of.timestamps.json", "", "/timestamps/1773601636393-The_taxable_value_is.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1773601638508-Property_taxes_are_b.timestamps.json"]	["/audio/1773601627158-The_property_s_estim.mp3", "/audio/1773601627790-The_property_s_asses.mp3", "/audio/1773601628588-The_property_s_final.mp3", "/audio/1773601629469-The_original_purchas.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1773601627158-The_property_s_estim.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1773601627790-The_property_s_asses.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1773601628588-The_property_s_final.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1773601629469-The_original_purchas.timestamps.json"]	/audio/1773601626379-When_calculating_the.mp3	/timestamps/1773601626379-When_calculating_the.timestamps.json
cmlbinv47001ir4evls3onwkc	cmk8if4vt0000sxhb8i62wdi6	What is the primary responsibility of the Florida Legislature regarding real estate?	{"To investigate consumer complaints","To create, change, and repeal state laws","To issue licenses to new applicants","To set the commission rates for brokers"}	1	{"correct": "Florida Legislature as the law-making body. Its role is to enact the statutes (like Chapter 475) that govern the state, whereas enforcing those laws is left to the Commission.", "incorrect": ["This is a power granted to the FREC.", "", "This is an administrative function of the FREC/DBPR.", "Neither the Legislature nor the FREC sets commission rates; they are negotiable."]}	0	chapter	2026-02-06 23:28:33.607	2026-02-06 23:28:33.607	\N	\N	\N	\N	/audio/1770420501589-Florida_Legislature_.mp3	/timestamps/1770420501589-Florida_Legislature_.timestamps.json	["/audio/1770420502334-This_is_a_power_gran.mp3", "", "/audio/1770420503259-This_is_an_administr.mp3", "/audio/1770420504184-Neither_the_Legislat.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1770420502334-This_is_a_power_gran.timestamps.json", "", "/timestamps/1770420503259-This_is_an_administr.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1770420504184-Neither_the_Legislat.timestamps.json"]	["/audio/1770420497492-To_investigate_consu.mp3", "/audio/1770420498452-To_create__change__a.mp3", "/audio/1770420499185-To_issue_licenses_to.mp3", "/audio/1770420499878-To_set_the_commissio.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1770420497492-To_investigate_consu.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1770420498452-To_create__change__a.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1770420499185-To_issue_licenses_to.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1770420499878-To_set_the_commissio.timestamps.json"]	/audio/1770420496341-What_is_the_primary_.mp3	/timestamps/1770420496341-What_is_the_primary_.timestamps.json
cmkzohnsi0017d90d0opjnm77	cmjrjorwn0003b3n6srvqqp17	A CAM license is required for:	{"Managing a condo building with a budget of over $10,000","Managing a condo building with a budget of over $50,000","Managing a condo building with a budget of over $100,000","Managing a condo building with a budget of over $150,000"}	2	{"correct": "Florida law (F.S. 468) requires a Community Association Manager (CAM) license if the person manages a community association that has more than 10 units OR has an annual budget in excess of $100,000.", "incorrect": ["A budget of $10,000 is below the statutory threshold of $100,000, so a CAM license would not be required based on budget alone.", "A budget of $50,000 is below the statutory threshold of $100,000.", "", "While a license is required for a $150,000 budget, this option is not the correct answer because the legal requirement actually begins at the $100,000 threshold. Option C is the more accurate definition of the law's starting point."]}	18	chapter	2026-01-29 16:38:27.762	2026-02-19 17:40:50.214	\N	\N	\N	\N	/audio/1769704684064-Florida_law__F_S__46.mp3	/timestamps/1769704684064-Florida_law__F_S__46.timestamps.json	["/audio/1769704685565-A_budget_of__10_000_.mp3", "/audio/1769704686575-A_budget_of__50_000_.mp3", "", "/audio/1769704688797-While_a_license_is_r.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1769704685565-A_budget_of__10_000_.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1769704686575-A_budget_of__50_000_.timestamps.json", "", "/timestamps/1769704688797-While_a_license_is_r.timestamps.json"]	["/audio/1769704678103-Managing_a_condo_bui.mp3", "/audio/1769704679220-Managing_a_condo_bui.mp3", "/audio/1769704680568-Managing_a_condo_bui.mp3", "/audio/1769704681622-Managing_a_condo_bui.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1769704678103-Managing_a_condo_bui.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1769704679220-Managing_a_condo_bui.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1769704680568-Managing_a_condo_bui.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1769704681622-Managing_a_condo_bui.timestamps.json"]	/audio/1771522843297-A_CAM_license_is_req.mp3	/timestamps/1771522843297-A_CAM_license_is_req.timestamps.json
cmljwldq1006wr4evd0phi9r9	cmk8if4vt0000sxhb8i62wdi6	Which body was established in 1925 to enforce the real estate law and ensure professionalism in the industry?	{"The Florida Legislature","The Department of Housing","The Florida Real Estate Commission (FREC)","The Realtor Association of Florida"}	2	{"correct": "<div>The Florida Real Estate Commission (FREC) was created by the Florida Legislature in 1925 to administer and enforce the license law. Its primary purpose is to protect the public by ensuring a high standard of professionalism in the real estate industry.</div>", "incorrect": ["The Florida Legislature enacts the laws (statutes), but it established the FREC to enforce them.", "This usually refers to federal agencies (HUD) or state departments that handle housing specifically, not the regulation of real estate licensees.", "", "The Realtor Association is a trade organization that supports professionals; it is not a government regulatory body with the power to enforce laws."]}	1	chapter	2026-02-12 20:20:41.715	2026-02-12 20:20:41.715	\N	\N	\N	\N	/audio/1770927633362-The_Florida_Real_Est.mp3	/timestamps/1770927633362-The_Florida_Real_Est.timestamps.json	["/audio/1770927634381-The_Florida_Legislat.mp3", "/audio/1770927635718-This_usually_refers_.mp3", "", "/audio/1770927636892-The_Realtor_Associat.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1770927634381-The_Florida_Legislat.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1770927635718-This_usually_refers_.timestamps.json", "", "/timestamps/1770927636892-The_Realtor_Associat.timestamps.json"]	["/audio/1770927629408-The_Florida_Legislat.mp3", "/audio/1770927630004-The_Department_of_Ho.mp3", "/audio/1770927630765-The_Florida_Real_Est.mp3", "/audio/1770927631414-The_Realtor_Associat.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1770927629408-The_Florida_Legislat.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1770927630004-The_Department_of_Ho.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1770927630765-The_Florida_Real_Est.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1770927631414-The_Realtor_Associat.timestamps.json"]	/audio/1770927628852-Which_body_was_estab.mp3	/timestamps/1770927628852-Which_body_was_estab.timestamps.json
cmljwrr8y006yr4evmfmrg858	cmk8if4vt0000sxhb8i62wdi6	How is the real estate industry described prior to the 1900s?	{"Heavily regulated and slow-moving","Highly professional and exclusive","Unregulated and highly competitive","Organized and trust-based"}	2	{"correct": "Prior to the enactment of license laws (such as Florida's first law in 1923 and the establishment of the FREC in 1925), the real estate industry was unregulated. It was often described as a \\"free-for-all\\" or \\"wild west\\" environment operating under the principle of Caveat Emptor (\\"Let the buyer beware\\"), where unscrupulous business practices were common.&nbsp;", "incorrect": ["The industry was the opposite of regulated; there were no state boards or license requirements to slow down or control business activities.", "Because there were no educational or ethical standards, the industry was not viewed as a \\"profession\\" in the modern sense, nor was it exclusive—anyone could claim to be an agent.", "", "The lack of regulation meant there was little organization or guaranteed trust; consumer protection was virtually non-existent."]}	2	chapter	2026-02-12 20:25:39.25	2026-02-12 20:25:39.25	\N	\N	\N	\N	/audio/1770927926238-Prior_to_the_enactme.mp3	/timestamps/1770927926238-Prior_to_the_enactme.timestamps.json	["/audio/1770927927561-The_industry_was_the.mp3", "/audio/1770927929593-Because_there_were_n.mp3", "", "/audio/1770927930916-The_lack_of_regulati.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1770927927561-The_industry_was_the.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1770927929593-Because_there_were_n.timestamps.json", "", "/timestamps/1770927930916-The_lack_of_regulati.timestamps.json"]	["/audio/1770927921316-Heavily_regulated_an.mp3", "/audio/1770927921942-Highly_professional_.mp3", "/audio/1770927922622-Unregulated_and_high.mp3", "/audio/1770927923341-Organized_and_trust_.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1770927921316-Heavily_regulated_an.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1770927921942-Highly_professional_.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1770927922622-Unregulated_and_high.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1770927923341-Organized_and_trust_.timestamps.json"]	/audio/1770927920286-How_is_the_real_esta.mp3	/timestamps/1770927920286-How_is_the_real_esta.timestamps.json
cmljwvyy70070r4evxmabwsim	cmk8if4vt0000sxhb8i62wdi6	What is the primary purpose of the Department of Business and Professional Regulation (DBPR)?	{"To create new state laws for businesses","To protect the public by overseeing professions and businesses"," To maximize profits for Florida corporations","To provide legal defense for real estate agents"}	1	{"correct": "&nbsp;DBPR is a state agency created to protect the public by ensuring professionals follow the law, meet licensing requirements, and operate safely.", "incorrect": ["Creating laws is the role of the Legislature.", "", "The agency's focus is on compliance and safety, not corporate profits.", "The DBPR regulates professionals, it does not defend them."]}	3	chapter	2026-02-12 20:28:55.855	2026-02-12 20:28:55.855	\N	\N	\N	\N	/audio/1770928127661-DBPR_is_a_state_agen.mp3	/timestamps/1770928127661-DBPR_is_a_state_agen.timestamps.json	["/audio/1770928128433-Creating_laws_is_the.mp3", "", "/audio/1770928129337-The_agency_s_focus_i.mp3", "/audio/1770928130084-The_DBPR_regulates_p.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1770928128433-Creating_laws_is_the.timestamps.json", "", "/timestamps/1770928129337-The_agency_s_focus_i.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1770928130084-The_DBPR_regulates_p.timestamps.json"]	["/audio/1770928123697-To_create_new_state_.mp3", "/audio/1770928124631-To_protect_the_publi.mp3", "/audio/1770928125358-To_maximize_profits_.mp3", "/audio/1770928126194-To_provide_legal_def.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1770928123697-To_create_new_state_.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1770928124631-To_protect_the_publi.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1770928125358-To_maximize_profits_.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1770928126194-To_provide_legal_def.timestamps.json"]	/audio/1770928122903-What_is_the_primary_.mp3	/timestamps/1770928122903-What_is_the_primary_.timestamps.json
cmlprtmpp00jqr4evxnshwrpv	cmlpniy5e00gyr4ev7l7y4vur	Which of the following scenarios best describes a transaction conducted at "arm's length"?&nbsp;	{"A father sells his vacation home to his daughter for half of its market value","A buyer and a seller, who are strangers to each other, negotiate freely to get the best price for themselves","A real estate broker acts as a fiduciary for a seller, putting the seller's interests above their own","A boss coerces an employee into buying their car by threatening to fire them if they refuse"}	1	{"correct": "An arm's length transaction is one where the parties are independent, unrelated, and acting in their own self-interest. They are \\"keeping each other at a distance\\" (at arm's length) to ensure a fair market value is reached without pressure or special favors.", "incorrect": ["This is a transaction between related parties (family). The price is influenced by the relationship rather than the open market, so it is not at arm's length.", "", "This describes a fiduciary relationship (Agency), which is based on trust and loyalty. In an arm's length deal, the parties are adversarial (each fighting for themselves), not loyal to each other.", "This transaction involves duress or undue influence. For a transaction to be at arm's length, both parties must be acting freely and independently, without coercion."]}	18	chapter	2026-02-16 22:53:45.661	2026-02-16 23:17:45.389	\N	\N	\N	\N	/audio/1771283860281-An_arm_s_length_tran.mp3	/timestamps/1771283860281-An_arm_s_length_tran.timestamps.json	["/audio/1771283861940-This_is_a_transactio.mp3", "", "/audio/1771283863607-This_describes_a_fid.mp3", "/audio/1771283865143-This_transaction_inv.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1771283861940-This_is_a_transactio.timestamps.json", "", "/timestamps/1771283863607-This_describes_a_fid.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771283865143-This_transaction_inv.timestamps.json"]	["/audio/1771283854904-A_father_sells_his_v.mp3", "/audio/1771283856143-A_buyer_and_a_seller.mp3", "/audio/1771283857155-A_real_estate_broker.mp3", "/audio/1771283858168-A_boss_coerces_an_em.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1771283854904-A_father_sells_his_v.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771283856143-A_buyer_and_a_seller.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771283857155-A_real_estate_broker.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771283858168-A_boss_coerces_an_em.timestamps.json"]	/audio/1771283854141-Which_of_the_followi.mp3	/timestamps/1771283854141-Which_of_the_followi.timestamps.json
cmljx0ycm0072r4evoh51dbsj	cmk8if4vt0000sxhb8i62wdi6	Which statement best describes the relationship between the Division of Real Estate (DRE) and the Florida Real Estate Commission (FREC)?	{"The DRE creates the rules that FREC must follow.","The DRE provides administrative support to the FREC.","The DRE and FREC are unrelated entities.","The FREC reports to the DRE for approval."}	1	{"correct": "While FREC makes the decisions and rules, the DRE handles the \\"behind-the-scenes\\" administrative work (like processing applications) that supports FREC.", "incorrect": ["DRE doesn't create rules. It handles the \\"behind-the-scenes\\" administrative work for FREC (like processing applications)&nbsp;", "", "They work closely together within the DBPR structure.", "FREC doesn't report to DRE. DRE handles the \\"behind-the-scenes\\" administrative work for FREC (like processing applications)&nbsp;"]}	4	chapter	2026-02-12 20:32:48.357	2026-02-12 20:33:44.391	\N	\N	\N	\N	/audio/1770928415166-While_FREC_makes_the.mp3	/timestamps/1770928415166-While_FREC_makes_the.timestamps.json	["/audio/1770928416546-DRE_doesn_t_create_r.mp3", "", "/audio/1770928417452-They_work_closely_to.mp3", "/audio/1770928418887-FREC_doesn_t_report_.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1770928416546-DRE_doesn_t_create_r.timestamps.json", "", "/timestamps/1770928417452-They_work_closely_to.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1770928418887-FREC_doesn_t_report_.timestamps.json"]	["/audio/1770928411047-The_DRE_creates_the_.mp3", "/audio/1770928411934-The_DRE_provides_adm.mp3", "/audio/1770928412879-The_DRE_and_FREC_are.mp3", "/audio/1770928413624-The_FREC_reports_to_.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1770928411047-The_DRE_creates_the_.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1770928411934-The_DRE_provides_adm.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1770928412879-The_DRE_and_FREC_are.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1770928413624-The_FREC_reports_to_.timestamps.json"]	/audio/1770928410287-Which_statement_best.mp3	/timestamps/1770928410287-Which_statement_best.timestamps.json
cmljx5m2z0074r4evnd6gojqv	cmk8if4vt0000sxhb8i62wdi6	The DBPR divides its responsibilities across specialized divisions to ensure:	{"Consistency, accountability, and consumer protection","Higher taxes for businesses","Less government oversight","That each profession polices itself"}	0	{"correct": "Centralized oversight is provided to ensure consistency, accountability, and consumer protection, rather than allowing professions to police themselves.", "incorrect": ["", "Taxation is not the primary goal.&nbsp;", "The DBPR provides centralized oversight.", "DBPR exists instead of each profession policing itself."]}	5	chapter	2026-02-12 20:36:25.739	2026-02-12 20:36:25.739	\N	\N	\N	\N	/audio/1770928577484-Centralized_oversigh.mp3	/timestamps/1770928577484-Centralized_oversigh.timestamps.json	["", "/audio/1770928578247-Taxation_is_not_the_.mp3", "/audio/1770928579045-The_DBPR_provides_ce.mp3", "/audio/1770928579881-DBPR_exists_instead_.mp3"]	["", "/timestamps/1770928578247-Taxation_is_not_the_.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1770928579045-The_DBPR_provides_ce.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1770928579881-DBPR_exists_instead_.timestamps.json"]	["/audio/1770928574027-Consistency__account.mp3", "/audio/1770928574711-Higher_taxes_for_bus.mp3", "/audio/1770928575354-Less_government_over.mp3", "/audio/1770928575991-That_each_profession.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1770928574027-Consistency__account.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1770928574711-Higher_taxes_for_bus.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1770928575354-Less_government_over.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1770928575991-That_each_profession.timestamps.json"]	/audio/1770928573028-The_DBPR_divides_its.mp3	/timestamps/1770928573028-The_DBPR_divides_its.timestamps.json
cmljx8cxg0076r4evdcdqzryj	cmk8if4vt0000sxhb8i62wdi6	Which of the following is a specific responsibility of the Division of Real Estate (DRE)?	{"Making final decisions on disciplinary cases","Processing license applications and renewals","Drafting the state constitution","Setting interest rates for mortgages"}	1	{"correct": "The DRE handles day-to-day administrative tasks, which the text lists as processing applications, renewals, and investigating complaints.", "incorrect": ["This is the responsibility of the Commission (FREC).", "", "This is a legislative/constitutional role, not DRE.", "The DRE does not regulate financial market rates."]}	6	chapter	2026-02-12 20:38:33.844	2026-02-12 20:38:33.844	\N	\N	\N	\N	/audio/1770928706663-The_DRE_handles_day_.mp3	/timestamps/1770928706663-The_DRE_handles_day_.timestamps.json	["/audio/1770928707429-This_is_the_responsi.mp3", "", "/audio/1770928708418-This_is_a_legislativ.mp3", "/audio/1770928709299-The_DRE_does_not_reg.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1770928707429-This_is_the_responsi.timestamps.json", "", "/timestamps/1770928708418-This_is_a_legislativ.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1770928709299-The_DRE_does_not_reg.timestamps.json"]	["/audio/1770928702563-Making_final_decisio.mp3", "/audio/1770928703407-Processing_license_a.mp3", "/audio/1770928704066-Drafting_the_state_c.mp3", "/audio/1770928705235-Setting_interest_rat.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1770928702563-Making_final_decisio.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1770928703407-Processing_license_a.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1770928704066-Drafting_the_state_c.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1770928705235-Setting_interest_rat.timestamps.json"]	/audio/1770928701318-Which_of_the_followi.mp3	/timestamps/1770928701318-Which_of_the_followi.timestamps.json
cmlk0m7w4008mr4evv0dl6yr6	cmk8if4vt0000sxhb8i62wdi6	For the purpose of real estate licensure, a "resident" of Florida is defined as a person who has resided in the state for:	{"6 months","1 Year ","4 months ","30 days"}	2	{"correct": "FREC rules define a resident as someone who has resided in Florida continuously for a period of 4 calendar months or more within the preceding year.", "incorrect": ["This is a common standard for tax residency but not for FREC licensure.", "Too long", "", "Too short&nbsp;"]}	31	chapter	2026-02-12 22:13:19.347	2026-02-12 22:13:19.347	\N	\N	\N	\N	/audio/1770934393693-FREC_rules_define_a_.mp3	/timestamps/1770934393693-FREC_rules_define_a_.timestamps.json	["/audio/1770934394734-This_is_a_common_sta.mp3", "/audio/1770934395334-Too_long.mp3", "", "/audio/1770934395913-Too_short.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1770934394734-This_is_a_common_sta.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1770934395334-Too_long.timestamps.json", "", "/timestamps/1770934395913-Too_short.timestamps.json"]	["/audio/1770934390424-6_months.mp3", "/audio/1770934390998-1_Year.mp3", "/audio/1770934391495-4_months.mp3", "/audio/1770934392030-30_days.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1770934390424-6_months.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1770934390998-1_Year.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1770934391495-4_months.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1770934392030-30_days.timestamps.json"]	/audio/1770934389554-For_the_purpose_of_r.mp3	/timestamps/1770934389554-For_the_purpose_of_r.timestamps.json
cmljxj1i10078r4evt019lkf5	cmk8if4vt0000sxhb8i62wdi6	What is the literal meaning of the Latin term "caveat emptor"?	{"Let the seller beware","Let the buyer beware","The master answers","Real estate is king"}	1	{"correct": "Caveat emptor means “let the buyer beware”. It signifies that the buyer is responsible for checking the quality of the goods (property) before purchasing.", "incorrect": ["The term places the burden on the buyer, not the seller.", "", "This refers to a different legal concept (respondeat superior), not caveat emptor.", "This is not a translation of the Latin term."]}	7	chapter	2026-02-12 20:46:52.208	2026-02-12 20:46:52.208	\N	\N	\N	\N	/audio/1770929194519-Caveat_emptor_means_.mp3	/timestamps/1770929194519-Caveat_emptor_means_.timestamps.json	["/audio/1770929195402-The_term_places_the_.mp3", "", "/audio/1770929196543-This_refers_to_a_dif.mp3", "/audio/1770929197378-This_is_not_a_transl.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1770929195402-The_term_places_the_.timestamps.json", "", "/timestamps/1770929196543-This_refers_to_a_dif.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1770929197378-This_is_not_a_transl.timestamps.json"]	["/audio/1770929190696-Let_the_seller_bewar.mp3", "/audio/1770929191705-Let_the_buyer_beware.mp3", "/audio/1770929192285-The_master_answers.mp3", "/audio/1770929192861-Real_estate_is_king.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1770929190696-Let_the_seller_bewar.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1770929191705-Let_the_buyer_beware.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1770929192285-The_master_answers.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1770929192861-Real_estate_is_king.timestamps.json"]	/audio/1770929189955-What_is_the_literal_.mp3	/timestamps/1770929189955-What_is_the_literal_.timestamps.json
cmljxl9en007ar4evl1lvlfvg	cmk8if4vt0000sxhb8i62wdi6	Under the early principle of caveat emptor, who was primarily responsible for discovering problems with a property?	{"The seller","The real estate agent","The government","The buyer"}	3	{"correct": "In the early days, buyers were largely on their own to discover defects or issues. Sellers and agents were not obligated to disclose important information, placing the full burden of due diligence on the buyer.", "incorrect": ["Sellers were not required to disclose information under this principle.<div><br></div>", "Agents operated with little oversight and were not required to protect the buyer's interest regarding disclosures.", "There was a lack of oversight and regulation during this period.", ""]}	8	chapter	2026-02-12 20:48:35.807	2026-02-12 20:48:35.807	\N	\N	\N	\N	/audio/1770929309873-In_the_early_days__b.mp3	/timestamps/1770929309873-In_the_early_days__b.timestamps.json	["/audio/1770929310884-Sellers_were_not_req.mp3", "/audio/1770929311987-Agents_operated_with.mp3", "/audio/1770929312921-There_was_a_lack_of_.mp3", ""]	["/timestamps/1770929310884-Sellers_were_not_req.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1770929311987-Agents_operated_with.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1770929312921-There_was_a_lack_of_.timestamps.json", ""]	["/audio/1770929306442-The_seller.mp3", "/audio/1770929307141-The_real_estate_agen.mp3", "/audio/1770929307766-The_government.mp3", "/audio/1770929308286-The_buyer.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1770929306442-The_seller.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1770929307141-The_real_estate_agen.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1770929307766-The_government.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1770929308286-The_buyer.timestamps.json"]	/audio/1770929305533-Under_the_early_prin.mp3	/timestamps/1770929305533-Under_the_early_prin.timestamps.json
cmljxrooe007er4evkqdbayur	cmk8if4vt0000sxhb8i62wdi6	What is the main purpose of real estate regulation?	{"To maximize profits for real estate brokerages","To protect consumers","To ensure property values always increase","To generate tax revenue for the state"}	1	{"correct": "The main purpose of real estate regulation is to protect consumers.", "incorrect": ["The focus of regulation is safety and protection, not industry profits.", "", "Regulation cannot control market values.", "While fees are collected, the purpose is consumer protection."]}	10	chapter	2026-02-12 20:53:35.534	2026-02-12 20:53:35.534	\N	\N	\N	\N	/audio/1770929608155-The_main_purpose_of_.mp3	/timestamps/1770929608155-The_main_purpose_of_.timestamps.json	["/audio/1770929609061-The_focus_of_regulat.mp3", "", "/audio/1770929610015-Regulation_cannot_co.mp3", "/audio/1770929610847-While_fees_are_colle.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1770929609061-The_focus_of_regulat.timestamps.json", "", "/timestamps/1770929610015-Regulation_cannot_co.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1770929610847-While_fees_are_colle.timestamps.json"]	["/audio/1770929604319-To_maximize_profits_.mp3", "/audio/1770929605204-To_protect_consumers.mp3", "/audio/1770929606277-To_ensure_property_v.mp3", "/audio/1770929606905-To_generate_tax_reve.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1770929604319-To_maximize_profits_.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1770929605204-To_protect_consumers.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1770929606277-To_ensure_property_v.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1770929606905-To_generate_tax_reve.timestamps.json"]	/audio/1770929603464-What_is_the_main_pur.mp3	/timestamps/1770929603464-What_is_the_main_pur.timestamps.json
cmljxw6r3007gr4evtd9knopl	cmk8if4vt0000sxhb8i62wdi6	Real Estate Regulation sets clear standards for which of the following areas to reduce the risk of fraud?	{"Interior design trends","Handling of funds and disclosure","Mortgage interest rates","Property appreciation rates"}	1	{"correct": "Standards are set for disclosure, advertising, handling of funds, and professional conduct to reduce fraud and abuse.", "incorrect": ["This is a matter of taste, not regulation.", "", "These are determined by the financial market, not real estate licensing regulation.", "The market determines value, not regulation."]}	11	chapter	2026-02-12 20:57:05.583	2026-02-12 20:57:05.583	\N	\N	\N	\N	/audio/1770929819561-Standards_are_set_fo.mp3	/timestamps/1770929819561-Standards_are_set_fo.timestamps.json	["/audio/1770929820338-This_is_a_matter_of_.mp3", "", "/audio/1770929821362-These_are_determined.mp3", "/audio/1770929822103-The_market_determine.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1770929820338-This_is_a_matter_of_.timestamps.json", "", "/timestamps/1770929821362-These_are_determined.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1770929822103-The_market_determine.timestamps.json"]	["/audio/1770929815570-Interior_design_tren.mp3", "/audio/1770929816312-Handling_of_funds_an.mp3", "/audio/1770929816902-Mortgage_interest_ra.mp3", "/audio/1770929817915-Property_appreciatio.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1770929815570-Interior_design_tren.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1770929816312-Handling_of_funds_an.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1770929816902-Mortgage_interest_ra.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1770929817915-Property_appreciatio.timestamps.json"]	/audio/1770929814882-Real_Estate_Regulati.mp3	/timestamps/1770929814882-Real_Estate_Regulati.timestamps.json
cmljy0jh5007ir4evp0jx67u4	cmk8if4vt0000sxhb8i62wdi6	Which real estate professional holds a broker's license but chooses to work under the supervision of another broker?	{"Sales Associate","Broker Associate","Managing Broker",Owner-Developer}	1	{"correct": "Broker associate holds a broker’s license (having completed the required education and experience) but chooses to work under another broker rather than operating their own brokerage.", "incorrect": ["A sales associate does not hold a broker's license.", "", "A managing broker typically runs the office and has legal responsibility, unlike a broker associate who works under one.&nbsp;<div><br></div>", "This is an unlicensed entity that sells its own property, not a licensee working under a broker.&nbsp;"]}	12	chapter	2026-02-12 21:00:28.697	2026-02-12 21:00:28.697	\N	\N	\N	\N	/audio/1770930021336-Broker_associate_hol.mp3	/timestamps/1770930021336-Broker_associate_hol.timestamps.json	["/audio/1770930022158-A_sales_associate_do.mp3", "", "/audio/1770930023419-A_managing_broker_ty.mp3", "/audio/1770930024765-This_is_an_unlicense.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1770930022158-A_sales_associate_do.timestamps.json", "", "/timestamps/1770930023419-A_managing_broker_ty.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1770930024765-This_is_an_unlicense.timestamps.json"]	["/audio/1770930017629-Sales_Associate.mp3", "/audio/1770930018167-Broker_Associate.mp3", "/audio/1770930018806-Managing_Broker.mp3", "/audio/1770930019518-Owner_Developer.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1770930017629-Sales_Associate.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1770930018167-Broker_Associate.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1770930018806-Managing_Broker.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1770930019518-Owner_Developer.timestamps.json"]	/audio/1770930016760-Which_real_estate_pr.mp3	/timestamps/1770930016760-Which_real_estate_pr.timestamps.json
cmljy3kei007kr4evv95zd9ih	cmk8if4vt0000sxhb8i62wdi6	Which level of licensure is permitted to operate independently and open a real estate brokerage?	{"Sales Associate"," Broker Associate",Broker,Realtor}	2	{"correct": "A broker is the highest level of licensure and is the only one permitted to operate independently, open a brokerage, and hire others.", "incorrect": ["Sales Associates must work under a broker.", "While they have a broker's license, they choose to work under another broker and do not operate independently.", "", "This is a trade association membership, not a license category that determines independence."]}	13	chapter	2026-02-12 21:02:49.866	2026-02-12 21:02:49.866	\N	\N	\N	\N	/audio/1770930162838-A_broker_is_the_high.mp3	/timestamps/1770930162838-A_broker_is_the_high.timestamps.json	["/audio/1770930163786-Sales_Associates_mus.mp3", "/audio/1770930164937-While_they_have_a_br.mp3", "", "/audio/1770930165998-This_is_a_trade_asso.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1770930163786-Sales_Associates_mus.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1770930164937-While_they_have_a_br.timestamps.json", "", "/timestamps/1770930165998-This_is_a_trade_asso.timestamps.json"]	["/audio/1770930159516-Sales_Associate.mp3", "/audio/1770930160123-Broker_Associate.mp3", "/audio/1770930161005-Broker.mp3", "/audio/1770930161547-Realtor.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1770930159516-Sales_Associate.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1770930160123-Broker_Associate.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1770930161005-Broker.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1770930161547-Realtor.timestamps.json"]	/audio/1770930158884-Which_level_of_licen.mp3	/timestamps/1770930158884-Which_level_of_licen.timestamps.json
cmlk0uy2f008or4evbv2bhf7h	cmk8if4vt0000sxhb8i62wdi6	A sales associate applicant fails the end-of-course exam for the 63-hour pre-licensing course. What is the rule regarding retesting?	{"They can retest immediately.","They must wait 30 days and can retest one time within a year.","They must repeat the entire course immediately.","They can retest as many times as needed within one year."}	1	{"correct": "Rule 61J2-3.008(6) states that students failing the exam must wait at least 30 days to retest and may retest a maximum of one time within one year.", "incorrect": ["Immediate retesting is prohibited; a 30-day wait is required.", "", "Repeating the course is only required if the retest is failed or the year expires.", "Only one retest is allowed before the course must be repeated."]}	32	chapter	2026-02-12 22:20:06.484	2026-02-12 22:20:06.484	\N	\N	\N	\N	/audio/1770934798856-Rule_61J2_3_008_6__s.mp3	/timestamps/1770934798856-Rule_61J2_3_008_6__s.timestamps.json	["/audio/1770934799974-Immediate_retesting_.mp3", "", "/audio/1770934801077-Repeating_the_course.mp3", "/audio/1770934802027-Only_one_retest_is_a.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1770934799974-Immediate_retesting_.timestamps.json", "", "/timestamps/1770934801077-Repeating_the_course.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1770934802027-Only_one_retest_is_a.timestamps.json"]	["/audio/1770934794304-They_can_retest_imme.mp3", "/audio/1770934795207-They_must_wait_30_da.mp3", "/audio/1770934795988-They_must_repeat_the.mp3", "/audio/1770934796874-They_can_retest_as_m.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1770934794304-They_can_retest_imme.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1770934795207-They_must_wait_30_da.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1770934795988-They_must_repeat_the.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1770934796874-They_can_retest_as_m.timestamps.json"]	/audio/1770934793621-A_sales_associate_ap.mp3	/timestamps/1770934793621-A_sales_associate_ap.timestamps.json
cmljy8jw4007or4ev9ifyetev	cmk8if4vt0000sxhb8i62wdi6	To qualify for a real estate sales associate license in Florida, an applicant must be at least	{"16 years old","18 years old","21 years old","25 years old"}	1	{"correct": "18 years old. To qualify, applicants must be at least 18 years of age and have earned a high school diploma or equivalent.", "incorrect": ["This is below the minimum age requirement.", "", "This is higher than the requirement.", "This is higher than the requirement."]}	14	chapter	2026-02-12 21:06:42.483	2026-02-12 21:06:42.483	\N	\N	\N	\N	/audio/1770930394022-18_years_old__To_qua.mp3	/timestamps/1770930394022-18_years_old__To_qua.timestamps.json	["/audio/1770930394811-This_is_below_the_mi.mp3", "", "/audio/1770930395511-This_is_higher_than_.mp3", "/audio/1770930396310-This_is_higher_than_.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1770930394811-This_is_below_the_mi.timestamps.json", "", "/timestamps/1770930395511-This_is_higher_than_.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1770930396310-This_is_higher_than_.timestamps.json"]	["/audio/1770930390472-16_years_old.mp3", "/audio/1770930391217-18_years_old.mp3", "/audio/1770930391786-21_years_old.mp3", "/audio/1770930392526-25_years_old.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1770930390472-16_years_old.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1770930391217-18_years_old.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1770930391786-21_years_old.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1770930392526-25_years_old.timestamps.json"]	/audio/1770930389552-To_qualify_for_a_rea.mp3	/timestamps/1770930389552-To_qualify_for_a_rea.timestamps.json
cmljybu97007qr4evfth07yfa	cmk8if4vt0000sxhb8i62wdi6	Which of the following is TRUE regarding U.S. citizenship and Florida residency for real estate applicants?	{"Applicants must be U.S. citizens","Applicants must be Florida residents for at least 6 months","U.S. citizenship is not required, and applicants do not have to be Florida residents","Applicants must be U.S. citizens but do not need to be Florida residents"}	2	{"correct": "U.S. citizenship is not required, and applicants do not have to be Florida residents to obtain a license.", "incorrect": ["Chapter 455.10 prohibits denying a license solely based on non-citizenship.", "Residency is not a requirement for licensure.", "", "Citizenship is not required."]}	15	chapter	2026-02-12 21:09:15.883	2026-02-12 21:09:15.883	\N	\N	\N	\N	/audio/1770930547851-U_S__citizenship_is_.mp3	/timestamps/1770930547851-U_S__citizenship_is_.timestamps.json	["/audio/1770930549055-Chapter_455_10_prohi.mp3", "/audio/1770930550045-Residency_is_not_a_r.mp3", "", "/audio/1770930550771-Citizenship_is_not_r.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1770930549055-Chapter_455_10_prohi.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1770930550045-Residency_is_not_a_r.timestamps.json", "", "/timestamps/1770930550771-Citizenship_is_not_r.timestamps.json"]	["/audio/1770930543607-Applicants_must_be_U.mp3", "/audio/1770930544518-Applicants_must_be_F.mp3", "/audio/1770930545444-U_S__citizenship_is_.mp3", "/audio/1770930546360-Applicants_must_be_U.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1770930543607-Applicants_must_be_U.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1770930544518-Applicants_must_be_F.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1770930545444-U_S__citizenship_is_.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1770930546360-Applicants_must_be_U.timestamps.json"]	/audio/1770930542969-Which_of_the_followi.mp3	/timestamps/1770930542969-Which_of_the_followi.timestamps.json
cmljyhw70007sr4evywv4xafp	cmk8if4vt0000sxhb8i62wdi6	Regarding criminal history, what must an applicant disclose on their application?	{"Only felonies committed within the last 5 years","Only convictions where they served jail time","Any conviction, guilty plea, or plea of \\"nolo contendere,\\" even if adjudication was withheld","Nothing, if the record was sealed or expunged"}	2	{"correct": "Applicants must fully disclose if they have been convicted, entered a plea of guilty or \\"nolo contendere,\\" even if adjudication was withheld or the record was sealed/expunged.", "incorrect": ["All crimes (convictions/pleas) must be disclosed, not just recent felonies.", "Withheld adjudication and pleas must also be disclosed.", "", "Disclosure is required even if the record was sealed or expunged."]}	16	chapter	2026-02-12 21:13:58.332	2026-02-12 21:13:58.332	\N	\N	\N	\N	/audio/1770930824234-Applicants_must_full.mp3	/timestamps/1770930824234-Applicants_must_full.timestamps.json	["/audio/1770930825309-All_crimes__convicti.mp3", "/audio/1770930826103-Withheld_adjudicatio.mp3", "", "/audio/1770930827083-Disclosure_is_requir.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1770930825309-All_crimes__convicti.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1770930826103-Withheld_adjudicatio.timestamps.json", "", "/timestamps/1770930827083-Disclosure_is_requir.timestamps.json"]	["/audio/1770930819164-Only_felonies_commit.mp3", "/audio/1770930820082-Only_convictions_whe.mp3", "/audio/1770930821329-Any_conviction__guil.mp3", "/audio/1770930822099-Nothing__if_the_reco.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1770930819164-Only_felonies_commit.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1770930820082-Only_convictions_whe.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1770930821329-Any_conviction__guil.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1770930822099-Nothing__if_the_reco.timestamps.json"]	/audio/1770930818170-Regarding_criminal_h.mp3	/timestamps/1770930818170-Regarding_criminal_h.timestamps.json
cmljynrrw007ur4evvy7yp3xy	cmk8if4vt0000sxhb8i62wdi6	Why is a U.S. Social Security number required for all applicants?	{"To register them for the draft","To determine compliance with child support obligations","To verify their credit score","To automatically register them to vote"}	1	{"correct": "Social Security number is used to determine whether applicants are in compliance with child support obligations.", "incorrect": ["Drafting is not the purpose&nbsp;", "", "Credit score is not important in this case&nbsp;", "Not the correct purpose"]}	17	chapter	2026-02-12 21:18:32.539	2026-02-12 21:18:32.539	\N	\N	\N	\N	/audio/1770931104852-Social_Security_numb.mp3	/timestamps/1770931104852-Social_Security_numb.timestamps.json	["/audio/1770931105516-Drafting_is_not_the_.mp3", "", "/audio/1770931106285-Credit_score_is_not_.mp3", "/audio/1770931106993-Not_the_correct_purp.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1770931105516-Drafting_is_not_the_.timestamps.json", "", "/timestamps/1770931106285-Credit_score_is_not_.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1770931106993-Not_the_correct_purp.timestamps.json"]	["/audio/1770931101095-To_register_them_for.mp3", "/audio/1770931101893-To_determine_complia.mp3", "/audio/1770931102658-To_verify_their_cred.mp3", "/audio/1770931103342-To_automatically_reg.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1770931101095-To_register_them_for.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1770931101893-To_determine_complia.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1770931102658-To_verify_their_cred.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1770931103342-To_automatically_reg.timestamps.json"]	/audio/1770931099848-Why_is_a_U_S__Social.mp3	/timestamps/1770931099848-Why_is_a_U_S__Social.timestamps.json
cmljyvom2007wr4evd0hsmatk	cmk8if4vt0000sxhb8i62wdi6	Under Chapter 455.11, can a non-citizen immigrant take the real estate examination?	{"No, only U.S. citizens can take the exam","Yes, but only if they have lived in Florida for 5 years","Yes, as long as they are legally authorized to work in the United States","No, they must wait until they are naturalized"}	2	{"correct": "&nbsp;Chapter 455.11 allows immigrants to qualify for the exam if they are legally authorized to work in the U.S., ensuring qualified individuals can enter the profession.", "incorrect": ["Non-citizens can qualify.", "The condition is work authorization, not a specific residency duration.", "", "Naturalization is not required if they have work authorization."]}	18	chapter	2026-02-12 21:24:41.69	2026-02-12 21:24:41.69	\N	\N	\N	\N	/audio/1770931471592-Chapter_455_11_allow.mp3	/timestamps/1770931471592-Chapter_455_11_allow.timestamps.json	["/audio/1770931472272-Non_citizens_can_qua.mp3", "/audio/1770931473549-The_condition_is_wor.mp3", "", "/audio/1770931474465-Naturalization_is_no.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1770931472272-Non_citizens_can_qua.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1770931473549-The_condition_is_wor.timestamps.json", "", "/timestamps/1770931474465-Naturalization_is_no.timestamps.json"]	["/audio/1770931467200-No__only_U_S__citize.mp3", "/audio/1770931468066-Yes__but_only_if_the.mp3", "/audio/1770931469079-Yes__as_long_as_they.mp3", "/audio/1770931469900-No__they_must_wait_u.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1770931467200-No__only_U_S__citize.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1770931468066-Yes__but_only_if_the.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1770931469079-Yes__as_long_as_they.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1770931469900-No__they_must_wait_u.timestamps.json"]	/audio/1770931466365-Under_Chapter_455_11.mp3	/timestamps/1770931466365-Under_Chapter_455_11.timestamps.json
cmljyzop5007yr4ev1rev4no7	cmk8if4vt0000sxhb8i62wdi6	A military veteran is applying for a real estate sales associate license 4 years after being honorably discharged. Which fees are waived for this applicant?	{"Initial licensing fee, application fee, and unlicensed activity fee"," Application fee only","None, because the 24-month window has passed","Examination fee only"}	0	{"correct": "Under Chapter 455.213, F.S., honorably discharged veterans who apply within 60 months (5 years) of discharge are eligible for a waiver of the initial license, application, and unlicensed activity fees.", "incorrect": ["", "The waiver covers more than just the application fee.&nbsp;", "The window is extended to 60 months (5 years).&nbsp;", "Examination fees are typically paid to third-party vendors and are not waived by the DBPR."]}	19	chapter	2026-02-12 21:27:48.425	2026-02-12 21:27:48.425	\N	\N	\N	\N	/audio/1770931656637-Under_Chapter_455_21.mp3	/timestamps/1770931656637-Under_Chapter_455_21.timestamps.json	["", "/audio/1770931657373-The_waiver_covers_mo.mp3", "/audio/1770931658372-The_window_is_extend.mp3", "/audio/1770931659611-Examination_fees_are.mp3"]	["", "/timestamps/1770931657373-The_waiver_covers_mo.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1770931658372-The_window_is_extend.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1770931659611-Examination_fees_are.timestamps.json"]	["/audio/1770931651966-Initial_licensing_fe.mp3", "/audio/1770931652637-Application_fee_only.mp3", "/audio/1770931653602-None__because_the_24.mp3", "/audio/1770931654320-Examination_fee_only.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1770931651966-Initial_licensing_fe.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1770931652637-Application_fee_only.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1770931653602-None__because_the_24.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1770931654320-Examination_fee_only.timestamps.json"]	/audio/1770931650940-A_military_veteran_i.mp3	/timestamps/1770931650940-A_military_veteran_i.timestamps.json
cmljxob3s007cr4evji001z4f	cmk8if4vt0000sxhb8i62wdi6	What was a major consequence of the real estate industry operating under "caveat emptor"?	{"Greater trust between buyers and sellers","Unfair practices and financial harm to consumers","Strict enforcement of ethical standards","A decrease in property values"}	1	{"correct": "The lack of oversight and disclosure requirements often led to unfair practices, misinformation, and financial harm to buyers.", "incorrect": ["The lack of rules led to mistrust, not trust.", "", "There was lack of oversight, rules, and standards.", "While harm occurred, the text focuses on fairness and accountability, not specifically on market values dropping."]}	9	chapter	2026-02-12 20:50:57.976	2026-02-12 21:20:38.973	\N	\N	\N	\N	/audio/1770931229272-The_lack_of_oversigh.mp3	/timestamps/1770931229272-The_lack_of_oversigh.timestamps.json	["/audio/1770931230089-The_lack_of_rules_le.mp3", "", "/audio/1770931230981-There_was_lack_of_ov.mp3", "/audio/1770931232676-While_harm_occurred_.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1770931230089-The_lack_of_rules_le.timestamps.json", "", "/timestamps/1770931230981-There_was_lack_of_ov.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1770931232676-While_harm_occurred_.timestamps.json"]	["/audio/1770931225394-Greater_trust_betwee.mp3", "/audio/1770931226286-Unfair_practices_and.mp3", "/audio/1770931226983-Strict_enforcement_o.mp3", "/audio/1770931227657-A_decrease_in_proper.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1770931225394-Greater_trust_betwee.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1770931226286-Unfair_practices_and.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1770931226983-Strict_enforcement_o.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1770931227657-A_decrease_in_proper.timestamps.json"]	/audio/1770931224652-What_was_a_major_con.mp3	/timestamps/1770931224652-What_was_a_major_con.timestamps.json
cmljz277w0080r4ev1561m20q	cmk8if4vt0000sxhb8i62wdi6	A low-income individual applying for a license may qualify for a fee waiver if their household income is at or below what percentage of the federal poverty guidelines?	{100%,130%,150%,200%}	1	{"correct": "Chapter 455.219, F.S. defines a low-income individual as someone whose household income is at or below 130% of the federal poverty guidelines.", "incorrect": ["The threshold is higher than the base poverty line.&nbsp;", "", "This is higher than the statutory limit.&nbsp;", "This is significantly higher than the statutory limit."]}	20	chapter	2026-02-12 21:29:45.74	2026-02-12 21:29:45.74	\N	\N	\N	\N	/audio/1770931779340-Chapter_455_219__F_S.mp3	/timestamps/1770931779340-Chapter_455_219__F_S.timestamps.json	["/audio/1770931780221-The_threshold_is_hig.mp3", "", "/audio/1770931781206-This_is_higher_than_.mp3", "/audio/1770931782027-This_is_significantl.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1770931780221-The_threshold_is_hig.timestamps.json", "", "/timestamps/1770931781206-This_is_higher_than_.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1770931782027-This_is_significantl.timestamps.json"]	["/audio/1770931774886-100_.mp3", "/audio/1770931775486-130_.mp3", "/audio/1770931776318-150_.mp3", "/audio/1770931777017-200_.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1770931774886-100_.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1770931775486-130_.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1770931776318-150_.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1770931777017-200_.timestamps.json"]	/audio/1770931773959-A_low_income_individ.mp3	/timestamps/1770931773959-A_low_income_individ.timestamps.json
cmlk2rxw3008yr4evcc6wya3i	cmk8if4vt0000sxhb8i62wdi6	The term "Prima Facie Evidence" regarding a real estate license best means:	{"The license is only valid if notarized","The physical license is evidence that the holder is validly licensed, unless refuted","The license has expired","The licensee has completed all continuing education"}	1	{"correct": "Prima facie means \\"at first sight.\\" The license itself serves as immediate legal proof of licensure.", "incorrect": ["Real estate licenses do not require notarization to be valid legal evidence.", "", "Prima facie evidence supports the validity of the license, not its expiration.", "While a valid license implies requirements are met, the term \\"prima facie evidence\\" refers to the legal weight of the document itself as proof of licensure, not a specific statement about continuing education credits."]}	37	chapter	2026-02-12 23:13:45.498	2026-02-12 23:13:45.498	\N	\N	\N	\N	/audio/1770938018243-Prima_facie_means__a.mp3	/timestamps/1770938018243-Prima_facie_means__a.timestamps.json	["/audio/1770938019357-Real_estate_licenses.mp3", "", "/audio/1770938020274-Prima_facie_evidence.mp3", "/audio/1770938022595-While_a_valid_licens.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1770938019357-Real_estate_licenses.timestamps.json", "", "/timestamps/1770938020274-Prima_facie_evidence.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1770938022595-While_a_valid_licens.timestamps.json"]	["/audio/1770938013816-The_license_is_only_.mp3", "/audio/1770938015150-The_physical_license.mp3", "/audio/1770938015947-The_license_has_expi.mp3", "/audio/1770938016764-The_licensee_has_com.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1770938013816-The_license_is_only_.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1770938015150-The_physical_license.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1770938015947-The_license_has_expi.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1770938016764-The_licensee_has_com.timestamps.json"]	/audio/1770938012903-The_term__Prima_Faci.mp3	/timestamps/1770938012903-The_term__Prima_Faci.timestamps.json
cmllll4gz009dr4evmbqac6pb	cmk8if4vt0000sxhb8i62wdi6	When you get a real estate sales associate license, you may operate:<div><br></div>	{"As an independent realtor ","For any broker ","For a broker who is registered as your employing broker ","As a broker associate"}	2	{"correct": "A sales associate must perform all real estate services under the direction, control, and management of one employing broker (or owner-developer) who is officially registered with the DBPR as their employer.", "incorrect": ["Sales associates cannot operate independently; only active Brokers can operate independently.", "You cannot work for \\"any\\" broker; you must work specifically for the one you are registered with.", "", "\\"Broker Associate\\" is a specific license status for someone who is qualified to be a broker but chooses to work under another broker. A sales associate operates as a \\"Sales Associate,\\" not a Broker Associate (unless they upgrade their license)."]}	38	chapter	2026-02-14 00:48:06.371	2026-02-14 00:48:06.371	\N	\N	\N	\N	/audio/1771030076892-A_sales_associate_mu.mp3	/timestamps/1771030076892-A_sales_associate_mu.timestamps.json	["/audio/1771030078151-Sales_associates_can.mp3", "/audio/1771030079353-You_cannot_work_for_.mp3", "", "/audio/1771030081216-_Broker_Associate__i.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1771030078151-Sales_associates_can.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771030079353-You_cannot_work_for_.timestamps.json", "", "/timestamps/1771030081216-_Broker_Associate__i.timestamps.json"]	["/audio/1771030072958-As_an_independent_re.mp3", "/audio/1771030073511-For_any_broker.mp3", "/audio/1771030074379-For_a_broker_who_is_.mp3", "/audio/1771030074922-As_a_broker_associat.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1771030072958-As_an_independent_re.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771030073511-For_any_broker.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771030074379-For_a_broker_who_is_.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771030074922-As_a_broker_associat.timestamps.json"]	/audio/1771030072199-When_you_get_a_real_.mp3	/timestamps/1771030072199-When_you_get_a_real_.timestamps.json
cmlllq3e3009fr4evvr7h5mwb	cmk8if4vt0000sxhb8i62wdi6	&nbsp;In which case is a sales associate NOT qualified to get a Broker's license in Florida?	{"A licensee who held a broker's license in another state for 2 of the last 5 years","A licensee who held a sales associate license in another state for the last 2 out of 5 years","A licensee who held a sales associate license for the last 2 out of 5 years, while employed by an owner-developer in Florida","All of the above"}	2	{"correct": "To qualify for a Broker's license, the 24 months of experience must be active experience under a licensed broker (in Florida or another state). Experience gained while working for an owner-developer (who is not a licensed broker) does not count toward the broker experience requirement.<div><br></div>", "incorrect": ["Active experience as a broker in another state counts toward the requirement.", "Active experience as a sales associate in another state counts toward the requirement.", "", "Only option C is the disqualifying factor."]}	39	chapter	2026-02-14 00:51:58.25	2026-02-14 00:51:58.25	\N	\N	\N	\N	/audio/1771030310526-To_qualify_for_a_Bro.mp3	/timestamps/1771030310526-To_qualify_for_a_Bro.timestamps.json	["/audio/1771030311611-Active_experience_as.mp3", "/audio/1771030312895-Active_experience_as.mp3", "", "/audio/1771030313667-Only_option_C_is_the.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1771030311611-Active_experience_as.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771030312895-Active_experience_as.timestamps.json", "", "/timestamps/1771030313667-Only_option_C_is_the.timestamps.json"]	["/audio/1771030304763-A_licensee_who_held_.mp3", "/audio/1771030305902-A_licensee_who_held_.mp3", "/audio/1771030307382-A_licensee_who_held_.mp3", "/audio/1771030308002-All_of_the_above.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1771030304763-A_licensee_who_held_.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771030305902-A_licensee_who_held_.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771030307382-A_licensee_who_held_.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771030308002-All_of_the_above.time