cmlllsgo4009hr4ev3dg4r0vh	cmk8if4vt0000sxhb8i62wdi6	What appears on a real estate license?&nbsp;	{"License Number & Brokerage Name ","FREC Secretary Signature and issuance date ","Department of Real Estate Stamp and expiration date ","Florida Real Estate Commission Stamp"}	0	{"correct": "The face of the license (wallet card) includes the License Number and the name of the Broker or Brokerage (employer) the licensee is registered with. This serves as prima facie evidence of who the associate is authorized to work for.", "incorrect": ["", "The license bears the name of the Governor and the Secretary of the DBPR, not the \\"FREC Secretary.\\"", "There is no \\"Department of Real Estate\\" stamp. The license bears the Seal of the State of Florida. (Also, the regulatory body is the Division of Real Estate, not Department).", "The license displays the Seal of the State of Florida, not a specific \\"FREC Stamp.\\""]}	40	chapter	2026-02-14 00:53:48.772	2026-02-14 00:53:48.772	\N	\N	\N	\N	/audio/1771030419830-The_face_of_the_lice.mp3	/timestamps/1771030419830-The_face_of_the_lice.timestamps.json	["", "/audio/1771030421265-The_license_bears_th.mp3", "/audio/1771030422970-There_is_no__Departm.mp3", "/audio/1771030424063-The_license_displays.mp3"]	["", "/timestamps/1771030421265-The_license_bears_th.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771030422970-There_is_no__Departm.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771030424063-The_license_displays.timestamps.json"]	["/audio/1771030415820-License_Number___Bro.mp3", "/audio/1771030416547-FREC_Secretary_Signa.mp3", "/audio/1771030417372-Department_of_Real_E.mp3", "/audio/1771030418040-Florida_Real_Estate_.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1771030415820-License_Number___Bro.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771030416547-FREC_Secretary_Signa.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771030417372-Department_of_Real_E.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771030418040-Florida_Real_Estate_.timestamps.json"]	/audio/1771030415076-What_appears_on_a_re.mp3	/timestamps/1771030415076-What_appears_on_a_re.timestamps.json
cmlllvtio009jr4evdt5656of	cmk8if4vt0000sxhb8i62wdi6	Can a sales associate, working on a commission basis, be employed by 2 different brokers?	{"Only if approved by DBPR ",Never,"Only for rental properties","Only for commercial properties"}	1	{"correct": "A sales associate (or broker associate) may have only one registered employer at any given time. They cannot work for two separate brokers simultaneously. (Note: Only a Broker—not a sales associate—may hold \\"Multiple Licenses\\" if they are the broker of record for two connected companies.)", "incorrect": ["The DBPR does not grant exceptions for sales associates to have multiple employers.", "", "No exception exists for rental properties.", "No exception exists for commercial properties."]}	41	chapter	2026-02-14 00:56:25.392	2026-02-14 00:56:25.392	\N	\N	\N	\N	/audio/1771030577717-A_sales_associate__o.mp3	/timestamps/1771030577717-A_sales_associate__o.timestamps.json	["/audio/1771030579162-The_DBPR_does_not_gr.mp3", "", "/audio/1771030579948-No_exception_exists_.mp3", "/audio/1771030580662-No_exception_exists_.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1771030579162-The_DBPR_does_not_gr.timestamps.json", "", "/timestamps/1771030579948-No_exception_exists_.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771030580662-No_exception_exists_.timestamps.json"]	["/audio/1771030572899-Only_if_approved_by_.mp3", "/audio/1771030573410-Never.mp3", "/audio/1771030574348-Only_for_rental_prop.mp3", "/audio/1771030575039-Only_for_commercial_.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1771030572899-Only_if_approved_by_.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771030573410-Never.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771030574348-Only_for_rental_prop.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771030575039-Only_for_commercial_.timestamps.json"]	/audio/1771030572201-Can_a_sales_associat.mp3	/timestamps/1771030572201-Can_a_sales_associat.timestamps.json
cmlllyyu3009lr4ev8fl3hmv0	cmk8if4vt0000sxhb8i62wdi6	David is an active duty member of US Army, who has been ordered to relocate to a base in Florida. His spouse Amy is a licensed real estate broker in Georgia and wishes to continue her career as a broker in Florida. What does Amy need to do?	{"Apply for a license by mutual recognition, provide proof of the spouse’s military status, submit fingerprints, and pass the Florida law exam","Apply for a license by exam, provide proof of the spouse’s military status, submit fingerprints, complete the broker pre-license course, and pass the state broker exam","Apply for a license by endorsement (or reciprocity), provide proof of the spouse’s military status and assignment to Florida, and submit fingerprints for a background check","Apply for a sales associate license by exam, provide proof of the spouse’s military status, submit fingerprints, and pass the sales associate state exam"}	2	{"correct": "Under Florida Statute 455.02, the spouse of an active duty member assigned to Florida may obtain a license by endorsement (reciprocity) without taking any pre-license course or state exam, provided they hold a valid license in another state.", "incorrect": ["\\"Mutual recognition\\" requires passing a 40-question law exam. Since the military spouse rule waives all exams, she does not need to use the mutual recognition path.", "She is exempt from the pre-license course and the state exam, so she does not need to apply by exam.", "", "She is already a broker; she does not need to step down to a sales associate license.&nbsp;"]}	42	chapter	2026-02-14 00:58:52.251	2026-02-14 00:58:52.251	\N	\N	\N	\N	/audio/1771030717599-Under_Florida_Statut.mp3	/timestamps/1771030717599-Under_Florida_Statut.timestamps.json	["/audio/1771030719887-_Mutual_recognition_.mp3", "/audio/1771030721092-She_is_exempt_from_t.mp3", "", "/audio/1771030722311-She_is_already_a_bro.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1771030719887-_Mutual_recognition_.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771030721092-She_is_exempt_from_t.timestamps.json", "", "/timestamps/1771030722311-She_is_already_a_bro.timestamps.json"]	["/audio/1771030709547-Apply_for_a_license_.mp3", "/audio/1771030711472-Apply_for_a_license_.mp3", "/audio/1771030713088-Apply_for_a_license_.mp3", "/audio/1771030714866-Apply_for_a_sales_as.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1771030709547-Apply_for_a_license_.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771030711472-Apply_for_a_license_.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771030713088-Apply_for_a_license_.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771030714866-Apply_for_a_sales_as.timestamps.json"]	/audio/1771030708055-David_is_an_active_d.mp3	/timestamps/1771030708055-David_is_an_active_d.timestamps.json
cmllm2p3f009nr4evccckir9q	cmk8if4vt0000sxhb8i62wdi6	An applicant was working as a sales associate in another state, which has a mutual recognition agreement with Florida. Half a year ago, the applicant moved to Florida. Is he/she still eligible to apply for a Florida real estate license under mutual recognition?	{"Yes, the applicant is eligible under mutual recognition","No, because Florida doesn't recognize agreements from other states  ","Yes, on case by case basis, with DBPR approval  ","No, because the applicant is a Florida resident now"}	3	{"correct": "Mutual recognition is reserved specifically for non-residents. Under Florida real estate law, a person who has resided in Florida for 4 months or more is considered a resident. Since the applicant moved 6 months ago, they are a resident and must take the standard pre-license course and state exam.", "incorrect": ["They are no longer eligible because they are a resident.", "Florida does recognize agreements (with some states), but only for non-residents.", "There is no case-by-case waiver for the residency rule.", ""]}	43	chapter	2026-02-14 01:01:46.251	2026-02-14 01:01:46.251	\N	\N	\N	\N	/audio/1771030898845-Mutual_recognition_i.mp3	/timestamps/1771030898845-Mutual_recognition_i.timestamps.json	["/audio/1771030899616-They_are_no_longer_e.mp3", "/audio/1771030900542-Florida_does_recogni.mp3", "/audio/1771030901589-There_is_no_case_by_.mp3", ""]	["/timestamps/1771030899616-They_are_no_longer_e.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771030900542-Florida_does_recogni.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771030901589-There_is_no_case_by_.timestamps.json", ""]	["/audio/1771030893695-Yes__the_applicant_i.mp3", "/audio/1771030894631-No__because_Florida_.mp3", "/audio/1771030895479-Yes__on_case_by_case.mp3", "/audio/1771030896413-No__because_the_appl.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1771030893695-Yes__the_applicant_i.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771030894631-No__because_Florida_.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771030895479-Yes__on_case_by_case.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771030896413-No__because_the_appl.timestamps.json"]	/audio/1771030892318-An_applicant_was_wor.mp3	/timestamps/1771030892318-An_applicant_was_wor.timestamps.json
cmllm51zu009pr4evlkj04ews	cmk8if4vt0000sxhb8i62wdi6	If a sales associate in Florida does not complete the 45-hour post-licensing course before the first renewal, but still wants to practice, which of the following applies:	{"They are allowed up to 3 months grace period to meet the requirement ","They are allowed up to 6 months grace period to meet the requirement  ","They have to pass Florida State Exam again  ","They will have to take the 63 hour course and pass Florida State Exam again"}	3	{"correct": "Failure to complete the post-licensing education before the first expiration date causes the license to become null and void. To practice again, the individual must basically start over: take the 63-hour pre-license course and pass the state exam again.", "incorrect": ["There is no grace period for the first renewal (post-licensing). Grace periods (involuntary inactive status) only apply to subsequent renewals (Continuing Education).", "There is no grace period for the first renewal (post-licensing). Grace periods (involuntary inactive status) only apply to subsequent renewals (Continuing Education).", "They cannot just retake the exam; they must also retake the pre-license course.", ""]}	44	chapter	2026-02-14 01:03:36.282	2026-02-14 01:03:36.282	\N	\N	\N	\N	/audio/1771031007336-Failure_to_complete_.mp3	/timestamps/1771031007336-Failure_to_complete_.timestamps.json	["/audio/1771031008938-There_is_no_grace_pe.mp3", "/audio/1771031010372-There_is_no_grace_pe.mp3", "/audio/1771031011422-They_cannot_just_ret.mp3", ""]	["/timestamps/1771031008938-There_is_no_grace_pe.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771031010372-There_is_no_grace_pe.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771031011422-They_cannot_just_ret.timestamps.json", ""]	["/audio/1771031002769-They_are_allowed_up_.mp3", "/audio/1771031003643-They_are_allowed_up_.mp3", "/audio/1771031004389-They_have_to_pass_Fl.mp3", "/audio/1771031005355-They_will_have_to_ta.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1771031002769-They_are_allowed_up_.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771031003643-They_are_allowed_up_.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771031004389-They_have_to_pass_Fl.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771031005355-They_will_have_to_ta.timestamps.json"]	/audio/1771031001409-If_a_sales_associate.mp3	/timestamps/1771031001409-If_a_sales_associate.timestamps.json
cmlpryj6m00jsr4ev69zk2hjd	cmlpniy5e00gyr4ev7l7y4vur	A principal instructs their real estate broker to take a specific action. The broker recognizes that following these instructions will likely result in financial loss or harm to the principal. What is the broker's professional obligation in this situation?	{"The broker is justified in unilaterally ignoring the instructions to protect the client","The broker must follow the instructions immediately without questioning the principal's judgment","The broker should selectively follow only the parts of the instructions that are safe and ignore the harmful parts","The broker should explain the potential risks and harm to the principal, and then either follow the instructions or withdraw from the engagement"}	3	{"correct": "A Single Agent owes the duties of Full Disclosure and Skill, Care, and Diligence. If an instruction is harmful (but legal), the broker cannot remain silent; they must warn the principal of the consequences. However, the duty of Obedience means the Principal is the boss. If the Principal understands the risk and still insists on the action, the broker must either obey the lawful instruction or resign if they feel they cannot in good conscience proceed.", "incorrect": ["A broker cannot simply refuse to follow instructions they dislike. Unless the instruction is illegal, the duty of Obedience generally requires compliance. Ignoring the client is a breach of contract.", "Following harmful instructions \\"without question\\" violates the duty of Skill, Care, and Diligence. A fiduciary has a responsibility to counsel their client and prevent them from making uneducated mistakes.", "A broker is not authorized to modify a client's instructions. You cannot choose to do \\"half\\" the job. You must advise the client and then follow the agreed-upon plan or resign.", ""]}	19	chapter	2026-02-16 22:57:34.365	2026-02-16 23:18:00.825	\N	\N	\N	\N	/audio/1771283875663-A_Single_Agent_owes_.mp3	/timestamps/1771283875663-A_Single_Agent_owes_.timestamps.json	["/audio/1771283877470-A_broker_cannot_simp.mp3", "/audio/1771283879097-Following_harmful_in.mp3", "/audio/1771283880587-A_broker_is_not_auth.mp3", ""]	["/timestamps/1771283877470-A_broker_cannot_simp.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771283879097-Following_harmful_in.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771283880587-A_broker_is_not_auth.timestamps.json", ""]	["/audio/1771283868475-The_broker_is_justif.mp3", "/audio/1771283869578-The_broker_must_foll.mp3", "/audio/1771283870652-The_broker_should_se.mp3", "/audio/1771283872000-The_broker_should_ex.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1771283868475-The_broker_is_justif.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771283869578-The_broker_must_foll.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771283870652-The_broker_should_se.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771283872000-The_broker_should_ex.timestamps.json"]	/audio/1771283867398-A_principal_instruct.mp3	/timestamps/1771283867398-A_principal_instruct.timestamps.json
cmlps2g3500jur4evmgr7jq41	cmlpniy5e00gyr4ev7l7y4vur	A broker has a "No Brokerage Relationship" (Nonrepresentation) with a consumer.&nbsp;<div>Which of the following duties does the broker still owe to this individual?</div>	{"Full disclosure","Accounting for all funds",Loyalty,"Limited confidentiality"}	1	{"correct": "Even in a No Brokerage Relationship (where you do not represent the customer), Florida law mandates three basic duties: 1) Deal honestly and fairly, 2) Disclose known material facts, and 3) Account for all funds. You must always safeguard money entrusted to you, regardless of the relationship.", "incorrect": ["Full disclosure is a fiduciary duty owed exclusively to a principal in a Single Agent relationship.", "", "Loyalty is a fiduciary duty owed exclusively to a principal in a Single Agent relationship.", "Limited confidentiality is a specific duty owed to a client in a Transaction Broker relationship."]}	20	chapter	2026-02-16 23:00:36.977	2026-02-16 23:18:11.065	\N	\N	\N	\N	/audio/1771283887367-Even_in_a_No_Brokera.mp3	/timestamps/1771283887367-Even_in_a_No_Brokera.timestamps.json	["/audio/1771283888643-Full_disclosure_is_a.mp3", "", "/audio/1771283889867-Loyalty_is_a_fiducia.mp3", "/audio/1771283890916-Limited_confidential.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1771283888643-Full_disclosure_is_a.timestamps.json", "", "/timestamps/1771283889867-Loyalty_is_a_fiducia.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771283890916-Limited_confidential.timestamps.json"]	["/audio/1771283882853-Full_disclosure.mp3", "/audio/1771283883443-Accounting_for_all_f.mp3", "/audio/1771283884037-Loyalty.mp3", "/audio/1771283884736-Limited_confidential.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1771283882853-Full_disclosure.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771283883443-Accounting_for_all_f.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771283884037-Loyalty.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771283884736-Limited_confidential.timestamps.json"]	/audio/1771283882329-A_broker_has_a__No_B.mp3	/timestamps/1771283882329-A_broker_has_a__No_B.timestamps.json
cmlodj44800djr4evze2lcagi	cmlo3p21500b9r4evvq0cbmdp	A licensed broker wants to open two separate real estate brokerages and be the qualifying broker for both. Which type of license must they request?	{"Group License ","Multiple Licenses ","Corporate License ","Dual Agency License"}	1	{"correct": "A broker may hold \\"Multiple Licenses\\" if they can prove it is necessary for their business to serve as the broker of record for more than one brokerage entity.", "incorrect": ["Group licenses are for associates working for developers.&nbsp;", "", "A corporation gets registered, but the broker holds the multiple licenses to run it.", "Dual Agency is illegal in Florida; this is a distractor term."]}	25	chapter	2026-02-15 23:25:54.2	2026-02-16 13:59:44.575	\N	\N	\N	\N	/audio/1771250381476-A_broker_may_hold__M.mp3	/timestamps/1771250381476-A_broker_may_hold__M.timestamps.json	["/audio/1771250382392-Group_licenses_are_f.mp3", "", "/audio/1771250383339-A_corporation_gets_r.mp3", "/audio/1771250384333-Dual_Agency_is_illeg.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1771250382392-Group_licenses_are_f.timestamps.json", "", "/timestamps/1771250383339-A_corporation_gets_r.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771250384333-Dual_Agency_is_illeg.timestamps.json"]	["/audio/1771250378014-Group_License.mp3", "/audio/1771250378593-Multiple_Licenses.mp3", "/audio/1771250379194-Corporate_License.mp3", "/audio/1771250379994-Dual_Agency_License.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1771250378014-Group_License.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771250378593-Multiple_Licenses.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771250379194-Corporate_License.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771250379994-Dual_Agency_License.timestamps.json"]	/audio/1771250377362-A_licensed_broker_wa.mp3	/timestamps/1771250377362-A_licensed_broker_wa.timestamps.json
cmlps6gu200jwr4evsctiepgb	cmlpniy5e00gyr4ev7l7y4vur	Which definition BEST describes "Designated Sales Associates"?	{"Sales associates appointed as single agents for the buyer and the seller in nonresidential transactions where both parties meet specific high-asset thresholds","Sales associates designated to facilitate a transaction as transaction brokers for both parties","Agents acting as undisclosed dual agents in residential transaction","The administrative staff responsible for maintaining brokerage disclosure files"}	0	{"correct": "Designated Sales Associates are a special exception for non-residential (commercial) transactions where both the buyer and seller have assets of $1 million or more. In this case, the broker designates one associate to act as a Single Agent for the buyer and another to act as a Single Agent for the seller.", "incorrect": ["", "Designated associates act as Single Agents (fiduciaries), not Transaction Brokers.", "Undisclosed dual agency is illegal. Designated sales associate status is a legal, disclosed arrangement.", "This is a distractor describing an office administrator role, not the legal agency status defined by statute."]}	21	chapter	2026-02-16 23:03:44.57	2026-02-16 23:18:22.713	\N	\N	\N	\N	/audio/1771283898602-Designated_Sales_Ass.mp3	/timestamps/1771283898602-Designated_Sales_Ass.timestamps.json	["", "/audio/1771283899687-Designated_associate.mp3", "/audio/1771283901295-Undisclosed_dual_age.mp3", "/audio/1771283902506-This_is_a_distractor.mp3"]	["", "/timestamps/1771283899687-Designated_associate.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771283901295-Undisclosed_dual_age.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771283902506-This_is_a_distractor.timestamps.json"]	["/audio/1771283893490-Sales_associates_app.mp3", "/audio/1771283894518-Sales_associates_des.mp3", "/audio/1771283895395-Agents_acting_as_und.mp3", "/audio/1771283896243-The_administrative_s.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1771283893490-Sales_associates_app.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771283894518-Sales_associates_des.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771283895395-Agents_acting_as_und.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771283896243-The_administrative_s.timestamps.json"]	/audio/1771283892035-Which_definition_BES.mp3	/timestamps/1771283892035-Which_definition_BES.timestamps.json
cmltsick300pnr4evo11f4k5f	cmlslqsgt00l1r4evfhnwe7be	&nbsp;The illegal act of mixing personal or business funds with trust funds is called:	{Conversion,Commingling,Reconciliation,Arbitration}	1	{"correct": "Commingling is the mixing of broker funds with client funds.", "incorrect": ["Conversion is the use (stealing) of the funds.", "", "Reconciliation is the balancing of the books (legal and required).", "<div>Arbitration is a dispute resolution process.<br></div>"]}	15	chapter	2026-02-19 18:24:03.603	2026-02-19 19:58:12.638	\N	\N	\N	\N	/audio/1771531089780-Commingling_is_the_m.mp3	/timestamps/1771531089780-Commingling_is_the_m.timestamps.json	["/audio/1771531090738-Conversion_is_the_us.mp3", "", "/audio/1771531091673-Reconciliation_is_th.mp3", "/audio/1771531092471-Arbitration_is_a_dis.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1771531090738-Conversion_is_the_us.timestamps.json", "", "/timestamps/1771531091673-Reconciliation_is_th.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771531092471-Arbitration_is_a_dis.timestamps.json"]	["/audio/1771531087214-Conversion.mp3", "/audio/1771531087740-Commingling.mp3", "/audio/1771531088264-Reconciliation.mp3", "/audio/1771531088821-Arbitration.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1771531087214-Conversion.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771531087740-Commingling.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771531088264-Reconciliation.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771531088821-Arbitration.timestamps.json"]	/audio/1771531086674-The_illegal_act_of_m.mp3	/timestamps/1771531086674-The_illegal_act_of_m.timestamps.json
cmlodqmmq00dpr4ev7xb9f4t7	cmlo3p21500b9r4evvq0cbmdp	Where are the headquarters of the Division of Real Estate (DRE) located?	{Tallahassee,Orlando,Miami,Tampa}	1	{"correct": "DRE is headquartered in Orlando.", "incorrect": ["Tallahassee is the location of the DBPR offices, not the DRE headquarters.", "", "Miami is not a headquarters location.", "Tampa is not s a headquarters location."]}	28	chapter	2026-02-15 23:31:44.786	2026-02-16 14:00:13.451	\N	\N	\N	\N	/audio/1771250410671-DRE_is_headquartered.mp3	/timestamps/1771250410671-DRE_is_headquartered.timestamps.json	["/audio/1771250411825-Tallahassee_is_the_l.mp3", "", "/audio/1771250412586-Miami_is_not_a_headq.mp3", "/audio/1771250413242-Tampa_is_not_s_a_hea.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1771250411825-Tallahassee_is_the_l.timestamps.json", "", "/timestamps/1771250412586-Miami_is_not_a_headq.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771250413242-Tampa_is_not_s_a_hea.timestamps.json"]	["/audio/1771250407972-Tallahassee.mp3", "/audio/1771250408592-Orlando.mp3", "/audio/1771250409226-Miami.mp3", "/audio/1771250409702-Tampa.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1771250407972-Tallahassee.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771250408592-Orlando.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771250409226-Miami.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771250409702-Tampa.timestamps.json"]	/audio/1771250407442-Where_are_the_headqu.mp3	/timestamps/1771250407442-Where_are_the_headqu.timestamps.json
cmlodozr200dnr4evyy7jewbe	cmlo3p21500b9r4evvq0cbmdp	How many years do Commission members serve?	{"1 Year","2 Years ","3 Years","4 Years "}	3	{"correct": "According to Florida Statute 475.02, members of the Florida Real Estate Commission (FREC) are appointed by the Governor for 4-year terms.  ", "incorrect": ["Commission members serve longer than 1 year; this short duration is typically associated with officer positions (like Chair or Vice-Chair) rather than the commission appointment itself. ", "While real estate licenses must be renewed every 2 years, the term for the Commissioners who regulate those licenses is 4 years.", "There is no 3-year term associated with FREC appointments; terms are specifically set at 4 years.", ""]}	27	chapter	2026-02-15 23:30:28.478	2026-02-16 14:00:06.389	\N	\N	\N	\N	/audio/1771250402321-According_to_Florida.mp3	/timestamps/1771250402321-According_to_Florida.timestamps.json	["/audio/1771250403996-Commission_members_s.mp3", "/audio/1771250405066-While_real_estate_li.mp3", "/audio/1771250406234-There_is_no_3_year_t.mp3", ""]	["/timestamps/1771250403996-Commission_members_s.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771250405066-While_real_estate_li.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771250406234-There_is_no_3_year_t.timestamps.json", ""]	["/audio/1771250399043-1_Year.mp3", "/audio/1771250399612-2_Years.mp3", "/audio/1771250400094-3_Years.mp3", "/audio/1771250400724-4_Years.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1771250399043-1_Year.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771250399612-2_Years.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771250400094-3_Years.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771250400724-4_Years.timestamps.json"]	/audio/1771250398396-How_many_years_do_Co.mp3	/timestamps/1771250398396-How_many_years_do_Co.timestamps.json
cmlpsdnyj00k0r4evanjjyy4w	cmlpniy5e00gyr4ev7l7y4vur	Which event would legally TERMINATE a single agent relationship between a broker and a seller who has listed their home?	{" The death of a prospective buyer (customer) who liked the house","The seller rejecting a buyer's offer","The sales associate who took the listing deciding to resign from the brokerage","The destruction of the property (e.g., by a large sinkhole)"}	3	{"correct": "Destruction of the property terminates the agency relationship by operation of law. If the \\"subject matter\\" of the contract no longer exists (the house is gone), the contract to sell it is void.", "incorrect": ["The death of a customer has no effect on the contract between the broker and the seller.", "Rejecting an offer is part of the negotiation process; it does not end the listing agreement.", "The listing contract belongs to the Broker, not the sales associate. If the associate leaves, the listing stays with the brokerage firm.", ""]}	23	chapter	2026-02-16 23:09:20.394	2026-02-16 23:18:44.942	\N	\N	\N	\N	/audio/1771283921186-Destruction_of_the_p.mp3	/timestamps/1771283921186-Destruction_of_the_p.timestamps.json	["/audio/1771283922404-The_death_of_a_custo.mp3", "/audio/1771283923397-Rejecting_an_offer_i.mp3", "/audio/1771283924780-The_listing_contract.mp3", ""]	["/timestamps/1771283922404-The_death_of_a_custo.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771283923397-Rejecting_an_offer_i.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771283924780-The_listing_contract.timestamps.json", ""]	["/audio/1771283917039-The_death_of_a_prosp.mp3", "/audio/1771283917742-The_seller_rejecting.mp3", "/audio/1771283918606-The_sales_associate_.mp3", "/audio/1771283919489-The_destruction_of_t.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1771283917039-The_death_of_a_prosp.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771283917742-The_seller_rejecting.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771283918606-The_sales_associate_.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771283919489-The_destruction_of_t.timestamps.json"]	/audio/1771283915999-Which_event_would_le.mp3	/timestamps/1771283915999-Which_event_would_le.timestamps.json
cmms3soe200ip4be7ruprazgq	cmmry1yz800fh4be796sih9l4	The size of homestead property is restricted to:	{"320 acres outside a city or up to 2 acres in town","160 acres outside a city or up to 0.5 acres in town","80 acres outside a city or up to 1 acre in town","40 acres outside a city or up to 0.25 acres in town"}	1	{"correct": "If the property is located outside a municipality (an unincorporated area), the protection extends to a maximum of 160 contiguous acres. If the property is located within a municipality (city or town limits), the protection is capped at one-half (0.5) of an acre of contiguous land.", "incorrect": ["This option provides inaccurate acreage limits, which does not reflect Florida's constitutional homestead provisions.", "", "This option provides inaccurate acreage limits, which does not reflect Florida's constitutional homestead provisions.", "This option provides inaccurate acreage limits, which does not reflect Florida's constitutional homestead provisions."]}	29	chapter	2026-03-15 18:44:11.258	2026-03-15 19:07:49.881	\N	\N	\N	\N	/audio/1773601664961-If_the_property_is_l.mp3	/timestamps/1773601664961-If_the_property_is_l.timestamps.json	["/audio/1773601666922-This_option_provides.mp3", "", "/audio/1773601668300-This_option_provides.mp3", "/audio/1773601669731-This_option_provides.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1773601666922-This_option_provides.timestamps.json", "", "/timestamps/1773601668300-This_option_provides.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1773601669731-This_option_provides.timestamps.json"]	["/audio/1773601657703-320_acres_outside_a_.mp3", "/audio/1773601658837-160_acres_outside_a_.mp3", "/audio/1773601659823-80_acres_outside_a_c.mp3", "/audio/1773601660906-40_acres_outside_a_c.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1773601657703-320_acres_outside_a_.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1773601658837-160_acres_outside_a_.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1773601659823-80_acres_outside_a_c.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1773601660906-40_acres_outside_a_c.timestamps.json"]	/audio/1773601656624-The_size_of_homestea.mp3	/timestamps/1773601656624-The_size_of_homestea.timestamps.json
cmlp7uu1200edr4evxal85yye	cmlo3p21500b9r4evvq0cbmdp	What number of FREC members may be licensed as active sales associates at one time?	{"One ","Two ",Three,Four}	0	{"correct": "The Florida Real Estate Commission is composed of five licensed members. Four of them must be brokers. Only one of the licensed members is permitted to be either a broker OR a sales associate. Therefore, the maximum number of sales associates allowed on the Commission at one time is one.", "incorrect": ["", "The law does not permit two sales associates; the other licensed seats are strictly reserved for brokers.", "The composition rules do not allow for three sales associates to serve simultaneously.", "Four is the number of members who are required to be brokers (with 5 years of experience), not sales associates."]}	37	chapter	2026-02-16 13:34:49.478	2026-02-16 14:01:31.65	\N	\N	\N	\N	/audio/1771250488122-The_Florida_Real_Est.mp3	/timestamps/1771250488122-The_Florida_Real_Est.timestamps.json	["", "/audio/1771250489338-The_law_does_not_per.mp3", "/audio/1771250490256-The_composition_rule.mp3", "/audio/1771250491492-Four_is_the_number_o.mp3"]	["", "/timestamps/1771250489338-The_law_does_not_per.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771250490256-The_composition_rule.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771250491492-Four_is_the_number_o.timestamps.json"]	["/audio/1771250484295-One.mp3", "/audio/1771250484942-Two.mp3", "/audio/1771250485440-Three.mp3", "/audio/1771250485967-Four.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1771250484295-One.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771250484942-Two.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771250485440-Three.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771250485967-Four.timestamps.json"]	/audio/1771250483791-What_number_of_FREC_.mp3	/timestamps/1771250483791-What_number_of_FREC_.timestamps.json
cmlp857qb00ejr4ev61uenyps	cmlo3p21500b9r4evvq0cbmdp	A sales associate is employed by an owner-developer who owns multiple properties under different entity names. If these entities are connected and controlled by that same owner-developer, what type of license must the associate obtain to sell for all of them?	{"Multiple license ","Group license ","Branch office license","General agent license"}	1	{"correct": "A Group license is specifically issued to sales associates or broker associates who are employed by an owner-developer. It allows the licensee to sell property for all the various affiliated entities owned by that developer, considering them as one employer.", "incorrect": ["A \\"Multiple license\\" is issued only to brokers (not sales associates) who are the broker of record for two or more separate brokerage entities.", "", "A branch office license is a registration for a physical office location, not a type of license held by an individual sales associate.", "General agent refers to a scope of authority (like a property manager), not a specific license category issued by the DBPR for this situation."]}	40	chapter	2026-02-16 13:42:53.795	2026-02-16 14:02:08.548	\N	\N	\N	\N	/audio/1771250524497-A_Group_license_is_s.mp3	/timestamps/1771250524497-A_Group_license_is_s.timestamps.json	["/audio/1771250525781-A__Multiple_license_.mp3", "", "/audio/1771250527095-A_branch_office_lice.mp3", "/audio/1771250528338-General_agent_refers.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1771250525781-A__Multiple_license_.timestamps.json", "", "/timestamps/1771250527095-A_branch_office_lice.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771250528338-General_agent_refers.timestamps.json"]	["/audio/1771250520476-Multiple_license.mp3", "/audio/1771250521039-Group_license.mp3", "/audio/1771250521621-Branch_office_licens.mp3", "/audio/1771250522354-General_agent_licens.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1771250520476-Multiple_license.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771250521039-Group_license.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771250521621-B