cmlp8f7bf00elr4ev0txi45i9	cmlo3p21500b9r4evvq0cbmdp	A broker who qualifies as the broker of record for more than one brokerage entity is said to hold which type of license?	{"Group license","Multiple licenses ","Branch office license","Universal license"}	1	{"correct": "A Multiple License is issued to a broker who qualifies as the broker for more than one business entity. The broker must hold a separate license for each brokerage company they manage.", "incorrect": ["A Group License is issued to a sales associate or broker associate working for an owner-developer (not a brokerage) with multiple connected entities.", "", "A branch office license registers a physical location, not the status of the individual broker's authority over multiple companies.", "There is no such license category as a \\"Universal license\\" in Florida real estate law."]}	41	chapter	2026-02-16 13:50:39.758	2026-02-16 14:02:17.56	\N	\N	\N	\N	/audio/1771250533673-A_Multiple_License_i.mp3	/timestamps/1771250533673-A_Multiple_License_i.timestamps.json	["/audio/1771250535178-A_Group_License_is_i.mp3", "", "/audio/1771250536473-A_branch_office_lice.mp3", "/audio/1771250537344-There_is_no_such_lic.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1771250535178-A_Group_License_is_i.timestamps.json", "", "/timestamps/1771250536473-A_branch_office_lice.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771250537344-There_is_no_such_lic.timestamps.json"]	["/audio/1771250530276-Group_license.mp3", "/audio/1771250530944-Multiple_licenses.mp3", "/audio/1771250531461-Branch_office_licens.mp3", "/audio/1771250532054-Universal_license.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1771250530276-Group_license.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771250530944-Multiple_licenses.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771250531461-Branch_office_licens.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771250532054-Universal_license.timestamps.json"]	/audio/1771250529779-A_broker_who_qualifi.mp3	/timestamps/1771250529779-A_broker_who_qualifi.timestamps.json
cmlo6lo2400c7r4evckbjms6o	cmlo3p21500b9r4evvq0cbmdp	Who appoints the Secretary of the DBPR?	{"The State Senate, subject to Governor confirmation","The Governor, subject to Senate confirmation","The Florida Real Estate Commission (FREC)","The Attorney General"}	1	{"correct": "The secretary is appointed by the governor, subject to confirmation by the state senate.&nbsp;", "incorrect": ["This option reverses the roles; the Governor appoints, and the Senate confirms.", "", "The FREC does not appoint the Secretary; the Secretary oversees the Department that supports the FREC.", "The Attorney General is a separate elected official and does not make this appointment."]}	1	chapter	2026-02-15 20:11:55.98	2026-02-16 13:56:13.862	\N	\N	\N	\N	/audio/1771250170631-The_secretary_is_app.mp3	/timestamps/1771250170631-The_secretary_is_app.timestamps.json	["/audio/1771250171651-This_option_reverses.mp3", "", "/audio/1771250172800-The_FREC_does_not_ap.mp3", "/audio/1771250173696-The_Attorney_General.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1771250171651-This_option_reverses.timestamps.json", "", "/timestamps/1771250172800-The_FREC_does_not_ap.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771250173696-The_Attorney_General.timestamps.json"]	["/audio/1771250167114-The_State_Senate__su.mp3", "/audio/1771250167998-The_Governor__subjec.mp3", "/audio/1771250168886-The_Florida_Real_Est.mp3", "/audio/1771250169433-The_Attorney_General.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1771250167114-The_State_Senate__su.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771250167998-The_Governor__subjec.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771250168886-The_Florida_Real_Est.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771250169433-The_Attorney_General.timestamps.json"]	/audio/1771250166315-Who_appoints_the_Sec.mp3	/timestamps/1771250166315-Who_appoints_the_Sec.timestamps.json
cmlo69tox00c5r4evcuzn38de	cmlo3p21500b9r4evvq0cbmdp	The Department of Business and Professional Regulation (DBPR) falls under which branch of the state government?	{"The Legislative Branch","The Judicial Branch","The Executive Branch","The Federal Government"}	2	{"correct": "DBPR is under the executive branch of the governor.", "incorrect": ["The legislative branch is responsible for making laws, not enforcing them through agencies like the DBPR.", "The judicial branch interprets laws (courts), whereas the DBPR is an administrative agency.", "", "The DBPR is a state agency of Florida, not a federal entity."]}	0	chapter	2026-02-15 20:02:43.416	2026-02-16 13:56:05.471	\N	\N	\N	\N	/audio/1771250161905-DBPR_is_under_the_ex.mp3	/timestamps/1771250161905-DBPR_is_under_the_ex.timestamps.json	["/audio/1771250163251-The_legislative_bran.mp3", "/audio/1771250164355-The_judicial_branch_.mp3", "", "/audio/1771250165315-The_DBPR_is_a_state_.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1771250163251-The_legislative_bran.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771250164355-The_judicial_branch_.timestamps.json", "", "/timestamps/1771250165315-The_DBPR_is_a_state_.timestamps.json"]	["/audio/1771250158865-The_Legislative_Bran.mp3", "/audio/1771250159624-The_Judicial_Branch.mp3", "/audio/1771250160254-The_Executive_Branch.mp3", "/audio/1771250160916-The_Federal_Governme.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1771250158865-The_Legislative_Bran.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771250159624-The_Judicial_Branch.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771250160254-The_Executive_Branch.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771250160916-The_Federal_Governme.timestamps.json"]	/audio/1771250158192-The_Department_of_Bu.mp3	/timestamps/1771250158192-The_Department_of_Bu.timestamps.json
cmlo6nyv300c9r4evfr6n652f	cmlo3p21500b9r4evvq0cbmdp	Under Chapter 455, F.S., the DBPR has the authority to issue citations to which group?	{"Unlicensed individuals","Individuals licensed by the DBPR","Homeowners selling their own property","The State Senate"}	1	{"correct": "DBPR may issue citations to individuals licensed by the DBPR.", "incorrect": ["DBPR issues cease and desist orders (not citations) to unlicensed individuals.", "", "Homeowners selling their own property are generally exempt and not subject to citations unless acting as unlicensed brokers.", "The DBPR has no regulatory authority over the State Senate."]}	2	chapter	2026-02-15 20:13:43.359	2026-02-16 13:56:22.443	\N	\N	\N	\N	/audio/1771250178817-DBPR_may_issue_citat.mp3	/timestamps/1771250178817-DBPR_may_issue_citat.timestamps.json	["/audio/1771250180139-DBPR_issues_cease_an.mp3", "", "/audio/1771250181392-Homeowners_selling_t.mp3", "/audio/1771250182288-The_DBPR_has_no_regu.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1771250180139-DBPR_issues_cease_an.timestamps.json", "", "/timestamps/1771250181392-Homeowners_selling_t.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771250182288-The_DBPR_has_no_regu.timestamps.json"]	["/audio/1771250175804-Unlicensed_individua.mp3", "/audio/1771250176476-Individuals_licensed.mp3", "/audio/1771250177195-Homeowners_selling_t.mp3", "/audio/1771250177711-The_State_Senate.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1771250175804-Unlicensed_individua.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771250176476-Individuals_licensed.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771250177195-Homeowners_selling_t.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771250177711-The_State_Senate.timestamps.json"]	/audio/1771250175181-Under_Chapter_455__F.mp3	/timestamps/1771250175181-Under_Chapter_455__F.timestamps.json
cmkzoeznh0015d90dbm9em83w	cmjrjorwn0003b3n6srvqqp17	A licensee does a Comparative Market Analysis (CMA) for a fee. What statement is true?	{"The licensee must have real estate and appraiser's license to charge for CMA","The licensee can charge for CMA only if they comply with USPAP (Uniform Standards of Professional Appraisal Practice)","Licensee may charge for CMA, as long as they don't present it as an appraisal","Only licensed appraisers can charge for CMAs"}	2	{"correct": "Real estate licensees are legally permitted to prepare and charge a fee for a Comparative Market Analysis (CMA), provided that the report is not represented or referred to as an appraisal.", "incorrect": ["A licensee does not need an appraiser's license to charge for a CMA; their real estate license is sufficient for this specific valuation service.", "CMAs are specifically exempt from USPAP standards. USPAP applies to formal appraisals, not to CMAs or Broker Price Opinions (BPOs) prepared by licensees in the ordinary course of business (unless the licensee mistakenly calls it an appraisal).", "", "Real estate licensees (brokers and sales associates) are permitted to charge for CMAs; the ability to charge for valuation services is not restricted solely to licensed appraisers, provided the service is not a formal appraisal for a federally related transaction."]}	17	chapter	2026-01-29 16:36:23.165	2026-02-19 17:01:43.766	\N	\N	\N	\N	/audio/1769704559716-Real_estate_licensee.mp3	/timestamps/1769704559716-Real_estate_licensee.timestamps.json	["/audio/1769704561142-A_licensee_does_not_.mp3", "/audio/1769704563328-CMAs_are_specificall.mp3", "", "/audio/1769704565642-Real_estate_licensee.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1769704561142-A_licensee_does_not_.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1769704563328-CMAs_are_specificall.timestamps.json", "", "/timestamps/1769704565642-Real_estate_licensee.timestamps.json"]	["/audio/1769704554430-The_licensee_must_ha.mp3", "/audio/1769704555780-The_licensee_can_cha.mp3", "/audio/1769704556691-Licensee_may_charge_.mp3", "/audio/1769704557872-Only_licensed_apprai.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1769704554430-The_licensee_must_ha.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1769704555780-The_licensee_can_cha.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1769704556691-Licensee_may_charge_.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1769704557872-Only_licensed_apprai.timestamps.json"]	/audio/1769704552874-A_licensee_does_a_Co.mp3	/timestamps/1769704552874-A_licensee_does_a_Co.timestamps.json
cmlo6pyv600cbr4evxxkxqnw5	cmlo3p21500b9r4evvq0cbmdp	What is the composition of the Florida Real Estate Commission (FREC)?	{"Five professional members and zero consumer members","Four professional members and three consumer members","Five professional members and two consumer members","Seven professional members"}	2	{"correct": "The Commission consists of five professional members and two consumer members.", "incorrect": ["This ignores the requirement for two consumer members.", "This lists the wrong ratio (4:3 instead of 5:2).", "", "This ignores the requirement for consumer members entirely."]}	3	chapter	2026-02-15 20:15:16.674	2026-02-16 13:56:30.446	\N	\N	\N	\N	/audio/1771250187762-The_Commission_consi.mp3	/timestamps/1771250187762-The_Commission_consi.timestamps.json	["/audio/1771250188585-This_ignores_the_req.mp3", "/audio/1771250189491-This_lists_the_wrong.mp3", "", "/audio/1771250190289-This_ignores_the_req.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1771250188585-This_ignores_the_req.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771250189491-This_lists_the_wrong.timestamps.json", "", "/timestamps/1771250190289-This_ignores_the_req.timestamps.json"]	["/audio/1771250184321-Five_professional_me.mp3", "/audio/1771250185220-Four_professional_me.mp3", "/audio/1771250186003-Five_professional_me.mp3", "/audio/1771250186656-Seven_professional_m.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1771250184321-Five_professional_me.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771250185220-Four_professional_me.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771250186003-Five_professional_me.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771250186656-Seven_professional_m.timestamps.json"]	/audio/1771250183524-What_is_the_composit.mp3	/timestamps/1771250183524-What_is_the_composit.timestamps.json
cmkznr6k6000vd90dx9diggxd	cmjrjorwn0003b3n6srvqqp17	The term "Follow-Up" refers to:	{"Following up with owners of expired listings ","Following up with your broker's clients ","Following up with clients and customers after a closed transaction ","Following up quickly with clients"}	2	{"correct": "In real estate sales, Follow-Up is specifically defined as what a sales associate does after the transaction is closed (post-closing). It involves staying in touch to ensure satisfaction, secure referrals, and maintain the relationship for future business.", "incorrect": ["Contacting owners of expired listings is considered Prospecting or lead generation, not follow-up.", "This describes a specific task, not the general business definition of the term \\"follow-up.\\"", "", "Responding quickly is a measure of responsiveness or communication speed, whereas \\"follow-up\\" is the long-term strategy of post-closing contact."]}	12	chapter	2026-01-29 16:17:52.374	2026-02-19 17:02:23.656	\N	\N	\N	\N	/audio/1769703464900-In_real_estate_sales.mp3	/timestamps/1769703464900-In_real_estate_sales.timestamps.json	["/audio/1769703466190-Contacting_owners_of.mp3", "/audio/1769703467306-This_describes_a_spe.mp3", "", "/audio/1769703468735-Responding_quickly_i.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1769703466190-Contacting_owners_of.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1769703467306-This_describes_a_spe.timestamps.json", "", "/timestamps/1769703468735-Responding_quickly_i.timestamps.json"]	["/audio/1769703459817-Following_up_with_ow.mp3", "/audio/1769703460533-Following_up_with_yo.mp3", "/audio/1769703461903-Following_up_with_cl.mp3", "/audio/1769703462652-Following_up_quickly.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1769703459817-Following_up_with_ow.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1769703460533-Following_up_with_yo.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1769703461903-Following_up_with_cl.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1769703462652-Following_up_quickly.timestamps.json"]	/audio/1769703458630-The_term__Follow_Up_.mp3	/timestamps/1769703458630-The_term__Follow_Up_.timestamps.json
cmlo6s8t400cdr4evr302asjy	cmlo3p21500b9r4evvq0cbmdp	Regarding the professional members of the FREC, four of them must have held active broker licenses for how long preceding their appointment?	{"Two years","Five years","Ten years","One year"}	1	{"correct": "Four of the professional members must have held active broker licenses during the five years preceding appointment.", "incorrect": ["Two years is the requirement for the fifth professional member.", "", "Ten years is not a requirement.", "One year is insufficient experience."]}	4	chapter	2026-02-15 20:17:02.872	2026-02-16 13:56:38.104	\N	\N	\N	\N	/audio/1771250195557-Four_of_the_professi.mp3	/timestamps/1771250195557-Four_of_the_professi.timestamps.json	["/audio/1771250196498-Two_years_is_the_req.mp3", "", "/audio/1771250197154-Ten_years_is_not_a_r.mp3", "/audio/1771250197842-One_year_is_insuffic.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1771250196498-Two_years_is_the_req.timestamps.json", "", "/timestamps/1771250197154-Ten_years_is_not_a_r.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771250197842-One_year_is_insuffic.timestamps.json"]	["/audio/1771250192406-Two_years.mp3", "/audio/1771250193057-Five_years.mp3", "/audio/1771250193698-Ten_years.mp3", "/audio/1771250194259-One_year.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1771250192406-Two_years.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771250193057-Five_years.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771250193698-Ten_years.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771250194259-One_year.timestamps.json"]	/audio/1771250191925-Regarding_the_profes.mp3	/timestamps/1771250191925-Regarding_the_profes.timestamps.json
cmkznf80x000pd90dbugbbhl3	cmjrjorwn0003b3n6srvqqp17	A CAM license is required for:	{"Managing a 4 family home ","Managing a building with 5 units ","Managing a building with 8 units ","Managing a building with 10 units"}	3	{"correct": "While the strict legal requirement is more than 10 units (or a budget over $100,000), this option represents the statutory threshold. Managing a community association of fewer than 10 units typically does not require a license, making this the only option that addresses the legal cutoff point where licensing requirements begin to apply.", "incorrect": ["Managing a 4-family home (4 units) falls well below the statutory threshold of more than 10 units required for a CAM license.", "Managing a 5-unit building falls well below the statutory threshold of more than 10 units required for a CAM license.", "Managing an 8-unit building falls well below the statutory threshold of more than 10 units required for a CAM license.", ""]}	9	chapter	2026-01-29 16:08:34.327	2026-02-19 17:02:35.969	\N	\N	\N	\N	/audio/1769702906138-While_the_strict_leg.mp3	/timestamps/1769702906138-While_the_strict_leg.timestamps.json	["/audio/1769702907427-Managing_a_4_family_.mp3", "/audio/1769702908866-Managing_a_5_unit_bu.mp3", "/audio/1769702910015-Managing_an_8_unit_b.mp3", ""]	["/timestamps/1769702907427-Managing_a_4_family_.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1769702908866-Managing_a_5_unit_bu.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1769702910015-Managing_an_8_unit_b.timestamps.json", ""]	["/audio/1769702901840-Managing_a_4_family_.mp3", "/audio/1769702902504-Managing_a_building_.mp3", "/audio/1769702903181-Managing_a_building_.mp3", "/audio/1769702903756-Managing_a_building_.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1769702901840-Managing_a_4_family_.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1769702902504-Managing_a_building_.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1769702903181-Managing_a_building_.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1769702903756-Managing_a_building_.timestamps.json"]	/audio/1769702901122-A_CAM_license_i