cmlo7llmq00clr4ev9qadmczy	cmlo3p21500b9r4evvq0cbmdp	Which action is an example of the FREC's quasi-judicial powers?	{"Adopting a new rule","Disciplining a licensee","Issuing a specialized license","Conducting an investigation"}	1	{"correct": "FREC exercises quasi-judicial powers when it hears complaints and disciplines licensees.", "incorrect": ["Adopting rules is a quasi-legislative power.", "", "Issuing licenses is an administrative/executive function.", "Conducting investigations is a DBPR power, not a FREC judicial power."]}	8	chapter	2026-02-15 20:39:52.445	2026-02-16 13:57:10.664	\N	\N	\N	\N	/audio/1771250227694-FREC_exercises_quasi.mp3	/timestamps/1771250227694-FREC_exercises_quasi.timestamps.json	["/audio/1771250228601-Adopting_rules_is_a_.mp3", "", "/audio/1771250229436-Issuing_licenses_is_.mp3", "/audio/1771250230490-Conducting_investiga.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1771250228601-Adopting_rules_is_a_.timestamps.json", "", "/timestamps/1771250229436-Issuing_licenses_is_.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771250230490-Conducting_investiga.timestamps.json"]	["/audio/1771250224637-Adopting_a_new_rule.mp3", "/audio/1771250225258-Disciplining_a_licen.mp3", "/audio/1771250225817-Issuing_a_specialize.mp3", "/audio/1771250226461-Conducting_an_invest.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1771250224637-Adopting_a_new_rule.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771250225258-Disciplining_a_licen.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771250225817-Issuing_a_specialize.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771250226461-Conducting_an_invest.timestamps.json"]	/audio/1771250223961-Which_action_is_an_e.mp3	/timestamps/1771250223961-Which_action_is_an_e.timestamps.json
cmkzn2w2h000nd90d4mmg2mif	cmjrjorwn0003b3n6srvqqp17	Which is NOT one of the five major sales specialties?	{"Special use ","Agricultural ","Businesses ",Commercial}	0	{"correct": "&nbsp;The five major sales specialties in real estate are Residential, Commercial, Industrial, Agricultural, and Businesses. \\"Special use\\" (such as churches or schools) is a category of property type, but it is not classified as one of the five major sales specialties for licensees.", "incorrect": ["", "Agricultural is one of the five recognized major sales specialties.", "Business brokerage is one of the five recognized major sales specialties.", "Commercial real estate is one of the five recognized major sales specialties."]}	8	chapter	2026-01-29 15:58:59.033	2026-02-19 17:02:45.713	\N	\N	\N	\N	/audio/1769702331628-The_five_major_sales.mp3	/timestamps/1769702331628-The_five_major_sales.timestamps.json	["", "/audio/1769702332846-Agricultural_is_one_.mp3", "/audio/1769702333839-Business_brokerage_i.mp3", "/audio/1769702334787-Commercial_real_esta.mp3"]	["", "/timestamps/1769702332846-Agricultural_is_one_.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1769702333839-Business_brokerage_i.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1769702334787-Commercial_real_esta.timestamps.json"]	["/audio/1769702327077-Special_use.mp3", "/audio/1769702327748-Agricultural.mp3", "/audio/1769702328670-Businesses.mp3", "/audio/1769702329141-Commercial.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1769702327077-Special_use.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1769702327748-Agricultural.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1769702328670-Businesses.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1769702329141-Commercial.timestamps.json"]	/audio/1769702326553-Which_is_NOT_one_of_.mp3	/timestamps/1769702326553-Which_is_NOT_one_of_.timestamps.json
cmlo7nxmk00cnr4evsj18obnr	cmlo3p21500b9r4evvq0cbmdp	What defines 'Voluntary Inactive' status?	{"A licensee who fails to renew on time","A licensee who chooses not to engage in the real estate business and requests the status","A licensee who has been disciplined by the FREC","A licensee working for a developer"}	1	{"correct": "This status is for a licensee who voluntarily chooses not to engage in the real estate business.", "incorrect": ["Failure to renew results in Involuntary Inactive status.", "", "Discipline leads to suspension or revocation, not voluntary status.", "Working for a developer usually requires an active license or group license."]}	9	chapter	2026-02-15 20:41:41.372	2026-02-16 13:57:19.218	\N	\N	\N	\N	/audio/1771250236053-This_status_is_for_a.mp3	/timestamps/1771250236053-This_status_is_for_a.timestamps.json	["/audio/1771250237169-Failure_to_renew_res.mp3", "", "/audio/1771250238005-Discipline_leads_to_.mp3", "/audio/1771250238955-Working_for_a_develo.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1771250237169-Failure_to_renew_res.timestamps.json", "", "/timestamps/1771250238005-Discipline_leads_to_.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771250238955-Working_for_a_develo.timestamps.json"]	["/audio/1771250232280-A_licensee_who_fails.mp3", "/audio/1771250233373-A_licensee_who_choos.mp3", "/audio/1771250234188-A_licensee_who_has_b.mp3", "/audio/1771250234943-A_licensee_working_f.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1771250232280-A_licensee_who_fails.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771250233373-A_licensee_who_choos.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771250234188-A_licensee_who_has_b.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771250234943-A_licensee_working_f.timestamps.json"]	/audio/1771250231561-What_defines__Volunt.mp3	/timestamps/1771250231561-What_defines__Volunt.timestamps.json
cmkzmsq6i000hd90d9cuu8kqs	cmjrjorwn0003b3n6srvqqp17	Which statement is TRUE about the term REALTOR?<div><br></div>	{"Only real estate Brokers can call themselves a REALTOR","Only a member of NAR can call themselves a REALTOR","You have to be approved by Florida Real Estate Commission to call yourself a REALTOR","Anyone who has a real estate license is a REALTOR"}	1	{"correct": "The term REALTOR is a registered trademark of the National Association of REALTORS (NAR). Only licensees who are active members of this specific trade organization are permitted to use the title.<div><br></div>", "incorrect": ["Sales associates and broker-associates can also be REALTORS if they join the association. The title is not restricted to brokers only.", "", "The Florida Real Estate Commission (FREC) issues state real estate licenses, but they do not control or approve the REALTOR designation, which is a private trade membership.", "Holding a real estate license makes you a \\"Real Estate Licensee.\\" You only become a REALTOR if you choose to join the NAR; many licensees practice without joining."]}	5	chapter	2026-01-29 15:51:04.842	2026-02-19 17:02:54.803	\N	\N	\N	\N	/audio/1769701845860-The_term_REALTOR_is_.mp3	/timestamps/1769701845860-The_term_REALTOR_is_.timestamps.json	["/audio/1769701847431-Sales_associates_and.mp3", "", "/audio/1769701849090-The_Florida_Real_Est.mp3", "/audio/1769701850484-Holding_a_real_estat.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1769701847431-Sales_associates_and.timestamps.json", "", "/timestamps/1769701849090-The_Florida_Real_Est.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1769701850484-Holding_a_real_estat.timestamps.json"]	["/audio/1769701841040-Only_real_estate_Bro.mp3", "/audio/1769701841889-Only_a_member_of_NAR.mp3", "/audio/1769701842922-You_have_to_be_appro.mp3", "/audio/1769701843902-Anyone_who_has_a_rea.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1769701841040-Only_real_estate_Bro.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1769701841889-Only_a_member_of_NAR.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1769701842922-You_have_to_be_appro.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1769701843902-Anyone_who_has_a_rea.timestamps.json"]	/audio/1769701839625-Which_statement_is_T.mp3	/timestamps/1769701839625-Which_statement_is_T.timestamps.json
cmms3k7xu00if4be70kal5led	cmmry1yz800fh4be796sih9l4	Which statement is TRUE regarding how ad valorem (property) taxes are assessed for condominiums and cooperatives?	{"Ad valorem taxes are assessed against each individual unit for both condominiums and cooperatives.","Ad valorem taxes are assessed against each individual condominium unit, but a cooperative is assessed as a single entire property.","Ad valorem taxes are assessed against each individual cooperative unit, but a condominium building is assessed as a single entire property.","Ad valorem taxes are assessed based strictly on the square footage of the unit, regardless of whether it is a condo or a co-op."}	1	{"correct": "Because a condominium is a legally separate parcel of real estate (fee simple ownership), the property appraiser assesses taxes against each individual condo unit. However, a cooperative is owned entirely by a single corporation. Therefore, the property appraiser issues one single tax bill for the entire cooperative building.", "incorrect": ["This is the trap. Co-op shareholders do not receive individual property tax bills. Instead, they pay their proportional share of the building's total tax bill through their monthly maintenance fees to the corporation.", "", "This has the facts completely reversed.", "Ad valorem means \\"according to value.\\" Taxes are assessed based on the designated market value of the property or corporation, not simply by measuring square footage."]}	24	chapter	2026-03-15 18:37:36.655	2026-03-15 19:06:34.751	\N	\N	\N	\N	/audio/1773601589866-Because_a_condominiu.mp3	/timestamps/1773601589866-Because_a_condominiu.timestamps.json	["/audio/1773601592188-This_is_the_trap__Co.mp3", "", "/audio/1773601592869-This_has_the_facts_c.mp3", "/audio/1773601594584-Ad_valorem_means__ac.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1773601592188-This_is_the_trap__Co.timestamps.json", "", "/timestamps/1773601592869-This_has_the_facts_c.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1773601594584-Ad_valorem_means__ac.timesta