cmlo7qerb00cpr4ev2nc18ckw	cmlo3p21500b9r4evvq0cbmdp	When does 'Involuntary Inactive' status occur?	{"When a licensee requests a break","When a licensee fails to renew an active or voluntary inactive license before the expiration date","When a licensee is deployed by the military","When a licensee moves out of state"}	1	{"correct": "This status occurs \\"when a licensee fails to renew... before the expiration date.\\"", "incorrect": ["Requesting a break is Voluntary Inactive.", "", "Military members are exempt from renewal provisions.", "Moving out of state requires notification but does not automatically trigger inactive status."]}	10	chapter	2026-02-15 20:43:36.886	2026-02-16 13:57:27.239	\N	\N	\N	\N	/audio/1771250244421-This_status_occurs__.mp3	/timestamps/1771250244421-This_status_occurs__.timestamps.json	["/audio/1771250245293-Requesting_a_break_i.mp3", "", "/audio/1771250246053-Military_members_are.mp3", "/audio/1771250247080-Moving_out_of_state_.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1771250245293-Requesting_a_break_i.timestamps.json", "", "/timestamps/1771250246053-Military_members_are.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771250247080-Moving_out_of_state_.timestamps.json"]	["/audio/1771250240738-When_a_licensee_requ.mp3", "/audio/1771250241793-When_a_licensee_fail.mp3", "/audio/1771250242497-When_a_licensee_is_d.mp3", "/audio/1771250243188-When_a_licensee_move.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1771250240738-When_a_licensee_requ.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771250241793-When_a_licensee_fail.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771250242497-When_a_licensee_is_d.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771250243188-When_a_licensee_move.timestamps.json"]	/audio/1771250240058-When_does__Involunta.mp3	/timestamps/1771250240058-When_does__Involunta.timestamps.json
cmlo7sek700crr4ev20dxl6xz	cmlo3p21500b9r4evvq0cbmdp	What happens to a license that remains in Involuntary Inactive status for more than 2 years?	{"It automatically converts to Voluntary Inactive","It becomes Null and Void","The licensee is fined $1,000 per month","It remains Involuntary Inactive until the licensee pays the fees"}	1	{"correct": "It becomes Null and Void. Florida law places a strict 2-year limit on Involuntary Inactive status. If the licensee does not reactivate within that window, the license is canceled (Null and Void) without further notice.", "incorrect": ["You cannot default back to Voluntary status.", "", "There are no monthly fines for expired licenses; you simply lose the license.", "It does not remain until the licensee pays the fees; it expires permanently after 2 years."]}	11	chapter	2026-02-15 20:45:09.943	2026-02-16 13:57:36.674	\N	\N	\N	\N	/audio/1771250253576-It_becomes_Null_and_.mp3	/timestamps/1771250253576-It_becomes_Null_and_.timestamps.json	["/audio/1771250254461-You_cannot_default_b.mp3", "", "/audio/1771250255440-There_are_no_monthly.mp3", "/audio/1771250256480-It_does_not_remain_u.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1771250254461-You_cannot_default_b.timestamps.json", "", "/timestamps/1771250255440-There_are_no_monthly.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771250256480-It_does_not_remain_u.timestamps.json"]	["/audio/1771250249311-It_automatically_con.mp3", "/audio/1771250249975-It_becomes_Null_and_.mp3", "/audio/1771250250765-The_licensee_is_fine.mp3", "/audio/1771250251533-It_remains_Involunta.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1771250249311-It_automatically_con.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771250249975-It_becomes_Null_and_.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771250250765-The_licensee_is_fine.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771250251533-It_remains_Involunta.timestamps.json"]	/audio/1771250248434-What_happens_to_a_li.mp3	/timestamps/1771250248434-What_happens_to_a_li.timestamps.json
cmkzo110k0011d90d336rjn3s	cmjrjorwn0003b3n6srvqqp17	A buyer hires an architect to design a house and then enters into a contract with a builder to construct the home on the buyer's lot. This is an example of:	{"Speculative building ","Tract building ","Custom building ","Industrial building"}	2	{"correct": "Custom building occurs when a builder constructs a home under contract with a buyer, often using plans provided by the buyer or an architect.", "incorrect": ["Speculative building is done without a buyer in place.", "Tract building involves choosing from a builder's pre-set floor plans and model homes, not unique architect plans.", "", "Industrial building refers to factories or warehouses, not residential homes."]}	15	chapter	2026-01-29 16:25:31.748	2026-02-19 17:40:00.238	\N	\N	\N	\N	/audio/1769703922782-Custom_building_occu.mp3	/timestamps/1769703922782-Custom_building_occu.timestamps.json	["/audio/1769703923631-Speculative_building.mp3", "/audio/1769703924858-Tract_building_invol.mp3", "", "/audio/1769703925952-Industrial_building_.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1769703923631-Speculative_building.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1769703924858-Tract_building_invol.timestamps.json", "", "/timestamps/1769703925952-Industrial_building_.timestamps.json"]	["/audio/1769703919248-Speculative_building.mp3", "/audio/1769703919869-Tract_building.mp3", "/audio/1769703920808-Custom_building.mp3", "/audio/1769703921364-Industrial_building.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1769703919248-Speculative_building.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1769703919869-Tract_building.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1769703920808-Custom_building.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1769703921364-Industrial_building.timestamps.json"]	/audio/1771522794081-A_buyer_hires_an_arc.mp3	/timestamps/1771522794081-A_buyer_hires_an_arc.timestamps.json
cmltowcyn00ngr4ev6cgmt4o8	cmlslqsgt00l1r4evfhnwe7be	Which of the following best describes the physical requirements for a broker’s principal office?	{"It must be an enclosed room in a stationary building that provides privacy for negotiations","It can be a motor home as long as it is parked in a commercial zone","It may be a virtual office as long as the broker has a P.O. Box","It must be located in a commercial office, not a residence"}	0	{"correct": "The DBPR requires the office to be an enclosed room in a stationary building where negotiations can be conducted with privacy.<div><br></div>", "incorrect": ["", "Mobile homes or RVs are not considered stationary buildings and cannot be registered as an office.", "Virtual offices without a physical enclosed room for privacy do not meet the requirement.", "Offices can be in a residence if zoning permits, provided the sign and privacy rules are met."]}	0	chapter	2026-02-19 16:42:58.846	2026-02-19 19:55:54.798	\N	\N	\N	\N	/audio/1771530950960-The_DBPR_requires_th.mp3	/timestamps/1771530950960-The_DBPR_requires_th.timestamps.json	["", "/audio/1771530952340-Mobile_homes_or_RVs_.mp3", "/audio/1771530953499-Virtual_offices_with.mp3", "/audio/1771530954470-Offices_can_be_in_a_.mp3"]	["", "/timestamps/1771530952340-Mobile_homes_or_RVs_.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771530953499-Virtual_offices_with.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771530954470-Offices_can_be_in_a_.timestamps.json"]	["/audio/1771530946925-It_must_be_an_enclos.mp3", "/audio/1771530947776-It_can_be_a_motor_ho.mp3", "/audio/1771530948681-It_may_be_a_virtual_.mp3", "/audio/1771530949502-It_must_be_located_i.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1771530946925-It_must_be_an_enclos.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771530947776-It_can_be_a_motor_ho.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771530948681-It_may_be_a_virtual_.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771530949502-It_must_be_located_i.timestamps.json"]	/audio/1771530945809-Which_of_the_followi.mp3	/timestamps/1771530945809-Which_of_the_followi.timestamps.json
cmlo7x3g700cvr4evr2ej6eqx	cmlo3p21500b9r4evvq0cbmdp	If a licensee voluntarily relinquished their license, what action does the FREC take?	{"Suspends the license","Cancels the license, making it Null and Void","Places the license in Voluntary Inactive status","Fines the licensee"}	1	{"correct": "Voluntarily relinquished license is \\"canceled by the FREC... Once canceled, the license is null and void.”", "incorrect": ["Suspension is a disciplinary action.", "", "Relinquishing means giving it up entirely, not holding it in inactive status.", "There is no fine for voluntarily surrendering a license."]}	13	chapter	2026-02-15 20:48:48.823	2026-02-16 13:57:52.959	\N	\N	\N	\N	/audio/1771250269860-Voluntarily_relinqui.mp3	/timestamps/1771250269860-Voluntarily_relinqui.timestamps.json	["/audio/1771250270805-Suspension_is_a_disc.mp3", "", "/audio/1771250272004-Relinquishing_means_.mp3", "/audio/1771250272725-There_is_no_fine_for.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1771250270805-Suspension_is_a_disc.timestamps.json", "", "/timestamps/1771250272004-Relinquishing_means_.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771250272725-There_is_no_fine_for.timestamps.json"]	["/audio/1771250266470-Suspends_the_license.mp3", "/audio/1771250267133-Cancels_the_license_.mp3", "/audio/1771250267928-Places_the_license_i.mp3", "/audio/1771250268517-Fines_the_licensee.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1771250266470-Suspends_the_license.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771250267133-Cancels_the_license_.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771250267928-Places_the_license_i.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771250268517-Fines_the_licensee.timestamps.json"]	/audio/1771250265626-If_a_licensee_volunt.mp3	/timestamps/1771250265626-If_a_licensee_volunt.timestamps.json
cmms3vas400ir4be7kaw8zqpf	cmmry1yz800fh4be796sih9l4	essica owns a Florida constitutional homestead property in her name alone. She is married to John, and they have one child together. If Jessica were to pass away, what is the default legal outcome for the ownership of the homestead?	{"John automatically receives fee simple absolute ownership of the entire property","John receives a life estate in the property, and their child receives a vested remainder estate","The property is sold, and the proceeds are split equally between John and the child","John and the child automatically become joint tenants with the right of survivorship"}	1	{"correct": "Under Florida law, if a homestead property is titled in only one spouse's name, and that spouse dies leaving behind a surviving spouse and lineal descendants (children), the law protects the family by granting the surviving spouse a life estate. The descendants automatically receive a vested remainder estate, meaning they will inherit the property in fee simple upon the surviving spouse's death.", "incorrect": ["John would only inherit the property in fee simple absolute if Jessica passed away with absolutely no living lineal descendants. Because they have a child, the ownership must be split into a life estate and a remainder.", "", "The purpose of Florida's constitutional homestead law is to keep the family home intact and protect the surviving spouse from being forced out, not to immediately liquidate the asset.", "Joint tenancy is a concurrent estate where people own the property at the exact same time. In this scenario, the ownership is sequential—John has current possession (life estate), and the child has a future interest (remainder)."]}	30	chapter	2026-03-15 18:46:13.587	2026-03-15 19:08:05.957	\N	\N	\N	\N	/audio/1773601679516-Under_Florida_law__i.mp3	/timestamps/1773601679516-Under_Florida_law__i.timestamps.json	["/audio/1773601681948-John_would_only_inhe.mp3", "", "/audio/1773601683715-The_purpose_of_Flori.mp3", "/audio/1773601685807-Joint_tenancy_is_a_c.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1773601681948-John_would_only_inhe.timestamps.json", "", "/timestamps/1773601683715-The_purpose_of_Flori.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1773601685807-Joint_tenancy_is_a_c.timestamps.json"]	["/audio/1773601673276-John_automatically_r.mp3", "/audio/1773601674386-John_receives_a_life.mp3", "/audio/1773601675358-The_property_is_sold.mp3", "/audio/1773601676413-John_and_the_child_a.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1773601673276-John_automatically_r.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1773601674386-John_receives_a_life.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1773601675358-The_property_is_sold.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1773601676413-John_and_the_child_a.timestamps.json"]	/audio/1773601672195-essica_owns_a_Florid.mp3	/timestamps/1773601672195-essica_owns_a_Florid.timestamps.json
cmlo851nm00cxr4evck21lx4j	cmlo3p21500b9r4evvq0cbmdp	For how long is a U.S. armed forces member exempt from license renewal after discharge from active duty?	{"Six months","One year","Two years","Five years"}	2	{"correct": "The exemption is valid during active duty and for two years after discharge from active duty.", "incorrect": ["Six months is incorrect based on this specific text.", "One year is incorrect.&nbsp;", "", "Five years is longer than the exemption granted"]}	14	chapter	2026-02-15 20:54:59.683	2026-02-16 13:58:00.303	\N	\N	\N	\N	/audio/1771250277616-The_exemption_is_val.mp3	/timestamps/1771250277616-The_exemption_is_val.timestamps.json	["/audio/1771250278747-Six_months_is_incorr.mp3", "/audio/1771250279368-One_year_is_incorrec.mp3", "", "/audio/1771250280152-Five_years_is_longer.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1771250278747-Six_months_is_incorr.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771250279368-One_year_is_incorrec.timestamps.json", "", "/timestamps/1771250280152-Five_years_is_longer.timestamps.json"]	["/audio/1771250274774-Six_months.mp3", "/audio/1771250275356-One_year.mp3", "/audio/1771250275848-Two_years.mp3", "/audio/1771250276376-Five_years.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1771250274774-Six_months.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771250275356-One_year.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771250275848-Two_years.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771250276376-Five_years.timestamps.json"]	/audio/1771250274161-For_how_long_is_a_U_.mp3	/timestamps/1771250274161-For_how_long_is_a_U_.timestamps.json
cmms3xf1f00it4be7ujml99cl	cmmry1yz800fh4be796sih9l4	Which of the following statements accurately describes the defining features of an estate by the entireties?	{"It is exclusively for legally married couples and includes the automatic right of survivorship","It allows each co-owner to leave their specific percentage of the property to their heirs in a will","It can be created by any two individuals, regardless of marital status, as long as they take title at the exact same time","It requires the property to go through the probate process before the surviving owner can claim full title"}	0	{"correct": "An estate by the entireties (or tenancy by the entirety) is a special form of joint ownership recognized in Florida that is strictly reserved for married couples. Its most important feature is the right of survivorship—meaning if one spouse passes away, the surviving spouse automatically absorbs their interest and becomes the sole owner in fee simple absolute.", "incorrect": ["", "This describes a Tenancy in Common. In an estate by the entireties, the right of survivorship dictates where the property goes, meaning a spouse cannot will their \\"half\\" of the property to a third party.", "This describes a standard Joint Tenancy with Right of Survivorship (JTWROS). While JTWROS also features survivorship, it can be formed by unmarried individuals. An estate by the entireties requires the standard \\"four unities\\" (possession, interest, time, and title) plus a mandatory fifth unity: marriage.", "The primary legal benefit of the right of survivorship is that the property ownership transfers immediately upon death, completely bypassing the probate process."]}	31	chapter	2026-03-15 18:47:52.418	2026-03-15 19:08:22.746	\N	\N	\N	\N	/audio/1773601695666-An_estate_by_the_ent.mp3	/timestamps/1773601695666-An_estate_by_the_ent.timestamps.json	["", "/audio/1773601697300-This_describes_a_Ten.mp3", "/audio/1773601700711-This_describes_a_sta.mp3", "/audio/1773601702579-The_primary_legal_be.mp3"]	["", "/timestamps/1773601697300-This_describes_a_Ten.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1773601700711-This_describes_a_sta.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1773601702579-The_primary_legal_be.timestamps.json"]	["/audio/1773601688362-It_is_exclusively_fo.mp3", "/audio/1773601689469-It_allows_each_co_ow.mp3", "/audio/1773601690962-It_can_be_created_by.mp3", "/audio/1773601692151-It_requires_the_prop.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1773601688362-It_is_exclusively_fo.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1773601689469-It_allows_each_co_ow.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1773601690962-It_can_be_created_by.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1773601692151-It_requires_the_prop.timestamps.json"]	/audio/1773601687301-Which_of_the_followi.mp3	/timestamps/1773601687301-Which_of_the_followi.timestamps.json
