cmms3zdj800iv4be7dfssll5k	cmmry1yz800fh4be796sih9l4	According to Chapter 475, Florida Statutes, the legal definition of "real property" or "real estate" specifically includes which of the following?	{"Any interest or estate in land, business enterprises, and business opportunities, including any assignment, leasehold, subleasehold, or mineral rights","Only fee simple estates, life estates, and tangible physical improvements permanently attached to the land","Any interest in land and business enterprises, but strictly excluding temporary leaseholds and mineral rights","Any interest in land, with the exception of business opportunities, which are regulated exclusively under corporate law"}	0	{"correct": "Chapter 475, F.S., provides a very broad definition of real property. Because Florida requires a real estate license to broker the sale of businesses (if real property or leases are involved), the statutory definition intentionally encompasses business enterprises, business opportunities, leaseholds, subleaseholds, and mineral rights alongside traditional land ownership.", "incorrect": ["", "This definition is far too narrow. While it describes freehold estates and fixtures, it completely ignores the business opportunity and leasehold aspects that are heavily regulated by Florida real estate license law.", "Mineral rights and leaseholds are explicitly included in the Chapter 475 definition. Brokering a leasehold estate requires a real estate license.", "Business opportunities are not excluded. In Florida, an individual must hold an active real estate broker or sales associate license to sell or lease a business enterprise or opportunity, even if the sale does not explicitly involve the transfer of a physical building."]}	32	chapter	2026-03-15 18:49:23.78	2026-03-15 19:08:40.652	\N	\N	\N	\N	/audio/1773601714128-Chapter_475__F_S___p.mp3	/timestamps/1773601714128-Chapter_475__F_S___p.timestamps.json	["", "/audio/1773601716440-This_definition_is_f.mp3", "/audio/1773601718