cmlts7hlh00pfr4evsmuxwat5	cmlslqsgt00l1r4evfhnwe7be	Which feature is required in marketing emails under the CAN-SPAM Act?	{"A valid physical postal address","A copy of the broker’s license","The agent’s home phone number","A personalized greeting"}	0	{"correct": "CAN-SPAM requires a physical address and an opt-out (unsubscribe) mechanism.", "incorrect": ["", "A copy of the license is not required in emails.", "Home phone numbers are not required.", "Greetings are a style choice, not a legal requirement."]}	11	chapter	2026-02-19 18:15:36.917	2026-02-19 19:57:41.145	\N	\N	\N	\N	/audio/1771531058567-CAN_SPAM_requires_a_.mp3	/timestamps/1771531058567-CAN_SPAM_requires_a_.timestamps.json	["", "/audio/1771531059474-A_copy_of_the_licens.mp3", "/audio/1771531060147-Home_phone_numbers_a.mp3", "/audio/1771531060979-Greetings_are_a_styl.mp3"]	["", "/timestamps/1771531059474-A_copy_of_the_licens.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771531060147-Home_phone_numbers_a.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771531060979-Greetings_are_a_styl.timestamps.json"]	["/audio/1771531055434-A_valid_physical_pos.mp3", "/audio/1771531056034-A_copy_of_the_broker.mp3", "/audio/1771531056669-The_agent_s_home_pho.mp3", "/audio/1771531057303-A_personalized_greet.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1771531055434-A_valid_physical_pos.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771531056034-A_copy_of_the_broker.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771531056669-The_agent_s_home_pho.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771531057303-A_personalized_greet.timestamps.json"]	/audio/1771531054818-Which_feature_is_req.mp3	/timestamps/1771531054818-Which_feature_is_req.timestamps.json
cmltr3wjn00ovr4ev7y9hqz12	cmlslqsgt00l1r4evfhnwe7be	A broker decides to close their branch office on Main Street and open a new branch office on First Avenue. What must the broker do regarding the registration?	{"Transfer the existing branch registration to the new address","Register the new location and pay the fee, as branch registrations are not transferable","Notify the DBPR within 10 days; no new fee is required","Nothing, as long as the principal office remains the same"}	1	{"correct": "Branch office registrations are not transferable. The old registration must be closed, and a new one opened with a new fee.", "incorrect": ["You cannot \\"move\\" or transfer a branch license to a new location.", "", "A new registration and fee are strictly required.", "Every physical business location must be registered."]}	1	chapter	2026-02-19 17:44:50.05	2026-02-19 19:56:04.794	\N	\N	\N	\N	/audio/1771530961453-Branch_office_regist.mp3	/timestamps/1771530961453-Branch_office_regist.timestamps.json	["/audio/1771530962447-You_cannot__move__or.mp3", "", "/audio/1771530963804-A_new_registration_a.mp3", "/audio/1771530964590-Every_physical_busin.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1771530962447-You_cannot__move__or.timestamps.json", "", "/timestamps/1771530963804-A_new_registration_a.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771530964590-Every_physical_busin.timestamps.json"]	["/audio/1771530957248-Transfer_the_existin.mp3", "/audio/1771530958316-Register_the_new_loc.mp3", "/audio/1771530959357-Notify_the_DBPR_with.mp3", "/audio/1771530960104-Nothing__as_long_as_.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1771530957248-Transfer_the_existin.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771530958316-Register_the_new_loc.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771530959357-Notify_the_DBPR_with.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771530960104-Nothing__as_long_as_.timestamps.json"]	/audio/1771530956401-A_broker_decides_to_.mp3	/timestamps/1771530956401-A_broker_decides_to_.timestamps.json
cmlocqcw000d9r4ev3qm76x6z	cmlo3p21500b9r4evvq0cbmdp	When the Florida Real Estate Commission (FREC) grants or denies a license application, it is exercising which specific power?	{"Executive power ","Quasi-legislative power ","Quasi-judicial power ","Ministerial power"}	2	{"correct": "Quasi-judicial powers involve the exercise of discretion and judgment in applying the law to specific individual cases. This includes granting or denying applications, suspending or revoking licenses, and making determinations of violations.", "incorrect": ["Executive powers relate to the administration and enforcement of the law, such as investigating complaints, fostering education, and adopting a seal.", "Quasi-legislative powers involve the authority to make rules and regulations (like laws) that regulate the profession.", "", "Ministerial powers are routine administrative duties (like record-keeping) that do not require the discretionary judgment used in granting/denying applications."]}	20	chapter	2026-02-15 23:03:32.543	2026-02-16 13:58:53.186	\N	\N	\N	\N	/audio/1771250328837-Quasi_judicial_power.mp3	/timestamps/1771250328837-Quasi_judicial_power.timestamps.json	["/audio/1771250330391-Executive_powers_rel.mp3", "/audio/1771250331600-Quasi_legislative_po.mp3", "", "/audio/1771250333029-Ministerial_powers_a.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1771250330391-Executive_powers_rel.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771250331600-Quasi_legislative_po.timestamps.json", "", "/timestamps/1771250333029-Ministerial_powers_a.timestamps.json"]	["/audio/1771250325108-Executive_power.mp3", "/audio/1771250325697-Quasi_legislative_po.mp3", "/audio/1771250326254-Quasi_judicial_power.mp3", "/audio/1771250326788-Ministerial_power.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1771250325108-Executive_power.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771250325697-Quasi_legislative_po.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771250326254-Quasi_judicial_power.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771250326788-Ministerial_power.timestamps.json"]	/audio/1771250324455-When_the_Florida_Rea.mp3	/timestamps/1771250324455-When_the_Florida_Rea.timestamps.json
cmloct9vs00dbr4evmc80zfge	cmlo3p21500b9r4evvq0cbmdp	Which of the following penalties or actions is NOT a legal authority of the Florida Real Estate Commission (FREC)?	{"Making determinations regarding license law violations","Imposing administrative fines for non-compliance","Imposing imprisonment as a penalty for criminal acts","Adopting an official seal to authenticate commission documents"}	2	{"correct": "The FREC is an administrative agency, not a court of law. It has the power to discipline licensees (revoke, suspend, fine administratively), but it cannot impose imprisonment. Only a criminal court (judiciary) can sentence someone to jail or prison.", "incorrect": ["Making determinations of violations is a key exercise of the FREC's Quasi-Judicial power. They decide if a licensee is guilty or innocent of breaking the rules.", "The FREC has the authority to impose administrative fines (up to $5,000 per violation) as part of its disciplinary process.", "", "Adopting a seal is a specific Executive power granted to the FREC. The seal authenticates their official documents and is prima facie evidence in court."]}	21	chapter	2026-02-15 23:05:48.616	2026-02-16 13:59:05.359	\N	\N	\N	\N	/audio/1771250340634-The_FREC_is_an_admin.mp3	/timestamps/1771250340634-The_FREC_is_an_admin.timestamps.json	["/audio/1771250342259-Making_determination.mp3", "/audio/1771250343877-The_FREC_has_the_aut.mp3", "", "/audio/1771250345172-Adopting_a_seal_is_a.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1771250342259-Making_determination.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771250343877-The_FREC_has_the_aut.timestamps.json", "", "/timestamps/1771250345172-Adopting_a_seal_is_a.timestamps.json"]	["/audio/1771250335273-Making_determination.mp3", "/audio/1771250336176-Imposing_administrat.mp3", "/audio/1771250337081-Imposing_imprisonmen.mp3", "/audio/1771250337958-Adopting_an_official.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1771250335273-Making_determination.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771250336176-Imposing_administrat.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771250337081-Imposing_imprisonmen.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771250337958-Adopting_an_official.timestamps.json"]	/audio/1771250334451-Which_of_the_followi.mp3	/timestamps/1771250334451-Which_of_the_followi.timestamps.json
cmlocv6po00ddr4eva3t5nvfr	cmlo3p21500b9r4evvq0cbmdp	Under Florida Statute 455, which power does the DBPR not have?	{"Investigating consumer complaints ","Issuing subpoenas ","Appointing FREC members ","Issuing citations to unlicensed individuals"}	2	{"correct": "The power to appoint FREC members is not granted to the DBPR. Instead, FREC members are appointed by the Governor, subject to confirmation by the State Senate, as outlined in Chapter 475.", "incorrect": ["Florida Statute 455 specifically grants the DBPR the authority to investigate complaints against licensees.", "The DBPR is granted the power to issue subpoenas and administer oaths when conducting investigations.", "", "The DBPR has the authority to issue citations and cease-and-desist orders to handle unlicensed activity and minor violations."]}	22	chapter	2026-02-15 23:07:17.82	2026-02-16 13:59:15.078	\N	\N	\N	\N	/audio/1771250350902-The_power_to_appoint.mp3	/timestamps/1771250350902-The_power_to_appoint.timestamps.json	["/audio/1771250352313-Florida_Statute_455_.mp3", "/audio/1771250353394-The_DBPR_is_granted_.mp3", "", "/audio/1771250354920-The_DBPR_has_the_aut.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1771250352313-Florida_Statute_455_.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771250353394-The_DBPR_is_granted_.timestamps.json", "", "/timestamps/1771250354920-The_DBPR_has_the_aut.timestamps.json"]	["/audio/1771250347163-Investigating_consum.mp3", "/audio/1771250347825-Issuing_subpoenas.mp3", "/audio/1771250348418-Appointing_FREC_memb.mp3", "/audio/1771250349184-Issuing_citations_to.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1771250347163-Investigating_consum.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771250347825-Issuing_subpoenas.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771250348418-Appointing_FREC_memb.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771250349184-Issuing_citations_to.timestamps.json"]	/audio/1771250346562-Under_Florida_Statut.mp3	/timestamps/1771250346562-Under_Florida_Statut.timestamps.json
cmms49o5y00j14be75bde57ro	cmmry1yz800fh4be796sih9l4	A developer is building a brand-new residential condominium complex. Under the Florida Condominium Act, at what specific unit threshold is the developer legally mandated to provide a prospectus (offering circular) to prospective buyers?	{"For all new condominium projects, regardless of the number of units","Only for condominium projects containing more than 20 units","Only for condominium projects containing 50 or more units","When the project involves timeshare units in addition to standard condominiums"}	1	{"correct": "Florida law requires that developers of residential condominiums with more than 20 units prepare a prospectus (often called an offering circular) and file it with the state. A copy of this detailed document, which summarizes the complex condo governance and financial details, must be given to every buyer before they sign a binding purchase contract.", "incorrect": ["While developers of smaller projects still must provide basic governance documents (like the declaration, articles of incorporation, and bylaws), the extensive, heavily regulated \\"prospectus\\" is not legally required if the project has 20 units or fewer.", "", "50 units is a distractor. The legal threshold that triggers the prospectus requirement is more than 20 units.", "Timeshares have their own strict set of disclosure laws under the Florida Vacation Plan and Timesharing Act (Chapter 721), but the 20+ unit rule for a prospectus applies to standard residential condominiums, regardless of whether timeshares are involved."]}	35	chapter	2026-03-15 18:57:24.06	2026-03-15 19:09:20.394	\N	\N	\N	\N	/audio/1773601753731-Florida_law_requires.mp3	/timestamps/1773601753731-Florida_law_requires.timestamps.json	["/audio/1773601756425-While_developers_of_.mp3", "", "/audio/1773601757815-50_units_is_a_distra.mp3", "/audio/1773601760245-Timeshares_have_thei.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1773601756425-While_developers_of_.timestamps.json", "", "/timestamps/1773601757815-50_units_is_a_distra.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1773601760245-Timeshares_have_thei.timestamps.json"]	["/audio/1773601747449-For_all_new_condomin.mp3", "/audio/1773601748383-Only_for_condominium.mp3", "/audio/1773601749249-Only_for_condominium.mp3", "/audio/1773601750287-When_the_project_inv.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1773601747449-For_all_new_condomin.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1773601748383-Only_for_condominium.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1773601749249-Only_for_condominium.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1773601750287-When_the_project_inv.timestamps.json"]	/audio/1773601746723-A_developer_is_build.mp3	/timestamps/1773601746723-A_developer_is_build.timestamps.json
cmlocz91600dfr4ev9rznwix9	cmlo3p21500b9r4evvq0cbmdp	If a broker notifies the DBPR that a sales associate is no longer associated with the brokerage, what happens to the associate's license status?	{"It becomes null and void","It automatically becomes involuntary inactive","It remains active until the expiration date","It is suspended pending a hearing"}	1	{"correct": "When a broker terminates an associate and notifies the DBPR, the associate ceases to have an employer. Since an active license requires an employing broker, the license status automatically reverts to involuntary inactive until the associate registers with a new broker.", "incorrect": ["Null and void applies to licenses that have expired without renewal (after the 2-year grace period) or failure to complete post-licensing education. It is not used for employment changes.", "", "A sales associate license cannot remain \\"active\\" without a registered employer.", "A suspension is a disciplinary penalty for a violation; losing one's job or changing brokers is not a violation."]}	23	chapter	2026-02-15 23:10:27.45	2026-02-16 13:59:25.938	\N	\N	\N	\N	/audio/1771250361338-When_a_broker_termin.mp3	/timestamps/1771250361338-When_a_broker_termin.timestamps.json	["/audio/1771250362912-Null_and_void_applie.mp3", "", "/audio/1771250364291-A_sales_associate_li.mp3", "/audio/1771250365675-A_suspension_is_a_di.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1771250362912-Null_and_void_applie.timestamps.json", "", "/timestamps/1771250364291-A_sales_associate_li.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771250365675-A_suspension_is_a_di.timestamps.json"]	["/audio/1771250357095-It_becomes_null_and_.mp3", "/audio/1771250357844-It_automatically_bec.mp3", "/audio/1771250358588-It_remains_active_un.mp3", "/audio/1771250359218-It_is_suspended_pend.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1771250357095-It_becomes_null_and_.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771250357844-It_automatically_bec.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771250358588-It_remains_active_un.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771250359218-It_is_suspended_pend.timestamps.json"]	/audio/1771250356532-If_a_broker_notifies.mp3	/timestamps/1771250356532-If_a_broker_notifies.timestamps.json
cmlod7pe400dhr4evs1hl4q2e	cmlo3p21500b9r4evvq0cbmdp	A licensed real estate broker relocates their brokerage to a new office building. Amidst the chaos of the move, they fail to inform the DBPR of the address change within the required 10-day window, what is the status of the licenses of the sales associates working under them until the change is registered?	{Active,"Cease to be in force ","Voluntary Inactive ",Canceled}	1	{"correct": "Cease to be in force. When a broker changes their business address, the license of the brokerage (and effectively the associates attached to that location) ceases to be in force until the DBPR is notified of the new location.", "incorrect": ["They cannot legally operate (Active) until the address is updated.", "", "Voluntary Inactive is a requested status, not a result of an address change.", "The licenses are not canceled; they are just paused until the paperwork is filed."]}	24	chapter	2026-02-15 23:17:01.839	2026-02-16 13:59:35.975	\N	\N	\N	\N	/audio/1771250372589-Cease_to_be_in_force.mp3	/timestamps/1771250372589-Cease_to_be_in_force.timestamps.json	["/audio/1771250373860-They_cannot_legally_.mp3", "", "/audio/1771250374763-Voluntary_Inactive_i.mp3", "/audio/1771250375765-The_licenses_are_not.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1771250373860-They_cannot_legally_.timestamps.json", "", "/timestamps/1771250374763-Voluntary_Inactive_i.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771250375765-The_licenses_are_not.timestamps.json"]	["/audio/1771250368760-Active.mp3", "/audio/1771250369445-Cease_to_be_in_force.mp3", "/audio/1771250370097-Voluntary_Inactive.mp3", "/audio/1771250370596-Canceled.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1771250368760-Active.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771250369445-Cease_to_be_in_force.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771250370097-Voluntary_Inactive.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771250370596-Canceled.timestamps.json"]	/audio/1771250368221-A_licensed_real_esta.mp3	/timestamps/1771250368221-A_licensed_real_esta.timestamps.json
cmlodn5ns00dlr4evn9oozuxw	cmlo3p21500b9r4evvq0cbmdp	Under what specific circumstance may the Florida Real Estate Commission (FREC) reinstate a license that has become null and void?	{"If the licensee pays a double renewal fee and a late penalty","Under no circumstances; a null and void license is permanent. ","If the licensee is found to have been unable to comply with the statute due to physical or economic hardship","If the licensee completes 28 hours of reactivation education"}	2	{"correct": "The Commission has the specific authority to reinstate a null and void license if the licensee can prove that they were unable to comply with the renewal requirements due to physical or economic hardship (e.g., a severe illness or financial crisis).", "incorrect": ["Simply paying extra fees is the remedy for a license that is \\"Involuntary Inactive\\" (within the first 2 years), not for one that has gone \\"Null and Void.\\"", "While a null and void license generally requires the applicant to start over, it is not \\"permanent\\" in this context because the Commission does have the power to reinstate it in cases of proven hardship.", "", "Reactivation education (28 hours) is the requirement for a license that has been Involuntary Inactive for more than 12 months but less than 24 months. It does not apply to a license that has already gone Null and Void."]}	26	chapter	2026-02-15 23:29:02.823	2026-02-16 13:59:57.377	\N	\N	\N	\N	/audio/1771250391802-The_Commission_has_t.mp3	/timestamps/1771250391802-The_Commission_has_t.timestamps.json	["/audio/1771250393483-Simply_paying_extra_.mp3", "/audio/1771250395172-While_a_null_and_voi.mp3", "", "/audio/1771250397122-Reactivation_educati.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1771250393483-Simply_paying_extra_.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771250395172-While_a_null_and_voi.timestamps.json", "", "/timestamps/1771250397122-Reactivation_educati.timestamps.json"]	["/audio/1771250387035-If_the_licensee_pays.mp3", "/audio/1771250387845-Under_no_circumstanc.mp3", "/audio/1771250389004-If_the_licensee_is_f.mp3", "/audio/1771250389888-If_the_licensee_comp.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1771250387035-If_the_licensee_pays.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771250387845-Under_no_circumstanc.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771250389004-If_the_licensee_is_f.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771250389888-If_the_licensee_comp.timestamps.json"]	/audio/1771250386094-Under_what_specific_.mp3	/timestamps/1771250386094-Under_what_specific_.timestamps.json
cmloduvfb00dtr4evj6vmrafe	cmlo3p21500b9r4evvq0cbmdp	Which statement correctly describes the appointment of the Director of the DRE?	{"Appointed by the Governor and confirmed by the Senate. ","Appointed by the FREC and approved by the DBPR. ","Appointed by the Secretary of the DBPR, subject to approval by the FREC. ","Elected by the licensees."}	2	{"correct": "Director is appointed by the Secretary of the DBPR, subject to approval by the FREC.", "incorrect": ["This describes the process for Commission members, not the DRE Director.", "&nbsp;The roles are reversed; the Secretary appoints and the FREC approves, not the other way around.", "", "The Director is an appointed official, not an elected one."]}	30	chapter	2026-02-15 23:35:02.807	2026-02-16 14:00:30.651	\N	\N	\N	\N	/audio/1771250427120-Director_is_appointe.mp3	/timestamps/1771250427120-Director_is_appointe.timestamps.json	["/audio/1771250428237-This_describes_the_p.mp3", "/audio/1771250429283-The_roles_are_revers.mp3", "", "/audio/1771250430465-The_Director_is_an_a.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1771250428237-This_describes_the_p.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771250429283-The_roles_are_revers.timestamps.json", "", "/timestamps/1771250430465-The_Director_is_an_a.timestamps.json"]	["/audio/1771250423384-Appointed_by_the_Gov.mp3", "/audio/1771250424287-Appointed_by_the_FRE.mp3", "/audio/1771250425236-Appointed_by_the_Sec.mp3", "/audio/1771250425834-Elected_by_the_licen.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1771250423384-Appointed_by_the_Gov.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771250424287-Appointed_by_the_FRE.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771250425236-Appointed_by_the_Sec.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771250425834-Elected_by_the_licen.timestamps.json"]	/audio/1771250422654-Which_statement_corr.mp3	/timestamps/1771250422654-Which_statement_corr.timestamps.json
cmlody9u300dvr4evqsjsn20l	cmlo3p21500b9r4evvq0cbmdp	The Florida Real Estate Commission (FREC) consists of a total of how many members?	{"Five members ","Seven members ","Nine members ","Four members"}	1	{"correct": "The Florida Real Estate Commission (FREC) consists of seven members in total.", "incorrect": ["Five is the number of professional (licensed) members, not the total composition of the Commission.", "", "The Commission does not have nine members; the total is fixed at seven.", "Four is the number of members who must specifically be brokers with 5 years of experience, not the total count."]}	31	chapter	2026-02-15 23:37:41.451	2026-02-16 14:00:38.949	\N	\N	\N	\N	/audio/1771250435439-The_Florida_Real_Est.mp3	/timestamps/1771250435439-The_Florida_Real_Est.timestamps.json	["/audio/1771250436629-Five_is_the_number_o.mp3", "", "/audio/1771250437626-The_Commission_does_.mp3", "/audio/1771250438737-Four_is_the_number_o.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1771250436629-Five_is_the_number_o.timestamps.json", "", "/timestamps/1771250437626-The_Commission_does_.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771250438737-Four_is_the_number_o.timestamps.json"]	["/audio/1771250432527-Five_members.mp3", "/audio/1771250433125-Seven_members.mp3", "/audio/1771250433707-Nine_members.mp3", "/audio/1771250434261-Four_members.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1771250432527-Five_members.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771250433125-Seven_members.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771250433707-Nine_members.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771250434261-Four_members.timestamps.json"]	/audio/1771250431826-The_Florida_Real_Est.mp3	/timestamps/1771250431826-The_Florida_Real_Est.timestamps.json
cmlp7c9s600e3r4ev3awyg9ot	cmlo3p21500b9r4evvq0cbmdp	How many members of the FREC are considered "professional" (licensed) members?	{"Two ","Four ","Five ",Seven}	2	{"correct": "Five of the members are professional (licensed) members.", "incorrect": ["Two is the number of consumer (unlicensed) members.", "Four is the specific number of professional members who must be brokers with 5 years of experience, but the total number of professional members is five (adding the one sales associate/broker seat).", "", "Seven is the total number of commissioners, including the consumer members."]}	32	chapter	2026-02-16 13:20:23.367	2026-02-16 14:00:47.037	\N	\N	\N	\N	/audio/1771250443073-Five_of_the_members_.mp3	/timestamps/1771250443073-Five_of_the_members_.timestamps.json	["/audio/1771250444011-Two_is_the_number_of.mp3", "/audio/1771250445795-Four_is_the_specific.mp3", "", "/audio/1771250446824-Seven_is_the_total_n.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1771250444011-Two_is_the_number_of.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771250445795-Four_is_the_specific.timestamps.json", "", "/timestamps/1771250446824-Seven_is_the_total_n.timestamps.json"]	["/audio/1771250440594-Two.mp3", "/audio/1771250441097-Four.mp3", "/audio/1771250441634-Five.mp3", "/audio/1771250442123-Seven.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1771250440594-Two.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771250441097-Four.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771250441634-Five.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771250442123-Seven.timestamps.json"]	/audio/1771250440069-How_many_members_of_.mp3	/timestamps/1771250440069-How_many_members_of_.timestamps.json
cmlp7iwm200e5r4ev8974nr4p	cmlo3p21500b9r4evvq0cbmdp	Regarding the four broker members of the FREC, which requirement must they meet?	{"They must have held active licenses for at least two years preceding appointment. ","They must be at least 60 years of age","They must have held active licenses for at least five years preceding appointment","They must have never been real estate brokers or sales associates"}	2	{"correct": "Four members must be Florida real estate brokers who have held active licenses during the five years preceding appointment.", "incorrect": ["The two-year requirement applies to the one member who can be either a broker or sales associate, not the four broker-only members.", "The age requirement applies to \\"at least one\\" of the seven members generally, not specifically to all four broker members.", "", "This requirement applies to the consumer members, not the broker members."]}	33	chapter	2026-02-16 13:25:32.889	2026-02-16 14:00:56.974	\N	\N	\N	\N	/audio/1771250452995-Four_members_must_be.mp3	/timestamps/1771250452995-Four_members_must_be.timestamps.json	["/audio/1771250454680-The_two_year_require.mp3", "/audio/1771250455905-The_age_requirement_.mp3", "", "/audio/1771250456785-This_requirement_app.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1771250454680-The_two_year_require.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771250455905-The_age_requirement_.timestamps.json", "", "/timestamps/1771250456785-This_requirement_app.timestamps.json"]	["/audio/1771250449054-They_must_have_held_.mp3", "/audio/1771250449787-They_must_be_at_leas.mp3", "/audio/1771250450694-They_must_have_held_.mp3", "/audio/1771250451494-They_must_have_never.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1771250449054-They_must_have_held_.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771250449787-They_must_be_at_leas.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771250450694-They_must_have_held_.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771250451494-They_must_have_never.timestamps.json"]	/audio/1771250448050-Regarding_the_four_b.mp3	/timestamps/1771250448050-Regarding_the_four_b.timestamps.json
cmlp7nfn900e7r4ev4yxojmyj	cmlo3p21500b9r4evvq0cbmdp	One of the professional members of FREC may be a sales associate or broker who has held an active license for how long?	{"One year preceding appointment","Two years preceding appointment","Five years preceding appointment","Ten years preceding appointment"}	1	{"correct": "One member must be either a broker or sales associate who has held an active license during the two years preceding appointment.", "incorrect": ["One year is not the experience threshold.", "", "Five years is the requirement for the four broker-only members.", "Ten years is not the requirement."]}	34	chapter	2026-02-16 13:29:04.245	2026-02-16 14:01:05.165	\N	\N	\N	\N	/audio/1771250462582-One_member_must_be_e.mp3	/timestamps/1771250462582-One_member_must_be_e.timestamps.json	["/audio/1771250463447-One_year_is_not_the_.mp3", "", "/audio/1771250464236-Five_years_is_the_re.mp3", "/audio/1771250464901-Ten_years_is_not_the.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1771250463447-One_year_is_not_the_.timestamps.json", "", "/timestamps/1771250464236-Five_years_is_the_re.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771250464901-Ten_years_is_not_the.timestamps.json"]	["/audio/1771250459052-One_year_preceding_a.mp3", "/audio/1771250459735-Two_years_preceding_.mp3", "/audio/1771250460390-Five_years_preceding.mp3", "/audio/1771250461208-Ten_years_preceding_.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1771250459052-One_year_preceding_a.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771250459735-Two_years_preceding_.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771250460390-Five_years_preceding.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771250461208-Ten_years_preceding_.timestamps.json"]	/audio/1771250458156-One_of_the_professio.mp3	/timestamps/1771250458156-One_of_the_professio.timestamps.json
cmlp7przl00e9r4evko8tbyoc	cmlo3p21500b9r4evvq0cbmdp	Which statement is TRUE regarding the two consumer members of the FREC?	{"They must be active real estate brokers","They must have held a sales associate license for at least two years","They must have never been real estate brokers or sales associates","They must be appointed by the Florida Association of Realtors"}	2	{"correct": "Two consumer members must be unlicensed or lay members who have never been real estate brokers or sales associates.", "incorrect": ["Consumer members cannot be brokers; they must be unlicensed.", "Consumer members cannot have held a license; if they had, they would not qualify as consumer members.<div><br></div>", "", "Consumer members are appointed by the Governor."]}	35	chapter	2026-02-16 13:30:53.553	2026-02-16 14:01:14.045	\N	\N	\N	\N	/audio/1771250470976-Two_consumer_members.mp3	/timestamps/1771250470976-Two_consumer_members.timestamps.json	["/audio/1771250471907-Consumer_members_can.mp3", "/audio/1771250473001-Consumer_members_can.mp3", "", "/audio/1771250473890-Consumer_members_are.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1771250471907-Consumer_members_can.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771250473001-Consumer_members_can.timestamps.json", "", "/timestamps/1771250473890-Consumer_members_are.timestamps.json"]	["/audio/1771250466930-They_must_be_active_.mp3", "/audio/1771250467836-They_must_have_held_.mp3", "/audio/1771250468649-They_must_have_never.mp3", "/audio/1771250469528-They_must_be_appoint.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1771250466930-They_must_be_active_.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771250467836-They_must_have_held_.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771250468649-They_must_have_never.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771250469528-They_must_be_appoint.timestamps.json"]	/audio/1771250466155-Which_statement_is_T.mp3	/timestamps/1771250466155-Which_statement_is_T.timestamps.json
cmlp7shqo00ebr4evy7vy9ffd	cmlo3p21500b9r4evvq0cbmdp	What is the specific age requirement for the Commission composition?	{"All members must be over 50","At least one of the seven members must be 60 years of age or older","The consumer members must be under 40","All broker members must be 60 years of age or older"}	1	{"correct": "At least one of the seven members must be 60 years of age or older.", "incorrect": ["There is no minimum age of 50 for all members.", "", "The text does not place a maximum age limit on consumer members.", "The age requirement applies to the commission as a whole (at least one member), not specifically to all broker members."]}	36	chapter	2026-02-16 13:33:00.24	2026-02-16 14:01:22.715	\N	\N	\N	\N	/audio/1771250479505-At_least_one_of_the_.mp3	/timestamps/1771250479505-At_least_one_of_the_.timestamps.json	["/audio/1771250480482-There_is_no_minimum_.mp3", "", "/audio/1771250481314-The_text_does_not_pl.mp3", "/audio/1771250482560-The_age_requirement_.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1771250480482-There_is_no_minimum_.timestamps.json", "", "/timestamps/1771250481314-The_text_does_not_pl.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771250482560-The_age_requirement_.timestamps.json"]	["/audio/1771250475771-All_members_must_be_.mp3", "/audio/1771250476589-At_least_one_of_the_.mp3", "/audio/1771250477419-The_consumer_members.mp3", "/audio/1771250478406-All_broker_members_m.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1771250475771-All_members_must_be_.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771250476589-At_least_one_of_the_.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771250477419-The_consumer_members.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771250478406-All_broker_members_m.timestamps.json"]	/audio/1771250475068-What_is_the_specific.mp3	/timestamps/1771250475068-What_is_the_specific.timestamps.json
cmmqesy05002g4be7qc1xbulb	cmmqbpz7v00044be7x0za79d7	The Civil Rights Act of 1866 prohibits discrimination in all real estate transactions based on which specific characteristic?	{Religion,Race,"National Origin",Sex}	1	{"correct": "The Civil Rights Act of 1866 prohibits discrimination based on Race only. There are no exceptions to this law.<div><br></div>", "incorrect": ["Religion is protected under the 1968 Fair Housing Act, not the 1866 Act.", "", "National Origin is protected under the 1968 Act.", "Sex was added to the Fair Housing Act in 1974.<br>"]}	0	chapter	2026-03-14 14:16:47.14	2026-03-14 23:11:10.953	\N	\N	\N	\N	/audio/1773529867263-The_Civil_Rights_Act.mp3	/timestamps/1773529867263-The_Civil_Rights_Act.timestamps.json	["/audio/1773529868866-Religion_is_protecte.mp3", "", "/audio/1773529869881-National_Origin_is_p.mp3", "/audio/1773529870798-Sex_was_added_to_the.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1773529868866-Religion_is_protecte.timestamps.json", "", "/timestamps/1773529869881-National_Origin_is_p.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1773529870798-Sex_was_added_to_the.timestamps.json"]	["/audio/1773529864177-Religion.mp3", "/audio/1773529864756-Race.mp3", "/audio/1773529865314-National_Origin.mp3", "/audio/1773529865802-Sex.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1773529864177-Religion.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1773529864756-Race.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1773529865314-National_Origin.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1773529865802-Sex.timestamps.json"]	/audio/1773529863658-The_Civil_Rights_Act.mp3	/timestamps/1773529863658-The_Civil_Rights_Act.timestamps.json
cmlp7xh6n00efr4evu8dwp63f	cmlo3p21500b9r4evvq0cbmdp	What is the status of the license if a licensee fails to renew their third two-year license before the expiration date?	{"The license becomes null and void. ","The license automatically reverts to involuntary inactive status","The license remains active for a 12-month grace period","The license is revoked by the FREC"}	1	{"correct": "For all renewals after the initial post-licensing period (like a third renewal), failure to renew by the deadline causes the license to automatically revert to involuntary inactive status. The licensee has up to 2 years to reactivate it.", "incorrect": ["Null and void applies specifically if a licensee fails to complete the post-licensing education required for the first renewal. Since this is the third license period, that rule does not apply.", "", "There is no \\"active grace period.\\" The license becomes inactive immediately upon expiration.", "Revocation is a permanent disciplinary action taken for severe violations, not for simply forgetting to renew."]}	38	chapter	2026-02-16 13:36:52.798	2026-02-16 14:01:43.058	\N	\N	\N	\N	/audio/1771250498535-For_all_renewals_aft.mp3	/timestamps/1771250498535-For_all_renewals_aft.timestamps.json	["/audio/1771250500501-Null_and_void_applie.mp3", "", "/audio/1771250501506-There_is_no__active_.mp3", "/audio/1771250502848-Revocation_is_a_perm.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1771250500501-Null_and_void_applie.timestamps.json", "", "/timestamps/1771250501506-There_is_no__active_.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771250502848-Revocation_is_a_perm.timestamps.json"]	["/audio/1771250493716-The_license_becomes_.mp3", "/audio/1771250494815-The_license_automati.mp3", "/audio/1771250495716-The_license_remains_.mp3", "/audio/1771250496533-The_license_is_revok.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1771250493716-The_license_becomes_.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771250494815-The_license_automati.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771250495716-The_license_remains_.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771250496533-The_license_is_revok.timestamps.json"]	/audio/1771250493012-What_is_the_status_o.mp3	/timestamps/1771250493012-What_is_the_status_o.timestamps.json
cmlp81ic100ehr4evr8bm5z3h	cmlo3p21500b9r4evvq0cbmdp	A sales associate did not complete the required post-licensing education before the expiration of the initial license. Which statement is TRUE regarding their ability to reactivate the license?	{"The licensee may reactivate the license by completing the 14-hour continuing education course within 6 months. ","The license becomes null and void, and the individual generally cannot reactivate it; they must retake the pre-license course and state exam to practice again","The license automatically reverts to involuntary inactive status and can be reactivated at any time within 2 years","The licensee is granted a one-time 12-month extension to complete the course"}	1	{"correct": "Failure to complete the 45-hour post-licensing requirement before the first expiration date causes the license to become null and void. The statute essentially revokes the license, and the individual is no longer licensed. To practice again, they must start from scratch (take the 63-hour pre-license course and pass the state exam), unless they can prove specific physical or economic hardship to the Commission within 6 months.", "incorrect": ["The 14-hour continuing education course is for subsequent renewal periods, not the initial post-licensing period.", "", "Involuntary Inactive status applies when a licensee fails to renew after they have already completed their initial post-licensing period. It does not apply to the first renewal.", "There is no automatic extension. Extensions are only granted for proven hardship cases applied for prior to expiration."]}	39	chapter	2026-02-16 13:40:00.912	2026-02-16 14:01:58.009	\N	\N	\N	\N	/audio/1771250513162-Failure_to_complete_.mp3	/timestamps/1771250513162-Failure_to_complete_.timestamps.json	["/audio/1771250514810-The_14_hour_continui.mp3", "", "/audio/1771250516447-Involuntary_Inactive.mp3", "/audio/1771250517785-There_is_no_automati.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1771250514810-The_14_hour_continui.timestamps.json", "", "/timestamps/1771250516447-Involuntary_Inactive.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771250517785-There_is_no_automati.timestamps.json"]	["/audio/1771250506058-The_licensee_may_rea.mp3", "/audio/1771250507711-The_license_becomes_.mp3", "/audio/1771250508936-The_license_automati.mp3", "/audio/1771250510081-The_licensee_is_gran.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1771250506058-The_licensee_may_rea.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771250507711-The_license_becomes_.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771250508936-The_license_automati.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771250510081-The_licensee_is_gran.timestamps.json"]	/audio/1771250504922-A_sales_associate_di.mp3	/timestamps/1771250504922-A_sales_associate_di.timestamps.json
cmms4bvtz00j34be780rdcwew	cmmry1yz800fh4be796sih9l4	When a purchaser acquires a condominium, what legal document do they receive as evidence of their ownership?	{"A proprietary lease granting the right to occupy the unit","A deed to the specific, individual unit","Shares of corporate stock proportional to the unit's size","A master title certificate shared with all other building residents"}	1	{"correct": "A condominium is classified as freehold, fee simple ownership of a specific three-dimensional airspace, plus an undivided fractional share of the common elements. Because it is real property, the purchaser receives a traditional deed to their particular unit, just as they would when buying a detached single-family home.", "incorrect": ["This option describes the ownership structure of a cooperative (co-op). In a co-op, the buyer does not actually buy real estate; instead, they purchase shares of stock in the corporation that owns the building and receive a proprietary lease to occupy a specific unit.", "", "This option describes the ownership structure of a cooperative (co-op). In a co-op, the buyer does not actually buy real estate; instead, they purchase shares of stock in the corporation that owns the building and receive a proprietary lease to occupy a specific unit.", "There is no such thing as a shared \\"master title certificate\\" for condo owners. Because each condo unit is legally recognized as an entirely separate parcel of real estate, each requires its own individual deed."]}	36	chapter	2026-03-15 18:59:07.367	2026-03-15 19:09:35.091	\N	\N	\N	\N	/audio/1773601768525-A_condominium_is_cla.mp3	/timestamps/1773601768525-A_condominium_is_cla.timestamps.json	["/audio/1773601770926-This_option_describe.mp3", "", "/audio/1773601773476-This_option_describe.mp3", "/audio/1773601774941-There_is_no_such_thi.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1773601770926-This_option_describe.timestamps.json", "", "/timestamps/1773601773476-This_option_describe.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1773601774941-There_is_no_such_thi.timestamps.json"]	["/audio/1773601762646-A_proprietary_lease_.mp3", "/audio/1773601763588-A_deed_to_the_specif.mp3", "/audio/1773601764623-Shares_of_corporate_.mp3", "/audio/1773601765518-A_master_title_certi.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1773601762646-A_proprietary_lease_.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1773601763588-A_deed_to_the_specif.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1773601764623-Shares_of_corporate_.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1773601765518-A_master_title_certi.timestamps.json"]	/audio/1773601761686-When_a_purchaser_acq.mp3	/timestamps/1773601761686-When_a_purchaser_acq.timestamps.json
cmltr782100oxr4evpoqro5q4	cmlslqsgt00l1r4evfhnwe7be	A sales associate is working with a buyer. Who has the legal authority to direct and control the associate's actions?	{"The buyer, since they are the customer","The sales associate themselves, as an independent contractor","The employing broker","The Florida Real Estate Commission (FREC) directly"}	2	{"correct": "Sales associates (and broker associates) must always work under the direction and control of their employing broker.", "incorrect": ["The buyer is a customer or principal, but they do not employ or supervise the licensee.", "While independent contractors for tax purposes, legally they are subordinates to the broker.", "", "FREC regulates the license law but does not manage daily business activities."]}	2	chapter	2026-02-19 17:47:24.937	2026-02-19 19:56:17.494	\N	\N	\N	\N	/audio/1771530972770-Sales_associates__an.mp3	/timestamps/1771530972770-Sales_associates__an.timestamps.json	["/audio/1771530974004-The_buyer_is_a_custo.mp3", "/audio/1771530975033-While_independent_co.mp3", "", "/audio/1771530977290-FREC_regulates_the_l.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1771530974004-The_buyer_is_a_custo.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771530975033-While_independent_co.timestamps.json", "", "/timestamps/1771530977290-FREC_regulates_the_l.timestamps.json"]	["/audio/1771530967732-The_buyer__since_the.mp3", "/audio/1771530968705-The_sales_associate_.mp3", "/audio/1771530969288-The_employing_broker.mp3", "/audio/1771530970531-The_Florida_Real_Est.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1771530967732-The_buyer__since_the.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771530968705-The_sales_associate_.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771530969288-The_employing_broker.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771530970531-The_Florida_Real_Est.timestamps.json"]	/audio/1771530966557-A_sales_associate_is.mp3	/timestamps/1771530966557-A_sales_associate_is.timestamps.json
cmms4dv2x00j54be7epd0z80m	cmmry1yz800fh4be796sih9l4	Which of the following statements does NOT accurately describe a legal characteristic or benefit of the Florida constitutional homestead exemption?	{"It provides protection from forced sale by judgment creditors for the nonpayment of certain personal debts","It allows for a tax deduction of up to $50,000 from the assessed value of the homesteaded property, provided it is properly claimed.","It guarantees that the property is fully protected from foreclosure in the event of unpaid property taxes or a defaulted mortgage","It mandates that the claimants must hold legal or equitable title to the property and use the home as their principal residence."}	2	{"correct": "The Florida homestead exemption is incredibly powerful, but it does not protect a homeowner from forced sale if the debt is tied directly to the property itself. Unpaid property taxes, special assessments, mortgages, and construction liens can absolutely result in a forced sale.", "incorrect": ["The law shields the home from outside judgment creditors (like credit card companies or medical bills), offers a significant property tax reduction (up to $50,000 depending on the property's value), and strictly requires that the owner actually holds title and lives there as their primary, permanent residence.", "The law shields the home from outside judgment creditors (like credit card companies or medical bills), offers a significant property tax reduction (up to $50,000 depending on the property's value), and strictly requires that the owner actually holds title and lives there as their primary, permanent residence.", "", "The law shields the home from outside judgment creditors (like credit card companies or medical bills), offers a significant property tax reduction (up to $50,000 depending on the property's value), and strictly requires that the owner actually holds title and lives there as their primary, permanent residence."]}	37	chapter	2026-03-15 19:00:39.704	2026-03-15 19:09:54.428	\N	\N	\N	\N	/audio/1773601785356-The_Florida_homestea.mp3	/timestamps/1773601785356-The_Florida_homestea.timestamps.json	["/audio/1773601788835-The_law_shields_the_.mp3", "/audio/1773601791560-The_law_shields_the_.mp3", "", "/audio/1773601794171-The_law_shields_the_.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1773601788835-The_law_shields_the_.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1773601791560-The_law_shields_the_.timestamps.json", "", "/timestamps/1773601794171-The_law_shields_the_.timestamps.json"]	["/audio/1773601778262-It_provides_protecti.mp3", "/audio/1773601779803-It_allows_for_a_tax_.mp3", "/audio/1773601781135-It_guarantees_that_t.mp3", "/audio/1773601782797-It_mandates_that_the.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1773601778262-It_provides_protecti.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1773601779803-It_allows_for_a_tax_.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1773601781135-It_guarantees_that_t.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1773601782797-It_mandates_that_the.timestamps.json"]	/audio/1773601776916-Which_of_the_followi.mp3	/timestamps/1773601776916-Which_of_the_followi.timestamps.json
cmltrbkdf00ozr4evmiqyquy4	cmlslqsgt00l1r4evfhnwe7be	Can a sales associate open their own office to meet clients closer to their home?	{"Yes, if they register it as a branch office","Yes, if they pay the office rent themselves","No, sales associates may not have offices of their own and must work from the broker’s office","No, unless they hold a broker associate license"}	2	{"correct": "Sales associates are prohibited from having independent offices. They must operate out of the broker's registered principal or branch office.", "incorrect": ["Only a broker can register a branch office.", "Who pays the rent does not change the rule; associates cannot operate independently.", "", "Broker associates also cannot have their own offices; they must work under the employing broker."]}	3	chapter	2026-02-19 17:50:47.522	2026-02-19 19:56:27.179	\N	\N	\N	\N	/audio/1771530984177-Sales_associates_are.mp3	/timestamps/1771530984177-Sales_associates_are.timestamps.json	["/audio/1771530985017-Only_a_broker_can_re.mp3", "/audio/1771530985957-Who_pays_the_rent_do.mp3", "", "/audio/1771530987028-Broker_associates_al.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1771530985017-Only_a_broker_can_re.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771530985957-Who_pays_the_rent_do.timestamps.json", "", "/timestamps/1771530987028-Broker_associates_al.timestamps.json"]	["/audio/1771530979593-Yes__if_they_registe.mp3", "/audio/1771530980858-Yes__if_they_pay_the.mp3", "/audio/1771530981825-No__sales_associates.mp3", "/audio/1771530982704-No__unless_they_hold.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1771530979593-Yes__if_they_registe.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771530980858-Yes__if_they_pay_the.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771530981825-No__sales_associates.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771530982704-No__unless_they_hold.timestamps.json"]	/audio/1771530978824-Can_a_sales_associat.mp3	/timestamps/1771530978824-Can_a_sales_associat.timestamps.json
cmlpq0owc00iyr4ev4h775vx2	cmlpniy5e00gyr4ev7l7y4vur	The brokerage relationship disclosure requirements outlined in Chapter 475, F.S., would legally apply to which of the following transactions?	{"The sale of a 50-unit apartment building","The sale of a single family home","A residential lease of a condo","The sale of a cloud storage and hosting business including real property"}	1	{"correct": "The disclosure requirements apply specifically to residential sales. Florida law defines a residential sale as the sale of improved residential property of four or fewer units. A single condominium unit fits this definition perfectly, so the disclosure is mandatory.", "incorrect": ["A 20-unit apartment complex is considered commercial (non-residential) property because it exceeds the 4-unit limit. Therefore, the residential disclosure forms are not required.", "", "Lease agreements are generally exempt from brokerage relationship disclosure requirements, unless the lease includes an option to purchase the property.", "The sale of a business opportunity (like a bookstore) is generally considered a commercial transaction or a business brokerage activity, which is exempt from the specific residential relationship disclosure mandates."]}	4	chapter	2026-02-16 22:03:15.781	2026-02-16 23:15:35.397	\N	\N	\N	\N	/audio/1771283730485-The_disclosure_requi.mp3	/timestamps/1771283730485-The_disclosure_requi.timestamps.json	["/audio/1771283732188-A_20_unit_apartment_.mp3", "", "/audio/1771283733407-Lease_agreements_are.mp3", "/audio/1771283735248-The_sale_of_a_busine.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1771283732188-A_20_unit_apartment_.timestamps.json", "", "/timestamps/1771283733407-Lease_agreements_are.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771283735248-The_sale_of_a_busine.timestamps.json"]	["/audio/1771283726319-The_sale_of_a_50_uni.mp3", "/audio/1771283726931-The_sale_of_a_single.mp3", "/audio/1771283727491-A_residential_lease_.mp3", "/audio/1771283728365-The_sale_of_a_cloud_.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1771283726319-The_sale_of_a_50_uni.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771283726931-The_sale_of_a_single.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771283727491-A_residential_lease_.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771283728365-The_sale_of_a_cloud_.timestamps.json"]	/audio/1771283725556-The_brokerage_relati.mp3	/timestamps/1771283725556-The_brokerage_relati.timestamps.json
cmlpq7lyv00j4r4ev9u7ts7aj	cmlpniy5e00gyr4ev7l7y4vur	When representing a seller of a home, which statement most accurately defines the fiduciary duty of "Loyalty" within a Single Agent relationship?&nbsp;	{"The broker is obligated to place the principal's financial and personal interests above all others, including their own","The broker is required to reveal any hidden property defects to potential buyers","The broker must possess and apply professional knowledge regarding the property's physical characteristics","The broker must properly handle and keep records of all money entrusted to them during the transaction"}	0	{"correct": "Loyalty is the fiduciary duty that requires the agent to act strictly in the best interest of the principal. This means the agent must prioritize the client's gain over their own commission or the interests of the other party.", "incorrect": ["", "Disclosing latent (hidden) defects is a duty of Honesty and Disclosure. This is a general duty owed to everyone (even customers/buyers you don't represent) to prevent fraud; it is not the definition of loyalty to a client.", "Knowing the details of the land and property falls under the duty of Using Skill, Care, and Diligence. This ensures the agent is competent, but it is distinct from the ethical requirement of loyalty.", "Keeping track of money falls under the duty of Accounting for all funds. This is a logistical duty required in all brokerage relationships, not a specific test of loyalty."]}	7	chapter	2026-02-16 22:08:38.647	2026-02-16 23:16:04.661	\N	\N	\N	\N	/audio/1771283759493-Loyalty_is_the_fiduc.mp3	/timestamps/1771283759493-Loyalty_is_the_fiduc.timestamps.json	["", "/audio/1771283761645-Disclosing_latent__h.mp3", "/audio/1771283763190-Knowing_the_details_.mp3", "/audio/1771283764513-Keeping_track_of_mon.mp3"]	["", "/timestamps/1771283761645-Disclosing_latent__h.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771283763190-Knowing_the_details_.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771283764513-Keeping_track_of_mon.timestamps.json"]	["/audio/1771283754458-The_broker_is_obliga.mp3", "/audio/1771283755474-The_broker_is_requir.mp3", "/audio/1771283756606-The_broker_must_poss.mp3", "/audio/1771283757665-The_broker_must_prop.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1771283754458-The_broker_is_obliga.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771283755474-The_broker_is_requir.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771283756606-The_broker_must_poss.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771283757665-The_broker_must_prop.timestamps.json"]	/audio/1771283753290-When_representing_a_.mp3	/timestamps/1771283753290-When_representing_a_.timestamps.json
cmmqevht2002i4be7ylc0d42y	cmmqbpz7v00044be7x0za79d7	The Civil Rights Act of 1964 is best known for ending segregation in which area?	{"Private residential housing","Public accommodations and facilities","Private clubs","Religious organizations"}	1	{"correct": "The Civil Rights Act of 1964 ended segregation in places of public accommodation (hotels, restaurants, gas stations) and workplaces.", "incorrect": ["Discrimination in private residential housing was addressed later by the 1968 Fair Housing Act.", "", "Private clubs are often exempt from public accommodation laws.", "Religious organizations were not the primary target of the public accommodation desegregation provisions."]}	1	chapter	2026-03-14 14:18:46.117	2026-03-14 23:11:20.913	\N	\N	\N	\N	/audio/1773529877511-The_Civil_Rights_Act.mp3	/timestamps/1773529877511-The_Civil_Rights_Act.timestamps.json	["/audio/1773529878652-Discrimination_in_pr.mp3", "", "/audio/1773529879520-Private_clubs_are_of.mp3", "/audio/1773529880760-Religious_organizati.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1773529878652-Discrimination_in_pr.timestamps.json", "", "/timestamps/1773529879520-Private_clubs_are_of.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1773529880760-Religious_organizati.timestamps.json"]	["/audio/1773529873271-Private_residential_.mp3", "/audio/1773529874118-Public_accommodation.mp3", "/audio/1773529874610-Private_clubs.mp3", "/audio/1773529875308-Religious_organizati.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1773529873271-Private_residential_.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1773529874118-Public_accommodation.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1773529874610-Private_clubs.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1773529875308-Religious_organizati.timestamps.json"]	/audio/1773529872543-The_Civil_Rights_Act.mp3	/timestamps/1773529872543-The_Civil_Rights_Act.timestamps.json
cmlpsab7x00jyr4evfosv04lr	cmlpniy5e00gyr4ev7l7y4vur	Which of the following is an example of a "General Agency" relationship?	{"A brokerage company hired by a seller under a listing agreement","The relationship between an employing broker and their broker associate","A sales associate working with a prospective buyer to find a house","General Agent is authorized to perform acts associated with the continued operations of a particular business. A sales associate (or broker associate) is a general agent of their employing broker because they represent the broker on an ongoing basis in multiple transactions."}	1	{"correct": "General Agent is authorized to perform acts associated with the continued operations of a particular business. A sales associate (or broker associate) is a general agent of their employing broker because they represent the broker on an ongoing basis in multiple transactions.", "incorrect": ["A listing agreement creates a Special Agency relationship. The broker is hired for one specific act (sell this house), and the authority ends when that act is done.", "", "This is typically a Special Agency (if Single Agent) or no agency, focused on specific transactions, not ongoing general authority.", "The sales associate is the agent of the broker, not the general agent of the seller. The link to the seller is through the broker."]}	22	chapter	2026-02-16 23:06:43.916	2026-02-16 23:18:34.8	\N	\N	\N	\N	/audio/1771283910693-General_Agent_is_aut.mp3	/timestamps/1771283910693-General_Agent_is_aut.timestamps.json	["/audio/1771283912246-A_listing_agreement_.mp3", "", "/audio/1771283913554-This_is_typically_a_.mp3", "/audio/1771283914649-The_sales_associate_.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1771283912246-A_listing_agreement_.timestamps.json", "", "/timestamps/1771283913554-This_is_typically_a_.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771283914649-The_sales_associate_.timestamps.json"]	["/audio/1771283904526-A_brokerage_company_.mp3", "/audio/1771283905412-The_relationship_bet.mp3", "/audio/1771283906234-A_sales_associate_wo.mp3", "/audio/1771283908325-General_Agent_is_aut.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1771283904526-A_brokerage_company_.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771283905412-The_relationship_bet.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771283906234-A_sales_associate_wo.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771283908325-General_Agent_is_aut.timestamps.json"]	/audio/1771283903699-Which_of_the_followi.mp3	/timestamps/1771283903699-Which_of_the_followi.timestamps.json
cmlpsi5o400k2r4evbhven50g	cmlpniy5e00gyr4ev7l7y4vur	Which duty is a real estate licensee obligated to perform in ALL THREE brokerage relationships (Single Agent, Transaction Broker, and No Brokerage)?	{Loyalty,"Full disclosure"," Deal honestly and fairly","Perform additional duties that are mutually agreed to"}	2	{"correct": "The duty to Deal Honestly and Fairly is universal. Whether you are a fiduciary, a neutral facilitator, or non-representative, you are never allowed to be dishonest or unfair.", "incorrect": ["Loyalty is exclusive to Single Agents", "Full Disclosure is exclusive to Single Agents", "", "\\"Perform additional duties mutually agreed to\\" is technically listed as a duty for Transaction Brokers. While you can agree to things in other relationships, this specific statutory phrasing is associated with Transaction Brokers"]}	24	chapter	2026-02-16 23:12:49.972	2026-02-16 23:18:54.505	\N	\N	\N	\N	/audio/1771283930617-The_duty_to_Deal_Hon.mp3	/timestamps/1771283930617-The_duty_to_Deal_Hon.timestamps.json	["/audio/1771283931570-Loyalty_is_exclusive.mp3", "/audio/1771283932400-Full_Disclosure_is_e.mp3", "", "/audio/1771283934355-_Perform_additional_.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1771283931570-Loyalty_is_exclusive.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771283932400-Full_Disclosure_is_e.timestamps.json", "", "/timestamps/1771283934355-_Perform_additional_.timestamps.json"]	["/audio/1771283926845-Loyalty.mp3", "/audio/1771283927389-Full_disclosure.mp3", "/audio/1771283928026-Deal_honestly_and_fa.mp3", "/audio/1771283928896-Perform_additional_d.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1771283926845-Loyalty.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771283927389-Full_disclosure.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771283928026-Deal_honestly_and_fa.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771283928896-Perform_additional_d.timestamps.json"]	/audio/1771283926359-Which_duty_is_a_real.mp3	/timestamps/1771283926359-Which_duty_is_a_real.timestamps.json
cmlppcjgs00iqr4ev2kf9c44y	cmlpniy5e00gyr4ev7l7y4vur	Which of the following is NOT an authorized brokerage relationship option in Florida?	{"Nonrepresentation (No Brokerage Relationship)","Single Agent","Dual Agent","Transaction Broker"}	2	{"correct": "Licensees may not operate as dual agents. It’s impossible to  represent both buyer and seller as a fiduciary at the same time.&nbsp;", "incorrect": ["Nonrepresentation is one of the three authorized options where the broker represents neither party.", "Single Agent is listed as an authorized option where the broker represents either the buyer or the seller.", "", "Transaction Broker is listed as an authorized option and is the presumed relationship in Florida."]}	0	chapter	2026-02-16 21:44:29.067	2026-02-16 23:14:52.834	\N	\N	\N	\N	/audio/1771283688585-Licensees_may_not_op.mp3	/timestamps/1771283688585-Licensees_may_not_op.timestamps.json	["/audio/1771283689977-Nonrepresentation_is.mp3", "/audio/1771283691490-Single_Agent_is_list.mp3", "", "/audio/1771283692594-Transaction_Broker_i.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1771283689977-Nonrepresentation_is.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771283691490-Single_Agent_is_list.timestamps.json", "", "/timestamps/1771283692594-Transaction_Broker_i.timestamps.json"]	["/audio/1771283685682-Nonrepresentation__N.mp3", "/audio/1771283686189-Single_Agent.mp3", "/audio/1771283686718-Dual_Agent.mp3", "/audio/1771283687269-Transaction_Broker.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1771283685682-Nonrepresentation__N.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771283686189-Single_Agent.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771283686718-Dual_Agent.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771283687269-Transaction_Broker.timestamps.json"]	/audio/1771283684891-Which_of_the_followi.mp3	/timestamps/1771283684891-Which_of_the_followi.timestamps.json
cmlppewzo00isr4evdronjynp	cmlpniy5e00gyr4ev7l7y4vur	Under Florida law, which brokerage relationship is presumed for all licensees unless another is chosen?	{"Single Agent","Transaction Broker",Nonrepresentation,"Designated Sales Associate"}	1	{"correct": "It is presumed that all licensees are operating as transaction brokers unless another relationship is chosen.", "incorrect": ["Single agency is not the default; it must be established specifically.", "", "Nonrepresentation is an option but not the legal presumption. ", "Designated Sales Associate is a special status for high-asset non-residential deals, not the default presumption."]}	1	chapter	2026-02-16 21:46:19.908	2026-02-16 23:15:01.437	\N	\N	\N	\N	/audio/1771283698001-It_is_presumed_that_.mp3	/timestamps/1771283698001-It_is_presumed_that_.timestamps.json	["/audio/1771283699079-Single_agency_is_not.mp3", "", "/audio/1771283700036-Nonrepresentation_is.mp3", "/audio/1771283701223-Designated_Sales_Ass.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1771283699079-Single_agency_is_not.timestamps.json", "", "/timestamps/1771283700036-Nonrepresentation_is.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771283701223-Designated_Sales_Ass.timestamps.json"]	["/audio/1771283694527-Single_Agent.mp3", "/audio/1771283695249-Transaction_Broker.mp3", "/audio/1771283695864-Nonrepresentation.mp3", "/audio/1771283696578-Designated_Sales_Ass.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1771283694527-Single_Agent.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771283695249-Transaction_Broker.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771283695864-Nonrepresentation.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1771283696578-Designated_Sales_Ass.timestamps.json"]	/audio/1771283693985-Under_Florida_law__w.mp3	/timestamps/1771283693985-Under_Florida_law__w.timestamps.json
cmmqex0o1002k4be77k7jofll	cmmqbpz7v00044be7x0za79d7	Title II of the Civil Rights Act of 1964 specifically prohibits discrimination in places of public accommodation based on all of the following EXCEPT:	{Race," Color",Religion,Sex}	3	{"correct": "Title II of the 1964 Act prohibits discrimination in public accommodations based on Race, Color, Religion, and National Origin. Sex was not included in Title II (though it was included in Title VII regarding employment).", "incorrect": ["Race, Color, and Religion are all protected classes under Title II of the 1964 Act.", "Race, Color, and Religion are all protected classes under Title II of the 1964 Act.", "Race, Color, and Religion are all protected classes under Title II of the 1964 Act.", ""]}	2	chapter	2026-03-14 14:19:57.216	2026-03-14 23:11:32.09	\N	\N	\N	\N	/audio/1773529887459-Title_II_of_the_1964.mp3	/timestamps/1773529887459-Title_II_of_the_1964.timestamps.json	["/audio/1773529888968-Race__Color__and_Rel.mp3", "/audio/1773529890527-Race__Color__and_Rel.mp3", "/audio/1773529891870-Race__Color__and_Rel.mp3", ""]	["/timestamps/1773529888968-Race__Color__and_Rel.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1773529890527-Race__Color__and_Rel.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1773529891870-Race__Color__and_Rel.timestamps.json", ""]	["/audio/1773529883303-Race.mp3", "/audio/1773529883898-Color.mp3", "/audio/1773529884427-Religion.mp3", "/audio/1773529885027-Sex.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1773529883303-Race.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1773529883898-Color.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1773529884427-Religion.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1773529885027-Sex.timestamps.json"]	/audio/1773529882772-Title_II_of_the_Civi.mp3	/timestamps/1773529882772-Title_II_of_the_Civi.timestamps.json
cmlppipk300iur4evt9a82waj	cmlpniy5e00gyr4ev7l7y4vur	A brokerage firm is acting as a Single Agent for a buyer. The buyer wants to purchase a home that is listed by the same brokerage firm, which is currently acting as a Single Agent for the seller. To legally allow this in-house transaction to proceed, what must happen?	{"The broker must remain a Single Agent for the seller and become a Transaction Broker for the buyer","The broker may continue as a Single Agent for both parties","The broker may assume any relationship agreed to by both parties","Both the seller and the buyer must transition to a transaction broker relationship"}	3	{"correct": "In Florida, a broker cannot be a fiduciary (Single Agent) for both the buyer and the seller in the same transaction, as this creates a conflict of interest. To proceed legally, the broker must obtain written consent from both parties to \\"step down\\" from the Single Agent role and become a Transaction Broker for both. This allows the broker to facilitate the deal neutrally.", "incorrect": ["It is not possible to be a Single Agent for one party and a Transaction Broker for the other in the same deal. The fiduciary duties owed to the Single Agent client (Loyalty, Full Disclosure) would prevent the broker from acting neutrally and fairly toward the Transaction Broker client.", "Representing both parties as a Single Agent is called Dual Agency, which is illegal in Florida residential transactions. You cannot owe \\"undivided loyalty\\" to two opposing sides.", "Parties cannot \\"agree\\" to violate the law. Since Dual Agency is prohibited by statute, the buyer and seller cannot sign a contract allowing it.", ""]}	2	chapter	2026-02-16 21:49:16.899	2026-02-16 23:15:15.468	\N	\N	\N	\N	/audio/1771283709948-In_Florida__a_broker.mp3	/timestamps/1771283709948-In_Florida__a_broker.timestamps.json	["/audio/1771283712262-It_is_not_possible_t.mp3", "/audio/1771283713779-Representing_both_pa.mp3", "/audio/1771283715220-Parties_cannot__agre.