cmms2k3hy00i54be7uk6jvmru	cmmry1yz800fh4be796sih9l4	A developer of a condominium with MORE than 20 residential units must provide buyers with a:	{"Proprietary Lease",Prospectus,"Governance Form","Copy of the deed only"}	1	{"correct": "Developers of 20+ units must file a Prospectus (a summary of the condo offering) and give it to purchasers.", "incorrect": ["Proprietary Lease is for Co-ops.", "", "Governance Form is required for all resales, but the Prospectus is the specific requirement for large developer projects.", "Copy of the deed only is Insufficient disclosure."]}	19	chapter	2026-03-15 18:09:31.318	2026-03-15 19:05:30.566	\N	\N	\N	\N	/audio/1773601527106-Developers_of_20__un.mp3	/timestamps/1773601527106-Developers_of_20__un.timestamps.json	["/audio/1773601527981-Proprietary_Lease_is.mp3", "", "/audio/1773601529454-Governance_Form_is_r.mp3", "/audio/1773601530297-Copy_of_the_deed_onl.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1773601527981-Proprietary_Lease_is.timestamps.json", "", "/timestamps/1773601529454-Governance_Form_is_r.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1773601530297-Copy_of_the_deed_onl.timestamps.json"]	["/audio/1773601523547-Proprietary_Lease.mp3", "/audio/1773601524199-Prospectus.mp3", "/audio/1773601524675-Governance_Form.mp3", "/audio/1773601525530-Copy_of_the_deed_onl.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1773601523547-Proprietary_Lease.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1773601524199-Prospectus.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1773601524675-Governance_Form.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1773601525530-Copy_of_the_deed_onl.timestamps.json"]	/audio/1773601522845-A_developer_of_a_con.mp3	/timestamps/1773601522845-A_developer_of_a_con.timestamps.json
cmms2crdq00hz4be75ifqf29z	cmmry1yz800fh4be796sih9l4	Which of the following is a benefit of Homestead protections in Florida?	{"Protection from all debts including mortgage foreclosure","Protection from property taxes","Protection from forced sale for personal debts (like credit cards)","Exemption from HOA rules"}	2	{"correct": "Homestead protects the home from forced sale to satisfy personal judgments (credit cards, medical bills).", "incorrect": ["It does not protect against mortgages or construction liens.", "You get a tax exemption (reduction in value), but not total protection from paying taxes.", "", "Homestead does not protect against HOA foreclosures."]}	16	chapter	2026-03-15 18:03:48.963	2026-03-15 19:05:02.79	\N	\N	\N	\N	/audio/1773601498799-Homestead_protects_t.mp3	/timestamps/1773601498799-Homestead_protects_t.timestamps.json	["/audio/1773601499949-It_does_not_protect_.mp3", "/audio/1773601501567-You_get_a_tax_exempt.mp3", "", "/audio/1773601502573-Homestead_does_not_p.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1773601499949-It_does_not_protect_.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1773601501567-You_get_a_tax_exempt.timestamps.json", "", "/timestamps/1773601502573-Homestead_does_not_p.timestamps.json"]	["/audio/1773601494398-Protection_from_all_.mp3", "/audio/1773601495291-Protection_from_prop.mp3", "/audio/1773601496191-Protection_from_forc.mp3", "/audio/1773601497014-Exemption_from_HOA_r.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1773601494398-Protection_from_all_.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1773601495291-Protection_from_prop.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1773601496191-Protection_from_forc.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1773601497014-Exemption_from_HOA_r.timestamps.json"]	/audio/1773601493511-Which_of_the_followi.mp3	/timestamps/1773601493511-Which_of_the_followi.timestamps.json
cmms2es2600i14be7laxjuesq	cmmry1yz800fh4be796sih9l4	When purchasing a Cooperative (Co-op), the buyer receives:	{"A Deed to the unit","Shares of stock and a proprietary lease","Fee simple ownership of the unit"," A time-share interval"}	1	{"correct": "In a Co-op, the corporation owns the building. The buyer gets stock in the corporation and a proprietary lease to live in the unit.", "incorrect": ["Deeds are for Condos, not Co-ops.", "", "Fee Simple ownership are for Condos, not Co-ops.", "Time-shares are a different ownership structure entirely."]}	17	chapter	2026-03-15 18:05:23.214	2026-03-15 19:05:11.91	\N	\N	\N	\N	/audio/1773601508672-In_a_Co_op__the_corp.mp3	/timestamps/1773601508672-In_a_Co_op__the_corp.timestamps.json	["/audio/1773601509640-Deeds_are_for_Condos.mp3", "", "/audio/1773601510547-Fee_Simple_ownership.mp3", "/audio/1773601511759-Time_shares_are_a_di.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1773601509640-Deeds_are_for_Condos.timestamps.json", "", "/timestamps/1773601510547-Fee_Simple_ownership.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1773601511759-Time_shares_are_a_di.timestamps.json"]	["/audio/1773601504769-A_Deed_to_the_unit.mp3", "/audio/1773601505599-Shares_of_stock_and_.mp3", "/audio/1773601506438-Fee_simple_ownership.mp3", "/audio/1773601507011-A_time_share_interva.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1773601504769-A_Deed_to_the_unit.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1773601505599-Shares_of_stock_and_.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1773601506438-Fee_simple_ownership.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1773601507011-A_time_share_interva.timestamps.json"]	/audio/1773601504056-When_purchasing_a_Co.mp3	/timestamps/1773601504056-When_purchasing_a_Co.timestamps.json
cmms2hbuk00i34be73hnnyist	cmmry1yz800fh4be796sih9l4	A Condominium is created by recording which document?	{"The Proprietary Lease","The Declaration of Condominium","The Articles of Incorporation only","The Bylaws only"}	1	{"correct": "The Declaration of Condominium is the legal document recorded in public records that actually creates the condominium entity.", "incorrect": ["The Proprietary Lease is used in Co-ops.", "", "The Articles of Incorporation is for creating the Association, but not the Condo units themselves.", "These are the rules of operation, not the creating document."]}	18	chapter	2026-03-15 18:07:22.172	2026-03-15 19:05:21.187	\N	\N	\N	\N	/audio/1773601517771-The_Declaration_of_C.mp3	/timestamps/1773601517771-The_Declaration_of_C.timestamps.json	["/audio/1773601518976-The_Proprietary_Leas.mp3", "", "/audio/1773601520166-The_Articles_of_Inco.mp3", "/audio/1773601521026-These_are_the_rules_.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1773601518976-The_Proprietary_Leas.timestamps.json", "", "/timestamps/1773601520166-The_Articles_of_Inco.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1773601521026-These_are_the_rules_.timestamps.json"]	["/audio/1773601513843-The_Proprietary_Leas.mp3", "/audio/1773601514662-The_Declaration_of_C.mp3", "/audio/1773601515444-The_Articles_of_Inco.mp3", "/audio/1773601516069-The_Bylaws_only.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1773601513843-The_Proprietary_Leas.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1773601514662-The_Declaration_of_C.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1773601515444-The_Articles_of_Inco.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1773601516069-The_Bylaws_only.timestamps.json"]	/audio/1773601513127-A_Condominium_is_cre.mp3	/timestamps/1773601513127-A_Condominium_is_cre.timestamps.json
cmms2pl0r00ib4be7li0xpz9t	cmmry1yz800fh4be796sih9l4	The physical components of real property include all of the following, EXCEPT:	{"Surface rights","Air rights","Subsurface rights","Equitable rights"}	3	{"correct": "Equitable rights (along with the legal \\"bundle of rights\\") are intangible legal concepts and interests, not tangible, physical parts of the real estate itself.", "incorrect": ["In Florida real estate law, the physical components of land and real property are strictly defined in three physical dimensions: the surface of the earth (surface rights), the space above the property up to a reasonable height (air rights), and the space below the surface down to the center of the earth (subsurface or mineral rights).", "In Florida real estate law, the physical components of land and real property are strictly defined in three physical dimensions: the surface of the earth (surface rights), the space above the property up to a reasonable height (air rights), and the space below the surface down to the center of the earth (subsurface or mineral rights).", "In Florida real estate law, the physical components of land and real property are strictly defined in three physical dimensions: the surface of the earth (surface rights), the space above the property up to a reasonable height (air rights), and the space below the surface down to the center of the earth (subsurface or mineral rights).", ""]}	22	chapter	2026-03-15 18:13:47.307	2026-03-15 19:06:03.267	\N	\N	\N	\N	/audio/1773601554272-Equitable_rights__al.mp3	/timestamps/1773601554272-Equitable_rights__al.timestamps.json	["/audio/1773601556829-In_Florida_real_esta.mp3", "/audio/1773601560090-In_Florida_real_esta.mp3", "/audio/1773601563106-In_Florida_real_esta.mp3", ""]	["/timestamps/1773601556829-In_Florida_real_esta.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1773601560090-In_Florida_real_esta.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1773601563106-In_Florida_real_esta.timestamps.json", ""]	["/audio/1773601550520-Surface_rights.mp3", "/audio/1773601551094-Air_rights.mp3", "/audio/1773601551704-Subsurface_rights.mp3", "/audio/1773601552367-Equitable_rights.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1773601550520-Surface_rights.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1773601551094-Air_rights.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1773601551704-Subsurface_rights.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1773601552367-Equitable_rights.timestamps.json"]	/audio/1773601549965-The_physical_compone.mp3	/timestamps/1773601549965-The_physical_compone.timestamps.json
cmms2r29400id4be7wsk0v6fe	cmmry1yz800fh4be796sih9l4	By legal definition, a fixture in real estate is an item that:	{"Was once personal property but has been attached to and incorporated into the real property","Is completely movable and strictly retains its status as personal property during a sale.","Is an intangible legal privilege associated with the ownership of the land, such as air rights","Is a piece of equipment installed by a commercial tenant that must be removed before the lease expires"}	0	{"correct": "A fixture is defined as an item that was originally personal property (like a ceiling fan still in its box), but has been permanently fixed, attached, or incorporated into the real estate (like wiring that ceiling fan into the living room ceiling). Once attached, it legally becomes part of the real property and transfers with the sale of the home.", "incorrect": ["", "Items that are completely movable and unattached (like a freestanding couch or a lawnmower) are classified as personal property (or chattel), not fixtures.", "Intangible legal privileges (like air rights, surface rights, or the bundle of rights) are concepts of ownership, not physical physical items that were attached to the land.", "This specifically describes a trade fixture, which is a special exception in commercial real estate. Unlike standard fixtures, trade fixtures remain the personal property of the tenant and can be removed."]}	23	chapter	2026-03-15 18:14:56.296	2026-03-15 19:06:18.353	\N	\N	\N	\N	/audio/1773601572599-A_fixture_is_defined.mp3	/timestamps/1773601572599-A_fixture_is_defined.timestamps.json	["", "/audio/1773601574489-Items_that_are_compl.mp3", "/audio/1773601576561-Intangible_legal_pri.mp3", "/audio/1773601578151-This_specifically_de.mp3"]	["", "/timestamps/1773601574489-Items_that_are_compl.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1773601576561-Intangible_legal_pri.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1773601578151-This_specifically_de.timestamps.json"]	["/audio/1773601565802-Was_once_personal_pr.mp3", "/audio/1773601567050-Is_completely_movabl.mp3", "/audio/1773601568053-Is_an_intangible_leg.mp3", "/audio/1773601569271-Is_a_piece_of_equipm.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1773601565802-Was_once_personal_pr.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1773601567050-Is_completely_movabl.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1773601568053-Is_an_intangible_leg.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1773601569271-Is_a_piece_of_equipm.timestamps.json"]	/audio/1773601564613-By_legal_definition_.mp3	/timestamps/1773601564613-By_legal_definition_.timestamps.json
cmms3lx2m00ih4be7h8im7tw3	cmmry1yz800fh4be796sih9l4	The legal "bundle of rights" associated with real property ownership includes all of the following, EXCEPT:	{"The right of possession","The right of utility","The right of disposition","The right of exclusion"}	1	{"correct": "Utility is not a legal right of ownership. Instead, \\"utility\\" is one of the four economic characteristics of value (along with Demand, Scarcity, and Transferability).", "incorrect": ["The legal rights attached to real property ownership are often memorized using the acronym DEEP C: Disposition (the right to sell or will the property), Enjoyment (the right to use the property without outside interference), Exclusion (the right to keep others from trespassing), Possession (the right to occupy the property), and Control (the right to physically alter or build on the property, within legal limits).", "", "The legal rights attached to real property ownership are often memorized using the acronym DEEP C: Disposition (the right to sell or will the property), Enjoyment (the right to use the property without outside interference), Exclusion (the right to keep others from trespassing), Possession (the right to occupy the property), and Control (the right to physically alter or build on the property, within legal limits).", "The legal rights attached to real property ownership are often memorized using the acronym DEEP C: Disposition (the right to sell or will the property), Enjoyment (the right to use the property without outside interference), Exclusion (the right to keep others from trespassing), Possession (the right to occupy the property), and Control (the right to physically alter or build on the property, within legal limits)."]}	25	chapter	2026-03-15 18:38:55.918	2026-03-15 19:06:52.158	\N	\N	\N	\N	/audio/1773601600855-Utility_is_not_a_leg.mp3	/timestamps/1773601600855-Utility_is_not_a_leg.timestamps.json	["/audio/1773601604682-The_legal_rights_att.mp3", "", "/audio/1773601608130-The_legal_rights_att.mp3", "/audio/1773601611907-The_legal_rights_att.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1773601604682-The_legal_rights_att.timestamps.json", "", "/timestamps/1773601608130-The_legal_rights_att.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1773601611907-The_legal_rights_att.timestamps.json"]	["/audio/1773601596820-The_right_of_possess.mp3", "/audio/1773601597417-The_right_of_utility.mp3", "/audio/1773601598031-The_right_of_disposi.mp3", "/audio/1773601598719-The_right_of_exclusi.mp3"]	["/timestamps/1773601596820-The_right_of_possess.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1773601597417-The_right_of_utility.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1773601598031-The_right_of_disposi.timestamps.json", "/timestamps/1773601598719-The_right_of_exclusi.timestamps.json"]	/audio/1773601596236-The_legal__bundle_of.mp3	/timestamps/1773601596236-The_legal__bundle_of.timestamps.json
